Text: Sebelum saya nak share tips buat azam tahun baru, saya nak share kenapa azam tahun baru selalu gagal.
Translated Text: Before I want to share tips for making new year's resolutions, I want to share why new year's resolutions always fail.

Text: 1st sebab azam tu kita buat based on what someone else (or society) is telling you to change. Bukan apa yg betul2 kita azamkan. Kita tak fokus utk diri sendiri
Translated Text: 1st because we make that resolution based on what someone else (or society) is telling you to change. It's not what we really want. We don't focus on ourselves

Text: 2nd sebab azam tu too vague. Kita kena buat azam yg membumi. Jangan berkerawang yang terlalu melangit. Kena sedar juga limit & kemampuan kita
Translated Text: 2nd because the resolution is too vague. We have to make an earthy resolve. Don't look too extravagant. Be aware of the limits & our ability

Text: 3rd sebab azam tu tak specific. Kalau tak specific mmg susah utk kita fokus
Translated Text: 3rd because the resolution is not specific. If it's not specific, it's hard for us to focus

Text: Ok jum baca tips nak buat azam tahun baru pulak
Translated Text: Ok, read the tips to make a new year's resolution

Text: 1st azam mestilah specific. Dan clear. Contoh nak sale 20k/month. Kena pecahkan pula per week nak berapa sale, sehari kena berapa sale pulak. Bila besar sgt nmpk mcm tak achievable. Tp bila kita kecikkan, nmpk lg clear & achiveable kan?
Translated Text: 1st resolution must be specific. And clear. Example of selling 20k/month. I have to break down how many sales per week, how many sales per day. When it's very big, it seems like it's not achievable. But when we make it smaller, it looks clear & achievable right?

Text: 2nd is measurable. Yup azam mesti something that can be measuared. Kalau tak nanti akan jd mencaPAH SGT & akhirnya jd melangit and end up will be too vague
Translated Text: 2nd is measurable. Yup, azam must be something that can be measured. If not, later you will achieve SGT & finally jd skyrocketed and end up will be too vague

Text: 3rd is achievable. Ini bukanlah bermaksud kita tak boleh ada azam yg besar. Tp kita mestilah realistik. Nak ada simpanan 20% ada realistic & achivable. Tp kalau nak buat 80% saving dr gaji kan tak realistik?
Translated Text: 3rd is achievable. This does not mean that we cannot have great determination. But we must be realistic. If you want to have 20% savings, there is realistic & achievable. But if you want to save 80% from your salary, isn't it realistic?

Text: 4th is relevant. Kita kena tanya diri kita kenapa kita nak berazam mcm ni. Adakah utk diri kita? Kalau kita ada niat yg menyimpang utk sesuatu azam tu, baik reset niat kita. Biarlah azam tu utk pembaikan diri kita. Bukan sebab2 lain yg negatif
Translated Text: 4th is relevant. We have to ask ourselves why we want to be determined like this. Is it for ourselves? If we have a deviant intention for something, it's good to reset our intention. Let that resolve to improve ourselves. Not other negative reasons

Text: Last is time bound. Selain azam mestilah yg achievable, the timeline toward reaching your goal should be realistic, too. That means giving yourself enough time to do it with lots of smaller intermediate goals set up along the way.
Translated Text: Last is time bound. Selain azam mestilah yg achievable, the timeline toward reaching your goal should be realistic, too. That means giving yourself enough time to do it with lots of smaller intermediate goals set up along the way.

Text: “Focus on these small wins so you can make gradual progress”
Translated Text: “Focus on these small wins so you can make gradual progress”

Text: Banjir di negara kita pun kita bantu, saudara kita di Syria pun kita bantu. InshaAllah kami cuba berikan yang terbaik.
Translated Text: We also help the flood in our country, we also help our brothers in Syria. InshaAllah we try to give the best.

Text: Pertolongan Allah kepada seseorang juga tergantung pada pertolongan yang dilakukan kita antara manusia. “Sesungguhnya Allah akan menolong seorang hamba-Nya selama hamba itu menolong orang lain.” (Hadith Muslim, Abu Daud Dan Tirmidzi).
Translated Text: God's help to someone also depends on the help we do between people. "Indeed Allah will help one of His servants as long as that servant helps others." (Hadith Muslim, Abu Daud and Tirmidhi).

Text: “Dan hendaklah kamu bertolong-tolongan utk mmbuat kebajikan & bertakwa & jgnlah kamu bertolong-tolongan pd melakukan dosa (maksiat) & pencerobohan. & bertakwalah kpd Allah krn sesungguhnya Allah maha berat azab seksa-Nya (bagi sesiapa yg melanggar perintah-Nya).” (al-Ma’idah: 2)
Translated Text: "And you should help each other to do good & pious & Don't help each other in committing sins (disobedience) & invasion. & fear Allah because indeed Allah is severe in His punishment (for those who violate His commandments)." (al-Ma'idah: 2)

Text:
Peralatan Yang Diperlukan:

1. Waterjet. Kalau takde, guna getah paip je.

2. Penyodok (utk sodok air dan lumpur)

3. Penyapu sampah

4. Plastik sampah

5. Sarung tangan getah

6. Kasut but getah

7. Kereta sorong
8. Cecair antiseptik
Translated Text:
Equipment needed:

1. Waterjet. If not, just use pipe rubber.

2. Shovel (for shoveling water and mud)

3. Garbage sweeper

4. Plastic waste

5. Rubber gloves

6. Rubber boots

7. Stroller
8. Antiseptic liquid

Text: 1. Sebolehnya, balik rumah masa air banjir masih paras betis untuk cuci rumah. Sbb mudah bersihkan rumah masa air belum surut kerana lumpur masih belum kering.
Translated Text: 1. If possible, return home when the flood water is still at calf level to wash the house. It's easy to clean the house when the water hasn't receded because the mud hasn't dried yet.

Text: 2. 1st thing 1st, bersihkan lumpur dulu. Bersihkan lumpur dulu sebelum pekakas or perabut yg lain
Translated Text: 2. 1st thing 1st, clean the mud first. Clean the mud first before other utensils or furniture

Text: 3. Bersihkan lantai dengan cecair antiseptik. Lumpur akan sgt berbau. Kalau boleh buat step ni, then buat. Pastu boleh bilas dgn air lg sekali
Translated Text: 3. Clean the floor with an antiseptic liquid. The mud will be very smelly. If you can do this step, then do it. You can rinse it with water again

Text: 4. Rendam peralatan makanan dlm air suam dan sabun basuh pinggan antibakteria
Translated Text: 4. Soak food utensils in warm water and antibacterial dishwashing soap

Text: 5. Jemur perabut yg mampu diselamatkan secepat mungkin. Bukak kipas & tingkap utk aliran udara
Translated Text: 5. Dry the furniture that can be saved as soon as possible. Open the fan & windows for air flow

Text: 6. Buang tilan yg dh terendam dgn air banjir lebih dr 24 jam sebab berisiko utk jd sarang kuman
Translated Text: 6. Dispose of tiles that have been submerged in flood water for more than 24 hours because they are at risk of becoming a breeding ground for germs.

Text: 7. Wallpaper semua cabut. Wallpaper akn serap air & buatkan dinding susah kering. Nnt dinding boleh jd sarang kuman sebab masih terlekat sisa air banjir
Translated Text: 7. Remove all wallpaper. Wallpaper will absorb water & make the wall hard to dry. The wall can become a breeding ground for germs because the remaining flood water is still attached

Text: 8. Bukak semua pintu & tingkap supaya aliran udara dan cahaya matahari masuk.
Translated Text: 8. Open all doors & windows to allow air flow and sunlight to enter.

Text: 9. Careful masa alihkan perabot dan cuci celah-celah perabot. Takut ada binatang berbahaya dan berbisa seperti ular dan biawak
Translated Text: 9. Careful when moving furniture and washing the crevices of furniture. Fear of dangerous and poisonous animals such as snakes and lizards

Text: 10. Buang makanan dan benda-benda yang rosak terutama dlm fridge
Translated Text: 10. Throw away food and damaged things, especially in the fridge

Text: 11. Pakai sarung tangan getah kalau hendak angkat atau bersihkan barang bagi mengelakkan dari sebarang kecelakaan dan kecederaan.
Translated Text: 11. Wear rubber gloves when lifting or cleaning things to avoid any accidents and injuries.

Text: Jangan lupa rehat & makan juga ye. Jaga diri semua!
Translated Text: Don't forget to rest & eat too Take care everyone!

Text: 1. Kategorikan pakaian ikut jenis pakaian. Contoh tshirt wanita, blause wanita, telekung kanak2, tshirt kanak2 perempuan, tshirt lelaki dewasa, pakaian sekolah rendah perempuan . Etc etc.
Translated Text: 1. Categorize clothes according to the type of clothes. Examples of women's t-shirts, women's blouses, children's t-shirts, girls' t-shirts, adult men's t-shirts, girls' primary school clothes. Etc etc.

Text: 2. Then labelkan saiz sekali, senang utk agihkan terus ke mangsa banjir. Contoh, tshirt wanita saiz M, seluar lelaki dewasa saiz L, etc.
Translated Text: 2. Then label the size once, easy to distribute directly to flood victims. For example, women's t-shirt size M, adult men's pants size L, etc.

Text: 3. Usahakan utk basuh dahulu semua pakaian sebelum didermakan. Selalu pakaian lama akan debu berhabuk dan berbau sedikit. Kalau boleh nnt mangsa banjir boleh pakai terus baju tu, kan senang
Translated Text: 3. Try to wash all the clothes first before donating. Old clothes will always be dusty and smell a little. If possible, flood victims can continue to wear the clothes, it's easy

Text: 4. Sebolehnya derma pakaian yg elok2 sahaja. Yang koyak, reput dsb mohon dielakkan
Translated Text: 4. If possible, donate nice clothes only. Those that are torn, rotten, etc. please avoid

Text: 5. Tak perlu derma used undergarments because of hygiene purpose. Yes, masa sorting pakaian mmg jumpa jugak, so please taw guys 🙏
Translated Text: 5. No need for derma used undergarments because of hygiene purposes. Yes, it's time to sort clothes, I'll see you, so please tell me guys 🙏

Text: Jom kita cuba bantu dengan cara yang terbaik & cuba minimakan penggunaan volunteers utk kerja sorting pakaian. Tenaga volunteers boleh digunakan utk kerja lain seperti basuh rumah/kawasan banjir.
Translated Text: Let's try to help in the best way & try to minimize the use of volunteers for clothes sorting work. Volunteers' energy can be used for other work such as washing houses/flooded areas.

Text: Berkongsi rezeki mmg amalam yang mulia. Moga-moga kita semua dapat buat yang terbaik.🙏
Translated Text: Sharing sustenance is a noble practice. May we all be able to do our best.🙏

Text:
1. Faham siapa target market/consumer

Mula2 dulu, Nike jual kasut berlari je. So pekerja dorang pun semua runners. Disebabkan ni, Nike sgt faham consumer dia. So bila Nike nak target atlet dari sport lain, dorang buat benda yg sama jugak
Translated Text:
1. Understand who the target market/consumer is

First, Nike only sold running shoes. So your employees are all runners. Because of this, Nike really understands his consumers. So when Nike wants to target athletes from other sports, they do the same thing

Text: Nike akan dapatkan top player setiap sukan & cuba every possible way utk faham apa yg atlet perlukan from tech & design standpoint. Then engineers Nike akan cipta apa yg atlet perlukan functionally & aesthetically.
Translated Text: Nike will get top player for every sport & try every possible way to understand what athletes need from tech & standpoint design. Then Nike engineers will create what athletes need functionally & aesthetically.

Text:
2. Nike tentukan siapa dorang punya customer base

1st, Nike cipta customer core aka the athlete
Bg Phil Knight,  “if we get the people at the top, we’ll get the others because they’ll know that the shoe can perform.”
Translated Text:
2. Nike tentukan siapa dorang punya customer base

1st, Nike cipta customer core aka the athlete
Bg Phil Knight,  “if we get the people at the top, we’ll get the others because they’ll know that the shoe can perform.”

Text:
So pyramid costomer base Nike mcm ni

Atlet
Weekend worriors
Orang lain yg pakai kasut atlet

So the key is to not only speaking to the core customer but also learning how to market to the customers at the bottom
Translated Text:
So pyramid costomer base Nike mcm ni

Atlet
Weekend worriors
Orang lain yg pakai kasut atlet

So the key is to not only speaking to the core customer but also learning how to market to the customers at the bottom

Text:
3. Cara Nike buat market research

Nike buat apa sahaja utk faham semua customer base
“To understand the rest of the pyramid, we do a lot of work at the grass-roots level.”
Translated Text:
3. Cara Nike buat market research

Nike buat apa sahaja utk faham semua customer base
“To understand the rest of the pyramid, we do a lot of work at the grass-roots level.”

Text:
Nike akan
-pergi ke amateur sport events
-hit the gym
-pergi tennis courts

Sebab Nike nk semua product berfungsi sama utk Michael Jordan ataupun org biasa
Translated Text:
Nike will
- go to amateur sports events
- hit the gym
- go to the tennis courts

Because Nike wants all products to work the same for Michael Jordan or ordinary people

Text:
4. Nike tentukan branding Nike

Knight says, “A brand is something that has a clear-cut identity among consumers, which a company creates by sending out a clear, consistent message over a period of years.”
Translated Text:
4. Nike tentukan branding Nike

Knight says, “A brand is something that has a clear-cut identity among consumers, which a company creates by sending out a clear, consistent message over a period of years.”

Text:
Bila Nike cuba masuk dlm casual shoe market, Nike gagal. Sale turun teruk. Dorang punya mesej tak jelas. Tu yg Nike stay utk jd sport apparel je, tak masuk dlm casual shoe market

When your brand stray away from its identity, your brand lose their touch.
Translated Text:
When Nike tried to enter the casual shoe market, Nike failed. Sales are down. They have an unclear message. That's what Nike is just staying for as sports apparel, not being included in the casual shoe market

When your brand strays away from its identity, your brand loses its touch.

Text:
5. Nike akhirnya faham branding Nike

Nike nak jd “the world’s best sports and fitness company and the Nike brand to represent sports and fitness activities.”
 So bila dh faham, senang nak rule out certain option, dari produk ke marketing
Translated Text:
5. Nike finally understands Nike branding

Nike wants to become "the world's best sports and fitness company and the Nike brand to represent sports and fitness activities."
 So when you understand, it's easy to rule out certain options, from product to marketing

Text:
6. Nike’s core marketing

Nike percaya ads yg berjaya ialah ads yg ada ikatan emosi dengan customer & dapat wake up the customer. So kalau dpt hasilkan ads mcm ni, mmg dpt bina long-term relationship dgn customer
Translated Text:
6. Nike's core marketing

Nike believes successful ads are ads that have an emotional bond with the customer & can wake up the customer. So if you can generate ads like this, you can really build long-term relationships with customers

Text:
7. Kenapa Nike partner dgn atlet

Sukan mmg dh sebati dgn american tp mcm mana nak yakinkan american dgn iklan 60 saat?

Nike buat iklan dgn Michael Jordan. Settle! Tak payah explain byk2. Orang tengok Jordan pun org dh faham. Key dia, cari atlet yg boleh stir up emotion
Translated Text:
7. Why does Nike partner with athletes

Sports are really mixed with Americans, but how do you convince Americans with a 60-second advertisement?

Nike made an ad with Michael Jordan. Settle! No need to explain much. People who look at Jordan also understand. The key is to find an athlete who can stir up emotion

Text:
Tapi Steve perasan yg retails experience selalunya tak best. So dia interview beberapa org dgn beberapa soalan simple:

“Where do you have your best customer service experience?”

But Steve noticed that the retails experience wasn't always the best. So he interviewed several people with some simple questions:

Text:
1. Guna quotation marks

Kalau letak quotation mark, search result hanya akan bg result yg hanya ada word tersebut shj
Eg: “Cherating beach experience”
Search result akn keluar semua result yg ada term cherating beach experience. Bkn hanya “cherarating” atau “beach experience”
Translated Text:
1. Use quotation marks

If you put a quotation mark, the search result will only give results that only have that word
Eg: “Cherating beach experience”
The search results will show all the results that have the term Cherating Beach Experience. Not just “cherarating” or “beach experience”

Text:
2. Tilde ~
Boleh guna tilde kalau nak synonyms termasuk dlm search result

Eg: Art ~lessons
Search result akn keluar art class, coaching, etc. Mantap kan esp kalau korang tgh google in a rush, lupa the exact words
Translated Text:
2. Tilde ~
You can use tilde if you want synonyms to be included in the search result

Eg: Art~lessons
Search results will show art class, coaching, etc. It's great especially if you google in a rush, forget the exact words

Text:
3. Dashes -
Kalau nk exclude a term/word dari korang punya result, boleh guna hyphen sblm word tu.
Translated Text:
3. Dashes-
If you want to exclude a term/word from you, you can use a hyphen before the word.

Text:
4. Site
Boleh guna ni utk searh within specific website only. Contoh kalau korang nak tengok specific words/term je dlm website tu

Eg: Steve Jobs site: https://t.co/JxseLgCO7s
So search result akan appear steve jobs shj dlm website https://t.co/JxseLgCO7s
Translated Text:
4. Site
Can be used to search within specific website only. For example, if you want to see specific words/terms on the website

Eg: Steve Jobs site: https://t.co/JxseLgCO7s
So search result will only appear steve jobs on the website https://t.co/JxseLgCO7s

Text:
5. Vertical bar |
Sama fungsi mcm or. So lebih terarah search result korang

Eg: restaurant | cafe
Translated Text:
5. Vertical bar |
Same function mcm or. So be more focused on your search results

Eg: restaurants | cafe

Text:
6. Two periods ..
Boleh guna 2 tempoh waktu utk search result diantara waktu tersebut shj. Ni antara function premium weh, tp dpt for free je!
Eg: best thriller movies 2013..2018
Translated Text:
6. Two periods ..
You can use 2 periods of time to search results between those times only. This is one of the premium functions, but you can get it for free!
Eg: best thriller movies 2013..2018

Text:
7. Location:

Boleh cari something within that location je. Paling best utk cari news

Eg: kes pecah rumah:seremban
Translated Text:
7. Location:

You can find something within that location. The best for finding news

Eg: burglary case: Seremban

Text:
8. Filetype:

Boleh filter jenis file yang korang nak je dlm search result korang
Eg: best content writing for f&b filetype:pdf
Cepat masa, mudah kerja. Kan?
Translated Text:
8. File types:

You can filter the type of file you want in your search results
Eg: best content writing for f&b filetype: pdf
Fast time, easy work. Right?

Text: Pada tahun 1950-an, sorang salesman bernama Ray Kroc start jual milkshake machine kpd McD. Kroc suka gila idea McD sampai dia nego untuk jadi franchise owners.
Translated Text: In the 1950s, a salesman named Ray Kroc started selling milkshake machines to McD. Kroc loved McD's idea so madly that he negotiated to become franchise owners.

Text: Long story short, dia berjaya beli the whole business dgn harga 2.7million USD. Lepas tu dia perasan, dia cuma untung 1.4% je dprd franchise owner. Kroc nak untung lebihh besar!
Translated Text: Long story short, he managed to buy the whole business for 2.7 million USD. After that he noticed that he only made 1.4% profit compared to the franchise owner. Kroc wants to make a bigger profit!

Text: So dia tukar strategi, Kroc start beli banyak lot tanah & start leasing them to franchise owner. So franchise owner pulak jadi tenants yg kena bayar monthly rent. Hahaha bijak kan?
Translated Text: So he changed his strategy, Kroc started buying many lots of land & start leasing them to franchise owners. So the franchise owner also becomes tenants who have to pay monthly rent. Hahaha wise right?

Text: So mmg Kroc dapat consistent cash yg banyak sgt & dia pun beli lebih banyak lot tanah. Dia teruskan je strategy mcm tu & now dah ada lebih 40,000 lokasi/branch McD. Banyangkan berapa byk dia dpt profit just from real estate.
Translated Text: So really Kroc can get a lot of consistent cash & he also bought more lots of land. He just continued with that strategy & now there are more than 40,000 locations/branches of McD. Imagine how much he can profit just from real estate.

Text: Harry Sonneborn, executive kat McD pernah cakap, “kami bukan dalam food business, we are in the real estate business. The only reason we sell hamburgers is because they are the greatest revenue producer, from which our tenants can pay us rent”.
Translated Text: Harry Sonneborn, executive kat McD pernah cakap, “kami bukan dalam food business, we are in the real estate business. The only reason we sell hamburgers is because they are the greatest revenue producer, from which our tenants can pay us rent”.

Text: Mantap kan! Kalau korang nak tahu lebih lanjut pasal ni, ada satu movie yang cerita pasal McD dari awal. Sebenarnya sedih jugak kisah McD ni. Kesian founder dia. Korang nak saya ulas filem ni tak? RT this tweet kalau nak haha https://t.co/beI1Hik0rJ

Text:
#1 cipta daily, weekly or monthly series
Contohnya hari tiap isnin korang post feedback, tiap minggu 1st korang record gambar/video behind the scene, tiap bulan sekali buat giveaway ke.
Translated Text:
#1 create daily, weekly or monthly series
For example, every Monday you post feedback, every 1st week you record pictures/videos behind the scene, once a month you do a giveaway.

Text: Korang jugak boleh tetapkan isnin post feedback, selasa post best selling product of the week, of the month. Buat series yg sesuai dgn bisnes korang. So korang kena brainstorm sekali je jenis content yg nak buat. So tak payah hari2 fikir untuk buat content apa. Penat weh
Translated Text: You can also set Monday to post feedback, Tuesday to post the best selling product of the week, of the month. Create a series that suits your business. So you have to brainstorm the type of content you want to create. So you don't have to think about what content to make. Tired

Text:
#2 Buat contest or giveaway
Korang kena tetapkan content/giveaway ni utk naikkan follower ke, spread brand awareness ke, promote launching product baru ke. So CTA boleh ikut matlamat contest or giveaway yg korang buat tu.
Translated Text:
#2 Create a contest or giveaway
You have to set this content/giveaway to increase followers, spread brand awareness, promote new product launches. So the CTA can follow the goal of the contest or giveaway you made.

Text:
#3 “Ask Me Anything”
Ask me bukan sesuai buat kat ig je, korang boleh buat jugak dekat twitter or other social media platform. Daripada Ask Me ni jugak korang boleh dapat idea untuk buat content taw. So mmg best sangat. Jangan lupa cuba ok?
Translated Text:
#3 “Ask Me Anything”
Ask me is not suitable for ig, you can also do it on twitter or other social media platforms. From this Ask Me, you can get ideas for creating content. So it's really good. Don't forget to try ok?

Text:
#4 Host a challenge
Dekat mana socmed pun, kalau korang berjaya initiate challenge or trend, mmg mantap. Sekejap je follower & exposure berdesup.
Translated Text:
#4 Host a challenge
Wherever social media is located, if you are successful in initiating a challenge or trend, that's great. For a moment, followers & exposure flashed.

Text:
#5 buat how-to or tutorial
This goes without saying. Mmg semua orang tahu kan? Ni antara highly sharable content. So boleh fikir tutorial yg sesuai dgn bisnes korang
Translated Text:
#5 make a how-to or tutorial
This goes without saying. Everyone knows right? This is among highly sharable content. So you can think of a tutorial that suits your business

Text:
#6 buat meme
Siapa je tak suka meme kan? So kalau korang tengok ada meme yg tgh trending, boleh edit meme utk sesuaikan dgn bisnes korang pulak
Translated Text:
#6 make memes
Who doesn't like memes, right? So if you see a trending meme, you can edit the meme to suit your business

Text:
#7 give your customers a spotlight
Korang boleh repost customer korang punya feedback. Share what your customers think about you. Ni jugak antara cara korang boleh engage dgn potential customers
Translated Text:
#7 give your customers a spotlight
You can repost your customers who have feedback. Share what your customers think about you. This is one of the ways you can engage with potential customers

Text:
#8 kongsi korang punya milestone
Korang baru dapat 1k follower? Share dekat customer korang! Produk terjual 3k unit? Sharee! Anniversary bisnes korang? Share! Anniversary produk? Shareee!
Translated Text:
#8 share if you have a milestone
You just got 1k followers? Share with your customers! Product sold 3k units? Share! Anniversary of your business? Share! Product anniversary? Share!

Text:
1. Buat to do list
Mmg dengar mcm simple kan, tp ramai tak buah weh. Korang listkan je semua kerja yg korang kena setel. Otak dh serabut sangat sebab fikir mcm2 kan. So keluarkan semua keserabutan tu. do your to do list
Translated Text:
1. Make a to do list
It sounds like it's simple, but many people don't get it. You just list all the work you have to set. The brain is very wired because of thinking like that, right? So remove all the clutter. do your to do list

Text:
2. Set priority
Bila dah buat to do list, now baju jelas kan mana yg priority & mana yg tak. So boleh mula dari situ. Start buat mana yg lg cepat dgn deadline & yg lebih utama
Translated Text:
2. Set priorities
When you've made a to do list, now it's clear which clothes are the priority & which is not So you can start from there. Start for which one is the fastest with the deadline & more important

Text:
3. Break bigger project into manageble chunks

kadang2 tu kita tak start2 buat sbb benda tu too complicated. Complicated sbb benda tu besar. So pecahkan into smaller project/to do. So bila cmtu, senang sikit utk kita buat & start
Translated Text:
3. Break bigger projects into manageable chunks

sometimes we don't start doing it because it's too complicated. Complicated because the thing is big. So break it into smaller project/to do. So when that happens, it's easy for us to do & start

Text:
4. Tentukan waktu bekerja 

Kadang2 bila kita set masa utk betul2 fokus, kita mmg boleh boleh buat semua kerja. Ikutlah timing korang. Kalau korang morning person, maybe boleh set lepas subuh terus start buat kerja. Set waktu ikut waktu korang paling produktif & start working
Translated Text:
4. Determine working hours

Sometimes when we set the time to focus properly, we can do all the work. Follow your timing. If you are a morning person, maybe you can set up after dawn and start working. Set the time according to your most productive time & start working

Text:
5. Remove distractions

Korang kenal pasti apa distractions korang yg buatkan korang bertangguh. Kalau sebab phone, set satu masa utk off phone or off noti utk buat kerja. Buang or jauhkan diri dgn apa yg distract anda waktu buat kerja
Translated Text:
5. Remove distractions

You know exactly what your distractions are that make you procrastinate. If it's because of the phone, set a time to turn off the phone or off the note to do work. Throw away or distance yourself from what distracts you when working

Text:
6. Do one thing at a time

Tak semua org pro at multitask. Maybe korang kena cuba setelkan satu2 kerja dulu before fikirkan next to list or project. Tiap kali korang latih buat kerja sampai siap, korang building up your resistance to procrastination.
Translated Text:
6. Do one thing at a time

Not everyone is pro at multitask. Maybe you guys have to try setting up one job first before thinking about next to list or project. Every time you train to work until you are ready, you are building up your resistance to procrastination.

Text: Because the brain is a muscle,  consistent workouts will make it better at accomplishing
Translated Text: Because the brain is a muscle,  consistent workouts will make it better at accomplishing

Text:
7. Rewards yourself with break

kena kena akui yg focus will be impossible to maintain. Set masa utk bekerja & bila rehat, rehat betul2
Translated Text:
7. Reward yourself with breaks

I have to admit that focus will be impossible to maintain. Set time to work & when you take a break, take a break

Text: Nak siapkan kerja cepat, kita kena kekalkan momentum bila kita dh dpt rentak utk buat kerja. Jangan bazirkan & boleh amal tips kat atas.  Cuba korang share cara korang combat procrastinate pulak hehe
Translated Text: If you want to prepare the work quickly, we have to maintain the momentum when we get the pace to do the work. Don't waste & You can follow the tips above. Try to share how you combat procrastination hehe

Text:
#1 Buat satu keputusan utk tahu apa yg korang nak even if korang tak tahu pun cemana nak buat
Buat 1 keputusan yg clear tentang apa yg korang nak. Try utk tak fikir mcm ni, contohnya cakap bestnya kalau. Taknak kalau2. Be firm with what you want.
Translated Text:
#1 Make a decision to know what you want even if you don't even know what to do
Make a clear decision about what you want. Try not to think like this, for example say it's best if. I don't care. Be firm with what you want.

Text: Contohnya, saya nak capai financial freedom before 40. Yups that it, very clear, even if you dont know how to be it at the moment buat you very clear with what you want in life
Translated Text: Contohnya, saya nak capai financial freedom before 40. Yups that it, very clear, even if you dont know how to be it at the moment buat you very clear with what you want in life

Text:
#2 Be clear about the outcome
Fikirkan outcome of your decisions secara detail. Practise visualising apa yg korang nak secara detail. Contohnya kalau korang order pizza, korang bayangkan topping apa kowang nak isi, bau pizza tu, rasa pizza tu
Translated Text:
#2 Be clear about the outcome
Think about the outcome of your decisions in detail. Practice visualizing what you want in detail. For example, if you order a pizza, imagine what toppings you want, the smell of the pizza, the taste of the pizza

Text:
#3 detach from the process

Ramai org jd bertangguh dgn apa yg dia cita2 kan sebab dia tak tahu cara utk capai. Tp percayalah, once we start to do something to achieve our dreams, the ways will appear. Selagi tak start buat, mmg susah nak nampak caranya mcm mana. Cuba try?
Translated Text:
#3 detach from the process

Many people put off what they want because they don't know how to achieve it. But believe me, once we start to do something to achieve our dreams, the ways will appear. As long as you don't start doing it, it's hard to see how to do it. Try to try?

Text:
#4 Terbuka dgn apa2 possibility when things dont go your way

Kita takde kuasa nk kawal semua & sometimes kita tak dpt apa yg kita nak. Rilex, simpan judgement kita on how thongs should be done based on our past experience.
Translated Text:
#4 Be open to all possibilities when things don't go your way

We don't have the power to control everything & sometimes we don't get what we want. Rilex, reserve our judgment on how thongs should be done based on our past experience.

Text:
#5 Bersyukur

Bersyukur dgn apa yg kita ada dlm hidup, saat ini. Bersyukur dpt melapangkan dada kita dengan apa yg terjadi. Bersyukur, redha, tapi masih usaha semampu yg boleh.
Translated Text:
#5 Be grateful

Be grateful for what we have in life, right now. Grateful to be able to open our chest with what happened. Grateful, pleased, but still trying as hard as possible.

Text: Nak dptkan apa yg kita nak dlm hidup ni bukan senang. Cabaran mesti ada. Confirm.  Kita akan hadapi komen negetif etc. Sebab itu kena pilih betul2 apa yg kita nak supaya berbaboi dgn pengorbanan kita.
Translated Text: Getting what we want in life is not easy. There must be challenges. Confirm. We will face negative comments etc. That's why we have to choose exactly what we want so that we can be happy with our sacrifices.

Text: Choose to get what you want, believe in your abilities, trust the process, and it will happen for you swiftly and easily. Pasti!
Translated Text: Choose to get what you want, believe in your abilities, trust the process, and it will happen for you swiftly and easily. Pasti!

#1 Jgn criticize, condemn or complain. Tp cuba faham why they do what they do.

Carnegie cakap, "any fool can criticize, condemn or complain- and most fools do." Haha betul la tu kan? 

Semua org ada their own life, own thought processes, own histories.
Translated Text:
#1 Jgn criticize, condemn or complain. Tp cuba faham why they do what they do.

Carnegie cakap, "any fool can criticize, condemn or complain- and most fools do." Haha betul la tu kan? 

Semua org ada their own life, own thought processes, own histories.

Text:
Before kita judge, cuba faham kenapa dorang buat mcm tu. Selalunya mesti ada reason behind it. So dont be too quick to criticise/condemn/complain. 
Berlatih buat yang satu ni ni, percayalah it could become a life changing conversation with whoever you are trying to talk to.
Translated Text:
Before we judge, try to understand why you did that. There must always be a reason behind it. So don't be too quick to criticize/condemn/complain.
Practice for this one, believe me it could become a life changing conversation with whoever you are trying to talk to.

Text:
#2 Be GENUINELY interested in other people
Tips ni campur dgn tips 1st tadi mmg kebabom weh, esp when meeting someone new. So bila nak tegur org dulu, boleh guna tips ni. Utk networking dgn idola or bakal mentor, boleh guna tips ni.
Translated Text:
#2 Be GENUINELY interested in other people
This tip is mixed with the 1st tip, it's really kebabom weh, especially when meeting someone new. So if you want to warn people first, you can use these tips. For networking with idols or future mentors, you can use these tips.

Text: Ingat taw, be genuine, sbb org boleh perasan je kalau org cuba nak fake something. Kita pun boleh tahu kan bila org fake dpn kita kan? Hahaha
Translated Text: Remember, be genuine, because people can only notice when people try to fake something. We can also tell when people are fake, right? Haha

Text:
#3 Be a good listener. Encourage others to talk about themselves
Most people love to talk about themselves. Ini adalah fakta. So, tugas kita ialah, ask them questions and encourage them to talk about themselves.
Translated Text:
#3 Be a good listener. Encourage others to talk about themselves
Most people love to talk about themselves. Ini adalah fakta. So, tugas kita ialah, ask them questions and encourage them to talk about themselves.

Text: Kalau perasan pun bila berborak ramai2 kan, semua org nak bercakap, susah nak potong kan bila org dah rancak bercerita pasal dorang. Biarkan aje dorang bercerita, kita jd pendengar yg baik. InshaAllah semua org suka ada kawan yg boleh jd good listener.
Translated Text: If you've noticed that when there's a lot of people chatting, everyone wants to talk, it's hard to interrupt when people are already talking about you. Just let people talk, we are good listeners. InshaAllah everyone likes to have a friend who can be a good listener.

Text: Dah semua org nak bercakap, siapa pulak nak mendengar kan? So, be one.
Translated Text: Everyone wants to talk, who wants to listen? So, be one.

Text: Ada byk lagi tips best dr buku ni. Buku ni saya recommend utk org yg nak step up their social game. Buku ni ditulis 85 tahun yg lepas & telah terjual lebih 30juta copies. Mmg impactful sangat buku ni. Walaupun dah lama ditulis, semua tips dia masih relaven sampai sekarang!

Text: Kita kena akui, kawan2 adalah modal kejayaan dalam alam kerja/business, dan istilahnya modal sosial. Tapi lepas kita habis belajar, makin susah utk kita buat kawan sedangkan utk berjaya kita perlukan ramai kawan. So, bolehlah amalkan 3 tips ni dulu utk improve our sosial beauty.

But after we finish studying, it becomes more difficult for us to make friends while to succeed we need many friends. So, you can practice these 3 tips first to improve our social beauty.

Text:
Bagi saya, jawapan yg paling mudah adalah bagitahu yg kita tengah occupied dengan projek sedia ada jadi tak dapat nak bantu.

Pastu boleh bgtahu, “tapi ada kawan yang boleh provide servis dengan bayaran sekian, sekian, kalau nak saya kenalkan pun boleh”
Translated Text:
For me, the easiest answer is to tell them that we are busy with an existing project so we can't help.

You can tell me, "but there is a friend who can provide service for so much, so much, if you want me to introduce you, you can."

Text:
Dapatlah jaga hubungan dengan orang yg request tu walaupun kita reject permintaan dia.

But if you wanna spend some times & betul2 nak bantu deme pun takde masalah jugak.
Translated Text:
Be able to maintain a relationship with the requester even if we reject his request.

But if you wanna spend some times & If you really want to help, there's no problem.

Text:
Untuk kita pulak jangan lupa benda ni.

Jangan rasa apa yg orang lain buat tu senang walaupun deme boleh buat dalam masa tak sampai sehari.

Sebab kita tak tahu berapa lama masa deme ambik untuk master benda tu & buat dalam masa yg singkat.
Translated Text:
For us, don't forget this thing.

Don't think that what other people do is easy even if you can do it in less than a day.

Because we don't know how long it will take to master that thing & do it in a short time.

Text:
So hargai hasil kerja diorang. Kalau nak minta bantuan, janganlah minta free semacam merendahkan hasil kerja deme.

At least tanya dulu berapa diorang cas. Kalau sesuai dengan bajet kita, ameklah. Kalau tak, try nego.
Translated Text:
So appreciate people's work. If you want to ask for help, don't ask for free in a way that degrades the results of your work.

At least ask first how much they charge. If it fits our budget, go for it. If not, try to negotiate.

Text:
Untuk designer, web developer, copywriter yg hadap masalah serupa, bertabahlah. Haha

Moga Allah murahkan rezeki kita semua. Amiin
Translated Text:
For designers, web developers, copywriters who face similar problems, persevere. Haha

May God bless us all. Amen

Text:
1. Manage your stress

Mmg stress bila fikir tentang hidup ni, tapi kita kena cuba clear our mind supaya dpt berfikir dgn lebih jelas. 

Risau emosi menyebabkan kita tersalah pilih, so please, manage your stress. Bila stress, pergilah joging jap atau makan aiskrim ke. Haha
Translated Text:
1. Manage your stress

It's stressful when you think about life, but we have to try to clear our mind so that we can think more clearly.

Emotional worries cause us to make the wrong choice, so please, manage your stress. When stressed, go jogging or eat ice cream. Haha

Text:
2. Give yourself some time. 

Take some time & bagi peluang utk diri kita duduk & brainstrom semua details tentang perkara2 besar dalam hidup kita. No rush.

Kadang kita ni dengan orang lain boleh tolerate, tapi dengan diri sendiri semua kita nak cepat je. Haha
Translated Text:
2. Give yourself some time.

Take some time & for the opportunity for ourselves to sit & brainstorm all the details about the big things in our lives. No rush.

Sometimes we can tolerate with other people, but with ourselves we all want to be quick. Haha

Text:
3. Fikirkan tentang our goals & value. 

Bila kita tahu matlamat hidup kita & apa yg kita value in life, then kita dpt buat informed decision. 

Informed decision tak semestinya tepat, tapi bermatlamat. At the very least, kita tak menyesal dengan decision yg kita buat.
Translated Text:
3. Think about our goals & value.

When we know our life goals & what we value in life, then we can make an informed decision.

Informed decision is not necessarily accurate, but purposeful. At the very least, we don't regret the decision we made.

Text:
4. Consider all the possibilities. 

Setiap keputusan yg kita buat akan ada different outcome. So bolehlah kita list semua outcome & consequences kpd decisions kita.  Ala buat pro & cons camtu haha

So that our decision tu better lah daripada kita hentam je. Haha
Translated Text:
4. Consider all the possibilities.

Every decision we make will have a different outcome. So can we list all outcomes & consequences to our decisions. How to make a pro & cons like that haha

So that our decision is better than us hitting it. Haha

Text:
Apa-apa pun, sebenarnya dunia ni memang tempat untuk kita berpenat-penat.

Banyak yang kita perlu usahakan atas dunia ni sebelum dapat kita tuai di akhirat nanti.

it's a long road & a tough battle. Nak tak nak, kita kena hadap jugak kan? So kita usahakanlah yg terbaik.
Translated Text:
Anyway, the world is indeed a place for us to get tired.

There is a lot that we need to work on in this world before we can reap in the afterlife.

it's a long road & a tough battle. I don't want it, we have to face it right? So let's do our best.

Text:
Masa tu hari kedua kitorang dekat Syria. Lepas dah agihkan bantuan ke semua khemah, inilah khemah terakhir yg kitorang singgah.

Mmg biasa dari Malaysia kita akan bawak gula2, coklat & jajan sikit utk budak2.
Translated Text:
It was our second day near Syria. After distributing aid to all the tents, this is the last tent we stopped by.

It's normal from Malaysia that we will bring sugar, chocolate & a little snack for the boys.

Text:
Dari awal lagi mmg team kat sana dah pesan, kalau nak bagi kena bagi semua supaya adil. Janganlah bagi kat budak yg kau suka je. Haha.

Sebelum masuk tu rasa mcm dah cukup dah semua, bila dekat2 nak sampai rasa risau betul weh takut tak cukup apa yg dibawak ni.
Translated Text:
From the very beginning, the team there has ordered that if you want to share, you have to share it with everyone so that it is fair. Don't give it to the boy you like. Haha.

Before entering, I felt like everything was enough, when I was about to arrive, I was really worried because I was afraid that what I had brought was not enough.

Text:
Dan kerisauan tu mmg jadi kenyataan. 

Lepas dah agih semua jajan yg dibawak ni, tinggal 1 je lolipop dalam poket.

Kebetulan ada 3 budak ni kat depan & dari tadi perhati saya. Allahu sedih weh kalau ingat semula.
Translated Text:
And that worry has come true.

After distributing all the snacks that were brought, there is only 1 lollipop left in the pocket.

It happened that there were 3 boys in front & from earlier I noticed. God, it's sad when you think back.

Text:
Lolipop tinggal satu ni, kalau coklat bolehlah patah2kan. Haha

Tapi takpelah, saya senyum je & panggil diorang.

"Come, meh sini"

Rilek je cakap BM kan. Sbb cakap BI pun diorang tak faham jugak. haha
Translated Text:
There's only one lollipop left, if it's chocolate you can break it. Haha

But it doesn't matter, I just smile & call someone

"Come, almost here"

Just talk about BM, right? As BI said, people don't understand. haha

Text:
Bila diorang datang kat aku, aku keluarkan lolipop tu sembunyi2. Risau weh takut kena serbu. Dahlah benda tinggal satu kan. Haha.

Then aku cakap kat diorang, share tau.

Pastu diorang macam blur2. Haha. Ofkoslah diorg tak faham.
Translated Text:
When people come to me, I take out the lollipop and hide it. I'm worried about being attacked. There's only one thing left, right? Haha.

Then I told people, share it.

People are like blur2. Haha. It's Ofkos that people don't understand.

Text:
Saya panggil team kat sana mintak tlg translatekan. Barulah deme angguk2 sambil senyum.

Lepas tu diorang terus main lari2 semua. Sy kejar & perhati lah nak tengok betul ke deme ni share kan, ke yg pegang tu terus bawak lari. Biasa budak2 kan mcm tu. Haha
Translated Text:
I called the team there and asked them to translate. Just nodded while smiling.

After that, everyone kept playing and running away. I chase & Pay attention to see if this deme is shared, right? If you hold it, you will run away. It's normal for boys to be like that. Haha

Text:
Maka nampaklah situasi ni.

Masing2 tunggu giliran untuk merasa lolipop yang ada sebatang ni.

Serius masa tengok diorang ni rasa sedihnya. Kenapalah tak bawak 100 lolipop masa tu.
Translated Text:
So look at this situation.

Everyone waits for their turn to taste the lollipop that is in this stick.

Seriously, when I see this person, I feel sad. Why didn't you bring 100 lollipops that time?

Text:
Tapi sebenarnya Allah dah susun kan benda ni.

Masa ni lah saya belajar & faham yg orang yang merasai betapa susahnya kehidupan ni lah yg tak kisah untuk berkongsi & bersyukur walau dgn sekecil2 nikmat yg diberi.
Translated Text:
But actually God has arranged this thing.

This is the time I study & understand that people who feel how difficult life is are the ones who don't mind sharing & be grateful even for the smallest favors given.

Text:
Bila saya reflects balik diri, rasa macam ya Allah banyak dah kau bagi kat aku, tapi sikit je aku bersyukur.

Bukan kata lolipop, hari2 perut kenyang, tempat tinggal selesa, aman dari peperangan, pakaian cukup serba serbi. Itupun banyak mengeluh lagi.
Translated Text:
When I reflect on myself, I feel like God, you have given me a lot, but I am grateful for just a little.

It's not a word of lollipops, full days, a comfortable place to live, safe from war, enough clothes. That's a lot of complaining again.

Text:
Bila kita jumpa mereka, mungkin kita membantu mereka dalam urusan dunia.

Tetapi dalam masa yg sama, mereka membantu kita dalam urusan akhirat yg kekal selamanya.
Translated Text:
When we meet them, maybe we help them in world affairs.

But at the same time, they help us in the affairs of the hereafter that last forever.

Text:
1. Buat Instagram Business account 

So basically, banyak features untuk bisnes yg tak available dekat personal profile. 

That's why penting untuk kita set kita punya akaun as business account. 

Macam mana nak set as business account? Ikut step dekat bawah ni...
Translated Text:
1. Create an Instagram Business account

So basically, there are many features for businesses that are not available in personal profiles.

That's why it's important for us to set that we have an account as a business account.

How do you set up as a business account? Follow the steps below...

Text:
1. Daripada profile kita, tap the hamburger menu kat bahagian atas kanan. 

2. Tap Settings. 

3. Tap Account. 

4. Choose Business 

5. Ada option utk connect akaun IG & FB page. 

6. Select your business category and add relevant contact details. 

DONE!
Translated Text:
1. Daripada profile kita, tap the hamburger menu kat bahagian atas kanan. 

2. Tap Settings. 

3. Tap Account. 

4. Choose Business 

5. Ada option utk connect akaun IG & FB page. 

6. Select your business category and add relevant contact details. 

DONE!

Text:
2. Optimize link dkt bio 

Dekat IG ni, post kita tak boleh letak link. Cuma ada satu tempat yg kita boleh letak link - bio. 

Kalau kita mmg dah ada website, kita boleh letak link website kita je kat situ.

Tp kalau kita ada banyk link mcm mana?
Translated Text:
2. Optimize the link in the bio

Near this IG, we can't post a link. There is only one place we can put the link - bio.

If we already have a website, we can put our website link there.

But what if we have a lot of links?

Text:
Boleh gunakan landing page untuk susun link2 yg kita ada tu. 

Antara yg saya pernah guna adalah: linktree & https://t.co/Iq7feyd5AG. 

https://t.co/Iq7feyd5AG ni @faizedzahar yg buat kalau tak silap. #sapotlokal haha
Translated Text:
You can use the landing page to organize the links we have.

Among the ones I have used are: linktree & https://t.co/Iq7feyd5AG.

https://t.co/Iq7feyd5AG this was made by @faizedzahar if I'm not mistaken. #sapotlocal haha

Text:
@faizedzahar 3. Geotag 

Geotag ni salah satu features yg kita tak patut lupa untuk gunakan setiap kali kita buat post. 

Bila ada geotag ni, ig akan compilekan semua post yg tag tu & sort ikut recent & top. 

Bila org search akan nampak gambar bisnes kita.
Translated Text:
@faizedzahar 3. Geotag

Geotag is one of the features that we should not forget to use every time we make a post.

When there is this geotag, I will compile all the posts with that tag & sort by recent & top.

When people search they will see pictures of our business.

Text: 1. Kenal pasti masalah pelanggan: Resipi minuman ini dicipta pada 135 tahun yg lalu oleh Dr John Pemberton di Atalanta, AS. Mulanya, coke hanya dijual di kaunter ‘soda-fountain’ di sekitar Atalanta. Then, dorang terfikir utk membotolkan air tsbt supaya mudah dibawa kemana shj.
Translated Text: 1. Identify the customer's problem: This drink recipe was created 135 years ago by Dr. John Pemberton in Atalanta, USA. At first, coke was only sold at 'soda-fountain' counters around Atalanta. Then, you think of bottling this water so that it is easy to take anywhere.

Text: 2. Membina identiti product: walaupun 94% pnduduk dunia kenal coke, Coca cola masih membelanjakan 10% (USD 41b) drpd profitnya utk iklan & public image. Dgn Bajet yg byk, dorang dpt bereksperimen secara kreatif dgn kempen  iklan coca cola ikut geographical settings.
Translated Text: 2. Build product identity: even though 94% of the world's population knows coke, Coca cola still spends 10% (USD 41b) of its profits for advertising & public image. With a large budget, you can experiment creatively with Coca Cola advertising campaigns according to geographical settings.

Text: 3. Bagaimana kempen mereka boleh berjaya? Dengan menjual coke bukan sbb airnya yg sedap/lazat tp dengan menjual rasa gembira, relaks & berkasih sayang & segala rasa positif apabila minum coke. Simple je kan?
Translated Text: 3. How can their campaign be successful? By selling coke not because the water is good/delicious but by selling happiness, relaxation & loving & all positive feelings when drinking coke. It's simple, right?

Text: 4. Ni contoh iklan pada hari Christmas. Nampakkan yg coke cuba menjual jenamanya dgn memberi gmbrn perasaan kebahagiaan kpd semua, baik ayahnya, akak kedai, mahupun Santa, semuanya tak terkecuali. Boleh tonton disini: https://t.co/qhrjnFfAhI
Translated Text: 4. This is an example of an advertisement on Christmas day. It seems that coke is trying to sell its brand by giving the impression of happiness to everyone, whether it's the father, the shop assistant, or Santa, all of them are no exception. Text:
1 - No work-life balance

Pernah dengar orang kata nak jadi businessman sbb nak ada lebih masa dengan keluarga?

Believe me, sangat rare utk business owner ada lebih masa dgn family compared to kerja mcm biasa. Lagi2 dalam fasa awal bisnes.
Translated Text:
1 - No work-life balance

Have you ever heard people say that they want to be a businessman because they want to have more time with their family?

Believe me, it is very rare for a business owner to have more time with his family compared to normal work. Still in the initial phase of business.

Text:
Unless, yg mewarisi bisnes daripada parents etc. Ofkos they will have more time with family lah. Haha

But seriously, bila buat decision utk buat bisnes get ready untuk korbankan work-life balance at least utk 3-5 tahun pertama.
Translated Text:
Unless, who inherited the business from parents etc. Ofkos they will have more time with family. Haha

But seriously, when you make a decision to start a business, get ready to sacrifice work-life balance at least for the first 3-5 years.

Text:
2 - Hidup yg penuh dengan uncertainties

Haha serius weh.

Bila jump dalam dunia bisnes, satu yg kita kena ingat setiap hari adalah new challenge untuk kita.

Mungkin kita akan untung.
Mungkin kita akan rugi.
Translated Text:
2 - A life full of uncertainties

Haha seriously.

When jumping into the business world, one thing we have to remember every day is a new challenge for us.

Maybe we will profit.
Maybe we will lose.

Text:
Kadang kita dah plan baik punya, tapi ada benda diluar kawalan kita jadi. Maka rugilah kita.

Contoh paling obvious, bila covid & PKP jadi, berapa banyak bisnes yg terpaksa ttp. Siapa jangka akan berlarutan sampai ke 2 tahun kan?
Translated Text:
Sometimes we have a good plan, but something happens out of our control. So we lose.

The most obvious example, when covid & MCO, so how many businesses are forced to do so? Who expected it to last up to 2 years right?

Text:
So yeah, mmg takde jaminan yg setiap bulan akan ada duit masuk dalam akaun kita macam masa makan gaji.

So kita ready x utk keadaan ni?
Translated Text:
So yeah, there is no guarantee that every month there will be money in our account like when we get paid.

So are we ready for this situation?

Text:
3 - Mengawal emosi

It's hard utk kawal emosi kita bila kita terlampau attach dengan apa yg kita buat.

Cuba bayangkan how we can control ourself bila keadaan bisnes kita tgh teruk. Defisit, no income, no client, big loss.
Translated Text:
3 - Control emotions

It's hard to control our emotions when we are too attached to what we do.

Try to imagine how we can control ourselves when our business situation is bad. Deficit, no income, no client, big loss.

Text:
Macam mana kita akan behave bila balik rumah jumpa anak2 dalam keadaan bisnes kita tak okay?

Bila partner kita buat something yg remeh waktu tu, adakah kita akan melenting?
Translated Text:
How will we behave when we return home to find our children in a situation where our business is not okay?

When our partner does something trivial at that time, will we bounce?

Text:
Kalau korang masih bekerja, cuba bayangkan hari yg paling korang stress.

Darabkan dengan 17. 

Gitulah stress business owner dalam fasa2 awal & bila diuji.
Translated Text:
If you are still working, try to imagine the most stressful day.

Multiply by 17.

That's the stress of business owners in the early phases & when tested.

Text:
So rasa demotivated ke? haha. 

Janganlah demotivated, ini cuma sebahagian daripada bbrp perkara yg sukar bila kita pilih jalan utk jadi business owner.

Bila kita dah tahu ni, kita boleh prepare awal2 utk berhadapan dgn benda2 ni semua.
Translated Text:
So do you feel demotivated? haha.

Don't be demotivated, this is just one of the many difficult things when we choose the path to become a business owner.

When we know this, we can prepare early to deal with all these things.

Text:
And if we can't, that's okay.

Siapa kata tak okay kerja dengan orang? Kita still boleh beri value pada orang & contribute to society kot. Bukan business owner je boleh buat benda tu.

So buatlah pilihan yg kita rasa bagus utk kita, bukan pilihan yg orang rasa bagus utk kita.
Translated Text:
And if we can't, that's okay.

Who said it's not okay to work with people? We can still give value to people & contribute to society. Only business owners can do that.

So make the choice that we think is good for us, not the choice that others think is good for us.

Text:
Bronnie Ware ni nurse kat Australia. Dia jaga bahagian palliative care. Ape tu?

Palliative care ni basically specialized medical care utk pesakit yg ada masalah penyakit kritikal.

So dia mmg berurusan dgn orang yang di penghujung usia.
Translated Text:
Bronnie Ware is a nurse in Australia. He takes care of the palliative care department. What's that?

Palliative care is basically specialized medical care for patients with critical illness problems.

So he is dealing with people who are at the end of their lives.

Text:
1. Berharap ada keberanian utk menjalani hidup yang mereka nak, berbanding hidup yang orang lain expect.

Actually dalam hidup ni mmg semua orang ada expectation utk kita.

Ada yang expect kita jadi doktor, ada yang expect kita jadi cikgu...
Translated Text:
1. Hoping to have the courage to live the life they want, rather than the life others expect.

Actually, in this life, everyone has expectations for us.

Some expect us to be doctors, some expect us to be teachers...

Text:
Ada yang expect kita kerja bagai nak gila then lupa daratan.

Wajar ke mcm tu?

Cuba tanya diri kita sendiri apa yang kita betul2 nak dalam hidup ni? 

Betul ke kita nak jadi doktor & cikgu? Ke sebenarnya kita nak bela lembu & tanam jagung? Haa
Translated Text:
Some people expect us to work like crazy and then forget the land.

Is that normal?

Try asking ourselves what do we really want in this life?

Do we really want to be doctors & teacher? Do we actually want to defend cattle & grow corn? Huh

Text:
2. Berharap tidak bekerja terlalu kuat.

Kata Bronnie Ware, semua pesakit lelaki berkongsi kekesalan yang sama. Huhu

Ramai yg jadikan pekerjaan sbgai tujuan hidup mereka sampai mengabaikan benda lain yang lebih penting dalam kehidupan.
Translated Text:
2. Hope not to work too hard.

According to Bronnie Ware, all male patients share the same regret. Huh

Many people make work the purpose of their lives to the point of neglecting other things that are more important in life.

Text:
Bukan nak kata kerja kuat tu tak bagus. Sy pun kerja kuat juga

Tapi kalau sampai abaikan benda & tanggungjawab yang lagi penting dalam kehidupan, then something wrong somewhere. 

Ada benda yg kita kena improve. Okey?
Translated Text:
I don't want to say that strong verbs are not good. I also work hard

But if you ignore things & more important responsibility in life, then something wrong somewhere.

There are things we have to improve. okay?

Text:
3. Berharap ada keberanian untuk meluahkan perasaan

Ini bukan untuk crush eh. Haha

Meluahkan perasaan ni boleh jadi pada mak, ayah, keluarga, kawan-kawan. Don't get me wrong
Translated Text:
3. Hope to have the courage to express feelings

This is not for crushes. Haha

Expressing these feelings can be to mom, dad, family, friends. Don't get me wrong

Text:
Try cek balik, dalam minggu ni atau bulan ni atau tahun ni, berapa kali kita call mak , ayah bagitahu yang kita sayang mereka? Huhu

Berapa ramai je yang bagitahu dekat kawan-kawan yang sebenarnya drg bermakna dalam hidup kita?
Translated Text:
Try to check back, in this week or this month or this year, how many times do we call mom, dad to tell them that we love them? Huh

How many people tell close friends who are really meaningful in our lives?

Text:
4. Berharap terus keep in touch dengan kawan-kawan

Kata Bronnie Ware,

Often they would not truly realise the full benefits of old friends until their dying weeks and it was not always possible to track them down.
Translated Text:
4. Berharap terus keep in touch dengan kawan-kawan

Kata Bronnie Ware,

Often they would not truly realise the full benefits of old friends until their dying weeks and it was not always possible to track them down.

Text:
Kadang kita ni bila dah sibuk sangat dengan macam2 benda dalam hidup, kita jadi lupa nak contact kawan-kawan yang dulu pernah tidur sebantal dengan kita. Haha

Yang tolong kita masa susah.
Yang angkat kita masa jatuh.
Yang bagi kita makan masa lapar. Kan?
Translated Text:
Sometimes when we are so busy with all kinds of things in life, we forget to contact friends who used to sleep with us. Haha

Who helps us in difficult times.
The one who lifts us when we fall.
Which for us to eat when we are hungry. Right?

Text:
Kenapa agaknya kita letak drg sebagai prioriti paling akhir dalam tangga yang perlu diingati sepanjang hayat kita?

Padehal diorang deserve more.

Tak ke? Hmm
Translated Text:
Why is it that we put drg as the last priority in the ladder that needs to be remembered for the rest of our lives?

In fact, people deserve more.

Isn't it? Hmmm

Text:
5. Berharap saya berikan ruang utk diri sendiri  lebih gembira & bahagia

Kebahagiaan ni pilihan guys.

Tapi kadang2 kita takut untuk buat pilihan tu.

Sebab pilihan tu bermaksud kita mungkin perlu lakukan sesuatu yang diluar expectation orang lain. Betul x?
Translated Text:
5. Hope I give myself space to be happier & happy

Happiness is a choice guys.

But sometimes we are afraid to make that choice.

Because that choice means we may have to do something that is beyond other people's expectations. Is that right?

Text:
Kita selalu fikir, apa org lain akn cakap, apa yang orang ni akan fikir.

Sampai kita lupa, 

Entah berapa banyak yang kita terluka sepanjang proses berfikir tentang orang lain ni, yang sebenarnya tak peduli pun pasal kita. Haha
Translated Text:

Text:

Text:
How it started?

Samsung diasaskan oleh Lee Chull pada tahun 1938. Waktu awal dulu, Samsung cuma ada 40 orang pekerja je dan fokus kat model bisnes trading.

Kiranya diorang cuma jual barang-barang runcit harian.
Translated Text:
How did it start?

Samsung was founded by Lee Chull in 1938. In the early days, Samsung only had 40 employees and focused on the trading business model.

I hope people only sell daily groceries.

Text:
Masa tahun 1950-an, Samsung try untuk kembangkan model bisnes diorang.

So apa yg diorang buat? 

Diorang mula masuk dalam industri kewangan iaitu insurans, sekuriti (pelaburan) dan retail.
Translated Text:
During the 1950s, Samsung tried to develop its business model.

So what do people do?

People started to enter the financial industry namely insurance, securities (investment) and retail.

Text:
Tahun 1960-an pulak, Samsung mula masuk dalam segmen elektronik. Haa itu yang kita kenal Samsung ni lah. Haha

Apa produk pertama yang diorang hasilkan?

TV!

Sekarang dah ada beribu device yg diorang cipta.
Translated Text:
In the 1960s, Samsung began to enter the electronics segment. That's what we know about Samsung. Haha

What was the first product people produced?

TV!

Now there are thousands of devices created by people.

Text:
Masa tahun 1983, Samsung start produce first computer diorang. 

Tahu tak, komputer ciptaan Samsung pada waktu tu 14 kali ganda lebih 'advance' daripada komputer yang dibangunkan Microsoft!

Power gila. Haha
Translated Text:
In 1983, Samsung started producing the first personal computer.

Did you know, the computers created by Samsung at that time were 14 times more 'advanced' than the computers developed by Microsoft!

Crazy power. Haha

Text:
Sekarang?

Kebanyakan daripada kita cuma tahu Samsung ni syarikat elektronik je, tapi Samsung ni lebih besar daripada tu. 

Lagi besar daripada apa yang kita semua bayangkan.
Translated Text:
Now?

Most of us only know that Samsung is an electronics company, but Samsung is bigger than that.

Bigger than what we all imagine.

Text:
Pada tahun 2019, pendapatan Samsung dilaporkan melebihi USD 200 billion. 

Bagaimana jika ditulis dengan angka nilai ini. 

200,000,000,000!
Translated Text:
In 2019, Samsung's revenue was reported to exceed USD 200 billion.

What if written with this value number.

200,000,000,000!

Text:
Macam mana boleh capai angka sebesar tu? 

Mudah je. Ceh tak mudah lah sebenarnya. Haha

Samsung ni terdiri daripada 80 gabungan bisnes yang bermacam-macam jenis. Bukan daripada sektor elektronik je.
Translated Text:
How can you reach such a big number?

It's easy. It's not really easy. Haha

Samsung consists of 80 business combinations of various types. Not from the electronics sector.

Text:
Dalam kategori pembinaan & kejuruteraan:

Samsung Engineering & Construction
Samsung Trading & Investment
Samsung Heavy Industries

Dalam kategori elektronik:

Samsung Electronics
Samsung Eletro-Mechanics
Samsung Techwin
Samsung Mobile Display
Samsung Digital Imaging
Translated Text:
In the coaching & vocational:

Samsung Engineering & Construction
Samsung Trading & Investments
Samsung Heavy Industries

In electronics category:

Samsung Electronics
Samsung Electro-Mechanics
Samsung Techwin
Samsung Mobile Display
Samsung Digital Imaging

Text:
Dalam kategori kewangan:

Samsung Life Insurance
Samsung Securities
Samsung Investment
Samsung Venture

Okay cukup lah. Banyak sangat pulak kalau nak list semua. Haha
Translated Text:
In the financial category:

Samsung Life Insurance
Samsung Securities
Samsung Investment
Samsung Venture

Okay that's enough. There are too many to list them all. Haha

Text:
Samsung jugak terlibat dengan oil & gas, marketing, hotel & resort, medical center, automotif dan banyak lagi. 

Padu kan? Tapi apa benda yang Samsung buat kita jarang tahu?
Translated Text:
Samsung is also involved with Oil & gas, marketing, hotel & resorts, medical centers, automotive and many more.

Mixed right? But what are the things that Samsung makes us rarely know?

Text:
Samsung ni terlibat secara langsung dalam penghasilan peralatan2 ketenteraan. 

Samsung juga membangunkan robot tentera Korea Selatan untuk cuba kurangkan keterlibatan tentera (manusia) di daerah DMZ. Korang tahu dah kan DMZ tu apa?
Translated Text:
Samsung is directly involved in the production of military equipment.

Samsung also developed a South Korean military robot to try to reduce the involvement of the (human) military in the DMZ area. Do you know what the DMZ is?

Text:
Kalau rasa Samsung ni tak cukup padu lagi, ketahuilah bahawasanya... 

Samsung buat kereta kebal jugak. Kereta kebal K-9! Kereta kebal ni bukan Korea Selatan je guna, tetapi beberapa negara lain pun guna kereta kebal ni antaranya, Turkey, Australia & India.
Translated Text:
If you think this Samsung is not cohesive enough, know that...

Samsung makes tanks too. The K-9 tank! This tank is not only used by South Korea, but several other countries also use this tank among them, Turkey, Australia & India.

Text:
Tentera robot, menara tertingi dunia, kereta kebal. Apa lagi yg Samsung tak buat? Kapal terbang kot.

Wait.

Samsung ada buat enjin jet. 

Ya tak bergurau, jenama sama yang menghasilkan peti sejuk rumah kita, buat enjin jet jugak weh. Haha
Translated Text:
Robot army, world's tallest tower, tanks. What else does Samsung not do? Airplane coat.

Wait.

Samsung makes jet engines.

No kidding, the same brand that produces our home refrigerators, also makes jet engines. Haha

Text:
Bukan setakat KLCC yg Samsung bina sebenarnya. 

Tahu Menara Burj Khalifa kat Dubai? 

Samsung juga yang bina tu. 

Okay sebenarnya apa je yg Samsung tak buat. haha
Translated Text:
It's not just KLCC that Samsung actually built.

Do you know the Burj Khalifa Tower in Dubai?

Samsung also built it.

Okay, what is Samsung not doing? haha

Text:
Ahmad Dawjee Dadabhoy ni memang businesman yg berjaya. Lahir kat India, tetapi masa tahun 1940-an, beliau memilih untuk settle down kat KL. 

Walaupun ada bisnes yang hebat & harta yang banyak, beliau memilih untuk tinggal kat rumah flat di Masjid India.
Translated Text:
Ahmad Dawjee Dadabhoy is a successful businessman. Born in India, but in the 1940s, he chose to settle down in KL.

Although there is a great business & a lot of property, he chose to live in a flat in Masjid India.

Text:
Mana ada orang sangka, seorang lelaki yang tinggal kat rumah flat tu rupa-rupanya businesman yg sangat dermawan. Tah2 mak ayah kita dulu ada berselisih bahu dgn dia kat Masjid India dulu. Haha

Beliau kekal tinggal di rumah tu sampailah beliau meninggal dunia pada tahun 1987.
Translated Text:
No one would think that a man who lives in that flat is apparently a very generous businessman. My father's mother used to have a disagreement with him at the Indian Mosque. Haha

He remained living in that house until he died in 1987.

Text:
Sebelum beliau meninggal dunia, beliau telah mewakafkan beberapa harta untuk kegunaan umat islam. 

Antara harta beliau yang diwakafkan adalah sebidang tanah seluas 1.2 hektar di Jalan Perak (KL), tiga biji rumah, satu kedai kat Pertama Complex & pemilikan sahamnya.
Translated Text:
Before he died, he had endowed several properties for the use of Muslims.

Among his property that was waqf is a 1.2 hectare plot of land in Jalan Perak (KL), three houses, a shop at Pertama Complex & share ownership.

Text:
Kesemua harta yang diwakafkan tu sekarang diuruskan oleh MAIWP melalui “vesting order” yang dikeluarkan oleh Mahkamah Tinggi Kuala Lumpur. 

Tanah yang diwakafkan, telah dibangunkan dengan kerjasama MAIWP, Lembaga Tabung Haji (LTH) dan Bank Islam Malaysia Berhad (BIMB).
Translated Text:
All the waqf properties are now managed by MAIWP through a "vesting order" issued by the Kuala Lumpur High Court.

The waqf land was developed in collaboration with MAIWP, Lembaga Tabung Haji (LTH) and Bank Islam Malaysia Berhad (BIMB).

Text:
Jadi kalau korang lalu Jalan Perak dan nampak Menara Bank Islam, ketahuilah itu merupakan tanah yang diwakafkan oleh Ahmad Dawjee. Sedekahkanlah al-Fatihah buatnya.

Seorang hartawan yang memilih kehidupan yang sangat zuhud dan sentiasa meletakkan kepentingan ummat dihadapan.
Translated Text:
So if you pass Jalan Perak and see Menara Bank Islam, know that it is land donated by Ahmad Dawjee. Give al-Fatihah as charity for him.

A tycoon who chooses a very ascetic life and always puts the interests of the community first.

Text:
Bukan tu je harta yang ditinggalkan. Lepas beliau meninggal dunia, koleksi buku beliau telah dikumpulkan dan semuanya berjumlah 1077 buah buku. 

Buku-buku tu semua disimpan di Perpustakaan Institut Profesional Baitulmal, Kampung Pandan.
Translated Text:
That's not the property left behind. After he died, his book collection was collected and totaled 1077 books.

The books are all stored in the Baitulmal Professional Institute Library, Kampung Pandan.

Text:
“Apabila seseorang manusia mati, segala amalannya akan terputus kecuali daripada tiga sumber, iaitu sedekah jariah, ilmu yang boleh dimanfaatkan dan anak soleh yang sering mendoakannya.”

Hadis Riwayat Muslim (1631)
Translated Text:
"When a person dies, all his deeds will be cut off except from three sources, namely charity, knowledge that can be used and pious children who often pray for him."

Muslim Narrated Hadith (1631)

Text:
Inilah market capitalisation Apple sejak Tim Cook jadi CEO dari 2012 sampai 2021. 

Kalau korang perasan, takdelah smooth je nak cecah 2.5 trillion valuation ni. Ada up & down. 

2015 dulu pernah ada krisis yg menyebabkan Tim Cook ubah direction Apple. https://t.co/p193rVfuFF
Translated Text:
This is Apple's market capitalization since Tim Cook was CEO from 2012 to 2021.

If you notice, it's not smooth enough to break this 2.5 trillion valuation. There are up & down.

In 2015, there was a crisis that caused Tim Cook to change Apple's direction. https://t.co/p193rVfuFF

Text:
Apa krisis yg jadi?

Waktu 2015 dulu, investor percaya yg jualan iPhone ni akan merudum atau akan tunjukkan trend penurunan setiap tahun.

Analysts at Credit Suisse, Morgan Stanley and Stifel semua turunkan estimation utk jualan iPhone tahun tu. https://t.co/SA348qqQtp
Translated Text:
What's the crisis going on?

Back in 2015, investors believed those selling iPhones would fade or show a downward trend every year.

Analysts at Credit Suisse, Morgan Stanley and Stifel all lowered their estimates for iPhone sales that year. https://t.co/SA348qqQtp

Text:
So sejak dari situ, daripada fokus kepada hardware semata-mata, Tim Cook ubah direction Apple ni kepada service-based provider.

✅iCloud
✅AppleTV
✅AppleNews
✅AppleMusic
✅AppleStore

So diorang lebih fokus utk provide servis ni kpd existing client diorg. https://t.co/WVMhNVvPXV
Translated Text:
So since then, instead of focusing solely on hardware, Tim Cook changed Apple's direction to a service-based provider.

✅ iCloud
✅ Apple TV
✅AppleNews
✅ Apple Music
✅ Apple Store

So people are more focused on providing this service to their existing clients. https://t.co/WVMhNVvPXV

Text:
Diorang tak perlu mencari customer base baru untuk tingkatkan revenue company, instead dia boleh fokuskan utk jaga pelanggan sedia ada.

Bila diorang fokus dekat servis macam ni, customer retention rate pun meningkat sbb customer dah terikat dengan segala jenis servis ni.
Translated Text:
People do not need to find a new customer base to increase the company's revenue, instead they can focus on taking care of existing customers.

When people focus on this kind of service, the customer retention rate also increases because the customer is bound to all types of this service.

Text:
The growth of Apple's services business berubah daripada $2.95 billion in fiscal 2011 kepada $53.77 billion in fiscal 2020.

This is one of major reason yg menyebabkan investor percaya yg Apple still boleh survive & grow dengan strategi baru ni.
Translated Text:
The growth of Apple's services business changed from $2.95 billion in fiscal 2011 to $53.77 billion in fiscal 2020.

This is one of the major reasons that causes investors to believe that Apple can still survive & grow with this new strategy.

Text:
Gitulah macam mana Tim Cook boleh jadikan Apple one of a few companies yg cecah valuation 1 Trillion dalam masa kurang 10 tahun.

Dan dalam 2 tahun berjaya jadikan Apple punya market capitalisation cecah 2 Trillion.
Translated Text:
That's how Tim Cook can make Apple one of a few companies with a valuation of 1 Trillion in less than 10 years.

And in 2 years managed to make Apple's market capitalization reach 2 Trillion.

Text:

But that's the interesting part, right? When there is a challenge, force us to think how to grow our company even better.

Text:
Kalau tengok daripad hasil research tu, kita dapat tengok perbezaan ketara antara character count dibawah 50 dan diatas 100.

Which means?

Headline terlampau pendek pun tak bagus.

Headline terlampau panjang pun tak bagus.
Translated Text:
If we look at the results of the research, we can see a significant difference between the character count below 50 and above 100.

Which means?

A headline that is too short is also not good.

Headlines that are too long are also not good.

Text:
Jadi bila kita nak buat headline, yg paling optimum adalah 60-70. Tapi kalau terlampau banyak/sikit huruf tu, buatlah dalam range 55-100.

Bila terlebih 100, memang engagement akan drop kaw-kaw punya.

Tapi kita nak tulis headline yg macam mana?
Translated Text:
So when we want to make a headline, the most optimal is 60-70. But if there are too many/too few letters, make it in the range of 55-100.

If it is more than 100, the engagement will drop.

But what kind of headline do we want to write?

Text:
Dalam kajian yg sama, BuzzSumo analyze headline dengan frasa yg merujuk kepada beberapa kategori. Antaranya:

1. Instructional
2. Hyperbole
3. Surprise
4. Curiosity
5. Guidance

Hasilnya, headline yg ada perkataan instructional ni akan mengundang banyak share. https://t.co/Y0oSTC7iZo
Translated Text:
In the same study, BuzzSumo analyzed headlines with phrases that refer to several categories. Among them:

1. Instructional
2. Hyperbole
3. Surprise
4. Curiosity
5. Guidance

As a result, headlines with the word instruction will invite many shares. https://t.co/Y0oSTC7iZo

Text:
Sebab tu kalau tengok, resipi, tutorial dan apa2 konten 'how to', mudah untuk dikongsi oleh pembaca.

Hyperbole pulak apa? Hyperbole tu clickbait lah basically. Haha

So instead of buat headline yg clickbait je, buatlah headline yg bersifat instructional. Lg beretika & berkualiti
Translated Text:
That's why if you look at recipes, tutorials and any 'how to' content, it's easy for readers to share.

What is hyperbole? Hyperbole is basically clickbait. Haha

So instead of making a clickbait headline, make an instructional headline. Lg ethical & quality

Text:
Lepas dah berjaya dapatkan attention reader daripada headline kita, next kita kena make sure introduction kita tu cukup power supaya pembaca habiskan pembacaan diorg.

Daripada 1000 orang yg klik untuk baca, 90% akan blah bila intro kita tak cukup power.
Translated Text:
After successfully getting the reader's attention from our headline, next we have to make sure our introduction is powerful enough so that the reader finishes reading it.

Out of 1000 people who click to read, 90% will blah if our intro is not powerful enough.

Text:
That's why penting untuk kita pastikan kesinambungan tu. Hehe.

And most importantly, make sure kita deliver apa yg kita dah janjikan pada pembaca2 kita tu.
Translated Text:
That's why it's important for us to ensure that continuity. Hehe.

And most importantly, make sure we deliver what we have promised to our readers.

Text:
1. Belanja lebih daripada income

Ada satu survey yang pernah dibuat oleh RinggitPlus. Daripada ribuan yg jawab survey tu, 30% daripadanya bagitahu yg memang diorang komitmen bulanan = gaji.

Dan separuh daripada 30% tu spend more than their income.
Translated Text:
1. Spend more than income

There is a survey that was once made by RinggitPlus. Of the thousands who answered the survey, 30% of them told me that monthly commitment = salary.

And half of that 30% spend more than their income.

Text:
Maksudnya, daripada 10,000, 3000 orang memang tak ada saving langsung setiap bulan.

Dan daripada 3000 tu, 1500 tu bukan setakat takde saving tapi setiap bulan bertambah hutangnya.

Aduhai kesian betul.
Translated Text:
That means, out of 10,000, 3000 people do not have any savings at all every month.

And out of the 3000, the 1500 is not only not saving, but the debt increases every month.

What a pity.

Text:
Mesti korang terfikir macam mana orang boleh spend more than their income.

Jawapannya mestilah daripada credit card atau personal loan. Dua hutang yg selalu merosakkan masa depan kalau tidak digunakan dengan betul.
Translated Text:
You must be thinking how people can spend more than their income.

The answer must be from a credit card or personal loan. Two debts that always ruin the future if not used correctly.

Text:
2. Semakin besar gaji, semakin banyak komitmen

Dalam survey yang sama dibuat, diorang nak tahu berapa banyak orang dalam kategori gaji 2K-5K, 5K-10K dan 10K+ simpan 1K dan lebih.

Mesti korang ingat yg gaji 10K+ ni boleh simpan 1K kan? Haha saya pun ingat camtu
Translated Text:
2. The bigger the salary, the more commitment

Text:
Statistik sebenar:

– 88% Malaysians yg bergaji 2k - 5K simpan kurang 1K setiap bulan.
– 67% Malaysians yg bergaji 5k - 10K simpan kurang 1K setiap bulan.
– 31% Malaysians yg bergaji 10K+ simpan kurang 1K setiap bulan.

Terkejut tak dengan statistik ni?
Translated Text:
Actual stats:

– 88% of Malaysians who earn 2k - 5k save less than 1k every month.
– 67% of Malaysians who earn 5k - 10k save less than 1k every month.
– 31% of Malaysians who earn 10K+ save less than 1K every month.

Are you surprised by this statistic?

Text:
Tbh, saya agak terkejut. Sebab saya jangka untuk yg gaji in between 5K - 10K, lebih separuh yg boleh simpan 1K+. Tapi 33% je boleh simpan banyak tu.

Dan yg lagi terkejut, dgn gaji 10K+ pun ada 31% yg tak mampu simpan 1K+.
Translated Text:
Tbh, I'm a bit surprised. Because I expect for those whose salary is between 5K - 10K, more than half can save 1K+. But only 33% can save that much.

And what's more surprising, even with a salary of 10K+, there are 31% who can't afford to save 1K+.

Text:

Kereta bertambah mewah mungkin.
Rumah bertambah besar mungkin.

Akhirnya tak mampu nak saving.
Translated Text:
Maybe some of these percentages are due to concrete not being able to store.

But mostly, when the salary increases, the commitment also increases.

More luxurious cars may be.
The house can get bigger.

Finally unable to save.
