Text:
1. Guna page/profile manusia

Walaupun page ni confirm fake, haha tapi kita nampak yg iklan daripada page mcm ni terima engagement yg lagi baik. 

Sebab bila iklan ni muncul kat timeline, tak ramai pun yg rajin untuk klik dekat profile utk cek. https://t.co/NLCOY823v5
Translated Text:
1. Use a human page/profile

Even though this page is confirmed to be fake, haha, we see that ads from this page receive better engagement.

Because when this ad appears on the timeline, not many people are diligent enough to click on the profile to check. https://t.co/NLCOY823v5

Text:
Bila dah ada call to action & link untuk diorang beli, org yg nampak & berminat akan terus klik link & buat decision untuk beli atau tak dekat web tu.

Bila ‘orang’ yg recommend ni impact dia berbeza daripada brand yg recommend.
Translated Text:
When there is a call to action & link for people to buy, people who see & interested will continue to click the link & make a decision to buy or not near that website.

When the 'person' who recommends this has a different impact than the recommended brand.

Text:
2. Bercerita

Disebabkan profile/page tu macam manusia, jadi dia create satu cerita yg sangat menarik & relatable.

Kalau tengok struktur penulisan pun nampak mcm manusia biasa. https://t.co/oiuEzsifVe
Translated Text:
2. Tell a story

Because the profile/page is like a human being, so he created a very interesting story & relatable.

If you look at the writing structure, it looks like a normal human. https://t.co/oiuEzsifVe

Text:
3. Natural

Dia exploit features yg ada dalam FB untuk nampakkan dia real.

Emotion, location & penggunaan emoji dalam penulisan jadikan iklan ni sangat natural & tak macam iklan. https://t.co/NesdByNoML
Translated Text:
3. Natural

He exploits features in FB to make him appear real.

Text:

Kita tak sedar pun yg dia tengah promote kat kita.

Text:
Starbucks gift card ni launch pada tahun 2001. Tahun tu, ramai dah start ada member card / loyalty card etc, but starbucks buat lain sikit, card dia boleh reload.

Boleh reload tapi orang tak boleh cashkan duitnya. Haha
Translated Text:
The Starbucks gift card was launched in 2001. That year, many people started having member cards / loyalty cards etc., but Starbucks made it a little different, the card can be reloaded.

You can reload but people can't cash the money. Haha

Text:
So setiap kali orang reload card, duit tu diorang kira as loan. Ni bukan saya kata, tapi memang ada dalam annual report diorang.

Bawah ni screenshot annual report Starbucks tahun 2018 dulu. https://t.co/avBWstvDhG
Translated Text:
So every time people reload the card, the money is counted as a loan. I didn't say this, but it is in someone's annual report.

Below is a screenshot of the Starbucks annual report in 2018. https://t.co/avBWstvDhG

Text:
So basically, untuk tahun 2018 dulu korang (yg ada starbuck card) pinjamkan pada Starbucks USD1.6 Billion weh.

Dan apa yg kita dapat dengan pinjamkan duit kat Starbucks? 

Takde apa.
Translated Text:
So basically, for the year 2018, you (those who have a starbuck card) loaned Starbucks USD 1.6 billion.

And what do we get by lending money to Starbucks?

It's okay.

Text:
In fact, pada tahun yg sama Starbucks dapat keuntungan USD185 juta disebabkan unredeemable reload card ni.

So biasanya, bila company buat loan dia kena bayar interest pada bank. 

Tapi bila Starbucks buat loan daripada customer (through gift card), dia pulak yg untung 10%.
Translated Text:
In fact, in the same year, Starbucks made a profit of USD 185 million due to this unredeemable reload card.

So usually, when a company makes a loan, it has to pay interest to the bank.

But when Starbucks makes a loan from a customer (through a gift card), he gets 10% profit.

Text:
What makes it more interesting adalah, loan ni takde apa2 restriction & risk pada Starbucks.

Sebab apa?

Sebab reload ni tak boleh ditunaikan pun. 

Once customer reload card, diorang cuma boleh beli kopi.
Translated Text:
What makes it more interesting is that this loan has no restrictions & risk at Starbucks.

Why?

Because this reload cannot be redeemed.

Once the customer reloads the card, people can only buy coffee.

Text:
Jadi apa risk pada Starbucks? None.

Even, bank pun ada risk tau, starbucks takde risk langsung. Haha

Tengoklah apa jadi bila ramai orang keluarkan duit daripada bank macam yg jadi kat Afghanistan baru2 ni.
Translated Text:
So what is the risk at Starbucks? None.

Even, even banks have risks, you know, starbucks has no risk at all. Haha

Look what happens when many people withdraw money from the bank like what happened in Afghanistan recently.

Text:
So yeah, that’s how Starbucks ‘menggunakan’ customer untuk grow lg bisnes diorang tanpa buatkan customer rasa dipergunakan. Haha

Sekarang Starbucks ada 32,392 stores di seluruh dunia.

Dkt Malaysia pun ada lebih 300 outlet. https://t.co/59LpCsA4jj
Translated Text:
So yeah, that's how Starbucks 'uses' customers to grow their own business without making the customer feel used. Ha ha

Now Starbucks has 32,392 stores worldwide.

In Malaysia there are also more than 300 outlets. https://t.co/59LpCsA4jj

Text:
1. Know your game and always have a plan

Kalau korang tengok Money Heist ni, Professor sentiasa ada plan. Ada satu babak Raquel tanya pada professor,

‘How long did it take to study every move we make, each time?’
Translated Text:
1. Know your game and always have a plan

Kalau korang tengok Money Heist ni, Professor sentiasa ada plan. Ada satu babak Raquel tanya pada professor,

‘How long did it take to study every move we make, each time?’

Text:
Jawapan Professor,

‘To be honest — half my life.’

Sebelum kita launch produk kita, always do our research. Plan properly & execute it nicely.
Translated Text:
Jawapan Professor,

‘To be honest — half my life.’

Sebelum kita launch produk kita, always do our research. Plan properly & execute it nicely.

Text:
Sentiasa ada backup plan if something happens.

Contoh kita launch produk, server crash. Apa yang kita kena buat?

Waktu kita launch produk, online banking down, apa payment method yg kita nak bagi pada customer?
Translated Text:
Always have a backup plan if something happens.

For example, we launch a product, the server crashes. What are we supposed to do?

When we launch the product, online banking is down, what payment method do we want to share with customers?

Text:
Hope for the best. 

But always prepare for the worst.

Tp janganlah sibuk plan bertahun2 tapi tak execute langsung. Haha. Ini pun banyak jugak terjadi.
Translated Text:
Hope for the best.

But always prepare for the worst.

But don't be busy planning for years but don't execute it right away. Ha ha. This also happens a lot.

Text:
2. Connect your team to a cause

Perasan tak yang semua dalam team members dalam Money Heist ni ada emotional attachment dengan mission diorang.

Diorang punya bonding antara satu sama lain pun sgt kuat.
Translated Text:
2. Connect your team to a cause

Don't you notice that all of the team members in Money Heist have an emotional attachment to their mission.

People have a very strong bonding with each other.

Text:
So kita pun perlu terapkan perkara yg sama untuk bangunkan team kita.

Pastikan apa rewards & mission yg team kita letakkan melebihi personal objectives setiap orang dalam team.

And make sure everyone keeps motivated by it.
Translated Text:
So we also need to apply the same thing to develop our team.

Make sure what rewards & The mission that our team puts above the personal objectives of each person in the team.

And make sure everyone keeps motivated by it.

Text:
3. Delegate the tasks

As a leader, do not try to do it all yourself.

Bila kita hire team members kita, mesti kita dah tahu diorang punya strength & weakness. So kita kena delegates the tasks properly.

Janganlah pulak bagi task yg kita tahu mmg dia lemah.
Translated Text:
3. Delegate the tasks

As a leader, don't try to do it all yourself.

When we hire our team members, we must already know that people have strength & weakness. So we have to delegate the tasks properly.

Don't give him tasks that we know he's weak at.

Text:
And please, janganlah kita micro manage our team. Kadang ada bos yg rasa decision dia saja yg betul. 

Dah tu buat apa kita ada team? Haha

Percayalah dengan kekuatan team members kita.
Translated Text:
And please, let's not micro manage our team. Sometimes there is a boss who thinks his decision is the right one.

Why do we have a team? Haha

Trust in the strength of our team members.

Text:
4. Execution is more important than theory

Kita dah ada plan, dah ada team members yg power, dah delegate all the tasks. Pastu nak buat apa lagi?

Execute.
Translated Text:
4. Execution is more important than theory

We already have a plan, we have team members who have power, we have delegated all the tasks. What else do you want to do?

Execute.

Text:
Execution part is always the hardest.

Tapi tanpa execution, tak jadi apa lah plan kita. Haha.

Apa pun jadi, ingat always stick to the plan.
Translated Text:
Execution part is always the hardest.

But without execution, it doesn't matter what our plan is. Ha ha.

Whatever happens, remember to always stick to the plan.

Text:
5. Fight for survival

Fight dan terus survive.

Tak semua teori akan menjadi. Lebih banyak perkara yg tak diharap terjadi daripada perkara yg kita harapkan.

Dan kita kena terus fight utk survive.
Translated Text:
5. Fight for survival

Fight and continue to survive.

Not all theories will be. More unexpected things happen than what we expect.

And we have to keep fighting to survive.

Text:
Make sure bisnes kita boleh adapt dengan situation semasa.

Keep on fighting sampailah kita menang.

After all, what’s more human than the fight for survival?
Translated Text:
Make sure our business can adapt to the current situation.

Keep on fighting until we win.

After all, what's more human than the fight for survival?

Translated Text: @FezzaHussin but what kind of customer do you get like Arturo Roman?

Text:
1 - Konsisten buka kedai.

Ada seorang peniaga ni nampak laku betul jualan dia pagi-pagi. Dah 2 tahun dia meniaga dekat situ. 

Tapi waktu dia baru start, hari-hari kuih tak habis.

Berapa bulan mcm tu?
Translated Text:
1 - Consistently open a store.

There is a merchant who seems to sell well in the morning. He has been doing business near there for 2 years.

But when he just started, the days of the cake did not end.

How many months is that?

Text:
4 bulan.

Dalam tempoh 4 bulan tu, memang sentiasa ada lebihan kuih walaupun bukak gerai sampai ke tengahari.

Tapi dia tetap konsisten bukak kedai sampailah ke hari ni.
Translated Text:
4 months.

During those 4 months, there is always a surplus of cookies even if the stall is open until noon.

But he remains consistent in opening the shop until this day.

Text:
Hari ni, purata jualan kuih dia lebih daripada 700 pack setiap hari. Satu pack harga dalam range RM2 - RM3.

Dia pesan,

Awal2 memang susah nak laku barang kita sbb orang belum kenal. Bila dah lama, kita dah ada pelanggan setia. Tapi syaratnya kena tahanlah sakit fasa awal tu.
Translated Text:
Today, his average cake sales are more than 700 packs per day. One pack price in the range of RM2 - RM3.

He ordered,

At first, it was difficult to sell our products because people didn't know them yet. For a long time, we have loyal customers. But the condition is that you have to endure the pain in the initial phase.

Text:
2 - Jaga kualiti produk

Ada sorang makcik ni jual nasi berlauk. Kalau tengok barisan waktu tengahari, aduhai memang panjang, tapi takdelah tunggu lama sangat sbb makcik ni buat kerja laju je.

Roughly ada lebih 200 pelanggan yang beli nasi campur daripada makcik ni setiap hari.
Translated Text:
2 - Take care of product quality

There is an aunt who sells rice with side dishes. If you look at the lunch line, it's really long, but don't wait too long because this aunt works fast.

Roughly there are more than 200 customers who buy mixed rice from this aunt every day.

Text:
Harga yg dijual pun tak murah tapi lauk2 dia memang semua sedap2. Ayam masak merah dia fuh memang terbaik. Haha

Pesan makcik ni,

Bila nak berniaga, kualiti dulu baru harga.
Translated Text:
The price they sell is not cheap, but their dishes are all delicious. Her red cooked chicken is really the best. Haha

This aunt's message,

When you want to do business, quality comes first, then price.

Text:
Pastikan apa yg kita jual ni berkualiti, lepas tu kita letaklah harga berapa pun mesti akan ada orang yg beli punya.

Tapi gerai makcik ni takdelah dia letak harga kaw2, biasa2 je. Haha
Translated Text:
Make sure what we sell is of good quality, then whatever price we put there must be people who buy it.

But at this aunt's stall, she doesn't put the price on you, it's normal. Haha

Text:
3. Layanan pada pelanggan

Ada sorang pakcik ni jual laksa dekat gerai dia. Kalau selalu beli kat gerai dia, konfem dia akan ingat nama kita dan menu yg kita selalu order.

Kalau biasa datang dgn kawan, harini datang sorang pun dia akan perasan jugak.
Translated Text:
3. Customer service

Text:
5. Rahsia kejayaan

Dalam satu interview dengan Andy Chin, Marketing VP MrDIY, dia sharekan antara rahsia kejayaan diorang boleh expand dengan sangat pantas. 

Antara pointnya...
Translated Text:
5. The secret of success

In an interview with Andy Chin, MrDIY's Marketing VP, he shared one of the secrets of success that people can expand very quickly.

Among the points...

Text:
1. Always look at the competitors, how they've done it. MrDIY banyak rujuk bisnes dalam sektor yg sama di luar negara.

2. Cut cost dengan strategi yg betul. Antara yg dilakukan adalah purchase with volume commitment (utk dapatkan better price) & uruskan logisitik sendiri.
Translated Text:
1. Always look at the competitors, how they've done it. MrDIY consults many businesses in the same sector abroad.

2. Cut costs with the right strategy. Among the things done is purchase with volume commitment (to get a better price) & handle logistics yourself.

Text:
3. React quckly to changes in the market. Other well-established plan & larger company biasa ada process decision-making yg panjang & jadikan company tu lambat react.

4. Data is the new oil. Untuk expand sepantas ni, bukan dengan keputusan membuta tuli, tapi dengan data.
Translated Text:
3. React quickly to changes in the market. Other well-established plans & Larger companies usually have a long & make the company slow to react.

4. Data is the new oil. To expand properly, not by blind decision, but by data.

Text:
Amazon diasaskan pada tahun 1994 dengan loan daripada parents Jeff Bezos. Parents dia bagi pinjam 100K untuk dia start Amazon ni.

Pada tahun 1997, Amazon go public. Waktu tu saham Amazon didagangkan pada harga $18/share.

Tahu harga dia sekarang brp?

$3500/share https://t.co/vGkeRZlRXN
Translated Text:
Amazon was founded in 1994 with a loan from Jeff Bezos' parents. His parents loaned him 100K for him to start Amazon.

In 1997, Amazon went public. At that time Amazon shares were trading at $18/share.

Do you know his price now?

$3500/share https://t.co/vGkeRZlRXN

Text:
Okay enough dengan benda dah lepas. Jom kita tengok future Amazon ni.

Walaupun vision Jeff Bezos ni untuk wujudkan largest online bookstore, tapi harini Amazon dah tukar jadi everything store.

Tengok revenue streams dia. https://t.co/cYPzvFq4ty
Translated Text:
Okay enough with the past. Let's see the future of Amazon.

Although Jeff Bezos' vision was to create the largest online bookstore, today Amazon has changed it to an everything store.

Look at his revenue streams. https://t.co/cYPzvFq4ty

Text:
So basically, pendapatan Amazon ni sekarang bukan daripada online store sahaja. Walaupun tak dinafikan online store tu still bagi revenue paling besar.

But, ada tambahan revenue streams lain, which are:

- 3rd party seller service
- Subscription service
- AWS
- Physical store
Translated Text:
So basically, Amazon's income now is not only from the online store. Although there is no denying that the online store still provides the largest revenue.

But, there are additional revenue streams, which are:

- 3rd party seller service
- Subscription service
- AWS
- Physical store

Text:
Dan kalau tengok graf nett profit dia, walaupun revenue dia meningkat drastically every year, nett profit dia tak meningkat sama drastik.

Apa jadi?

Amazon laburkan revenue dia back to the business. That's how we grow. Allocate big portion back to the business bkn mustang. Hahah
Translated Text:
And if you look at his net profit graph, even though his revenue has increased drastically every year, his net profit has not increased as drastically.

what happened?

Amazon is generating its revenue back to the business. That's how we grow. Allocate big portion back to the business not mustang. hahaha

Text:
Antara perkara yg menarik pasal Amazon ni adalah macam mana dia kurangkan cost acquistion utk new customer & improve repeat purchase.

Apa dia buat?

Amazon Prime.
Translated Text:
One of the interesting things about Amazon is how it reduces acquisition costs for new customers & improve repeat purchase.

What did he do?

Amazon Prime.

Text:
Dengan Amazon Prime ni, customer boleh dapat manfaat tambahan. 

Untuk shopping boleh dapat fast & free delivery, exclusive deals, vouchers. https://t.co/L6hf4QxeQS
Translated Text:
With Amazon Prime, customers can get additional benefits.

For shopping you can get fast & free delivery, exclusive deals, vouchers. https://t.co/L6hf4QxeQS

Text:
Kalau perasan, Shopee & Lazada pun dah mula buat perkara yg hampir serupa. Lazada ada voucher club, Shopee ada shopee pass.

Bila kita subscribe voucher club/shopee pass tu kita akan dapat banyak voucher. 

Personally, saya suka lazada voucher club lg. Haha
Translated Text:
If you notice, Shopee & Lazada has started doing something almost similar. Lazada has voucher club, Shopee has shopee pass.

When we subscribe to the voucher club/shopee pass we will get many vouchers.

Personally, I like lazada voucher club again. Haha

Text:
Okay, so what's interesting?

Bila ada Amazon Prime ni, dia reduce customers’ acquisition costs and facilitate repeat purchases.

Sebab customer dah subscribe dengan kita, takkanlah dia pergi beli dkt website lain.
Translated Text:
Okay, so what's interesting?

When Amazon Prime is available, it reduces customers' acquisition costs and facilitates repeat purchases.

Because the customer has subscribed with us, he will not go to buy from another website.

Text:
Contoh saya subscribe lazada voucher club, takkanlah saya nak beli barang yg ada dekat lazada dekat shopee. 

Baik saya guna lazada & manfaatkan segala kupon yg ada tu. 

Dan itu membuatkan customer sentiasa repeat purchase.
Translated Text:
For example, I subscribe to lazada voucher club, I will not want to buy items that are available at lazada or shopee.

Well I use lazada & take advantage of all the coupons that are available.

And that makes customers always repeat purchases.

Text:
Ada banyak sangat perkara yg kita boleh belajar daripada Amazon ni. Antaranya, macam mana prinsip yg dibawa untuk majukan Amazon.

Ada 14 fundamental principles yg diterapkan dalam Amazon. And first sekali yg diletakkan adalah customer obsession. https://t.co/11L0ustnFW
Translated Text:
There are many things we can learn from Amazon. Among them, what kind of principles are brought to advance Amazon.

There are 14 fundamental principles applied in Amazon. And the first thing that is put is customer obsession. https://t.co/11L0ustnFW

Text:
Remember, for business to makes money, it always about our customer.

Dan bila kita berurusan dengan manusia ni, macam biasalah mana pernah statik.

Hari ni majoriti suka ni.
Hari esok majoriti dah tak suka.

Dan bisnes kita nak kena adapt dengan benda tu utk kekal relevan.
Translated Text:
Remember, for business to make money, it's always about our customer.

And when we deal with these people, it's normal to be static.

Today the majority likes this.
Tomorrow the majority will not like it.

And our business needs to adapt to that to remain relevant.

Text:
This is interesting. Not saying that this hack is ethical, tapi ada satu research bagitahu tentang psikologi manusia ketika beratur ni.

Saya ringkaskan research tu dalam thread kat bawah.
Translated Text:
This is interesting. Not saying that this hack is ethical, but there is one research that tells us about human psychology in this regulation.

I summarize the research in the thread below.

Text:
1. Perbezaan respon.

Research yg dibuat bagitahu, ada perbezaan respon terhadap beratur ni antara tangible product dengan non-tangible product.

Tangible product - produk yg fizikal, boleh dilihat, boleh disentuh.

Non tangible product - bukan produk fizikal, servis mostly.
Translated Text:
1. Response differences.

The research that was done told us that there is a difference in response to queuing between tangible products and non-tangible products.

Tangible product - a physical product that can be seen and touched.

Non tangible product - not a physical product, service mostly.

Text:
So dalam research tu conclude yang respon manusia terhadap beratur dekat premis yg sediakan tangible product ni adalah positif.

Maksudnya, manusia suka.

Contoh kedai baju, ramai orang beratur. Haa, ada jual baju apa tu mesti bagus. Jom kita beratur.
Translated Text:
So in the research, it was concluded that the human response to queuing near the premise that provides this tangible product is positive.

Meaning, people like it.

Example of a clothes shop, many people are queuing. Haa, there are clothes for sale, they must be good. Let's get in line.

Text:
Tapi bila dekat non-tangible product, respon pelanggan adalah negatif.

Contohnya klinik, ramai orang beratur. Orang akan rasa doktor tu lambat buat kerja, klinik tu tak bagus etc.
Translated Text:
But when it comes to non-tangible products, the customer's response is negative.

For example the clinic, many people queue. People will think that the doctor is slow to work, the clinic is not good, etc.

Text:
2. Filler waiting time is important.

Filler ni adalah objek/perkara yg pelanggan boleh buat time beratur. Filler can be mental or physical activites.

Contohnya, pelanggan boleh isi masa beratur dengan berborak dengan kawan, main phone etc.
Translated Text:
2. Filler waiting time is important.

This filler is an object/thing that customers can do while queuing. Filler can be mental or physical activities.

For example, customers can fill the queue time by chatting with friends, playing on the phone etc.

Text:
But sebagai tokey kedai, kita juga boleh sediakan filler ni untuk pelanggan. Filler ni can be context related or context unrelated.

Contohnya, bila kita buka kedai makan. Kita boleh sediakan tester as filler waiting time. So waktu pelanggan beratur, diorg boleh rasa tester tu.
Translated Text:
But as a shop tokey, we can also prepare this filler for customers. This filler can be context related or context unrelated.

For example, when we open a restaurant. We can provide testers as filler waiting time. So when customers queue up, people can feel the tester.

Text:
Untuk context unrelated, kedai makan tu boleh sediakan TV.

Untuk isi masa beratur tu, pelanggan boleh tengok TV.

And this filler, will generate positive impact.
Translated Text:
For an unrelated context, the restaurant can provide TV.

For the duration of the queue, customers can watch TV.

And this filler, will generate positive impact.

Text:
3. Emotional response

Beratur ni akan generate scarcity pada pelanggan & pelanggan akan rasa dia perlu compete dengan pelanggan yg lain.

Dan manusia memang fitrah dia sukakan kemenangan.
Translated Text:
3. Emotional response

Queuing will generate scarcity for customers & the customer will feel he has to compete with other customers.

And it is human's nature that he likes to win.

Text:
So this kind of customer tend to make faster decision to buy our product.

First, sebab diorang rasa produk kita bagus.

Second, sebab diorang nak menang & dapatkan produk yg  pelanggan lain pun akan rebut sama.
Translated Text:
So this kind of customer tends to make a faster decision to buy our product.

First, because people think our products are good.

Second, because people want to win & get a product that other customers will grab the same.

Text:
This kind of concept proven by Apple Store setiap tahun.

First day pelancaran, ramai yang sanggup beratur & tunggu berjam atau berhari untuk jadi yg pertama dapatkan produk tu.

Sebab apa?

Sebab dia rasa dia menang bila jd yg pertama.
Translated Text:
This kind of concept proven by Apple Store every year.

First day of launch, many are willing to queue & wait hours or days to be the first to get the product.

Why?

Because he thinks he wins when he is the first.

Text:
Semua kemudahan ini akan berkuatkuasa bermula 10 Ogos 2021.

Berikut antara perkara penting untuk kefahaman bersama :

MAKSUD VAKSINASI LENGKAP :

💉 Vaksin jenis dua dos suntikan (Pfizer, AstraZeneca dan Sinovac) : Telah MELEPASI HARI KE-14 dari tarikh suntikan dos kedua.
Translated Text:
All these facilities will be effective from 10 August 2021.

Here are some important things for mutual understanding:

MEANING OF COMPLETE VACCINATION :

💉 Two-dose injection type vaccine (Pfizer, AstraZeneca and Sinovac): 14 DAYS have passed from the date of the second dose injection.

Text: 💉 Vaksin jenis satu dos suntikan (Johnson & Johnson dan CanSino) : Telah MELEPASI HARI KE-28 dari tarikh suntikan.
Translated Text: 💉 Single-dose vaccine (Johnson & Johnson and CanSino) : DAY 28 has passed from the date of injection.

Text:
KEMUDAHAN KUARANTIN DAN PERJALANAN 

Kemudahan ini untuk individu yang telah menerima vaksinasi lengkap DI SELURUH NEGARA (semua fasa PPN).

1️⃣ 🏠 Pengembara yang pulang atau tiba dari luar negara dan telah divaksin lengkap, DIBENARKAN jalani kuarantin wajib di rumah.
Translated Text:
QUARANTINE AND TRAVEL FACILITIES

This facility is for individuals who have received complete vaccination NATIONWIDE (all phases of PPN).

1️⃣ 🏠 Travelers who return or arrive from abroad and have been fully vaccinated, are ALLOWED to undergo mandatory quarantine at home.

Text:
2️⃣ 👫 Pasangan suami isteri jarak jauh yang telah divaksin lengkap DIBENARKAN rentas daerah/negeri untuk bertemu pasangan masing-masing.

3️⃣ 👨‍👩‍👧 Ibu bapa yang telah divaksin lengkap DIBENARKAN rentas daerah/negeri untuk berjumpa anak berumur bawah 18 tahun.
Translated Text:
2️⃣ 👫 Long-distance married couples who have been fully vaccinated are ALLOWED cross-district/state to meet their respective partners.

3️⃣ 👨‍👩‍👧 Parents who have been fully vaccinated are ALLOWED cross-district/state to see children under the age of 18.

Text:
KEMUDAHAN KEAGAMAAN

Kemudahan ini untuk individu yang telah menerima vaksinasi lengkap DI NEGERI FASA 1 DAN FASA 2

1️⃣ 🕌 Aktiviti solat di masjid dan surau bagi individu (umat Islam) yang telah divaksin lengkap DIBENARKAN tertakluk kepada ketetapan Pihak Berkuasa Agama Negeri
Translated Text:
RELIGIOUS FACILITIES

This facility is for individuals who have received complete vaccination IN PHASE 1 AND PHASE 2 STATES

1️⃣ 🕌 Prayer activities in mosques and suraus for individuals (Muslims) who have been fully vaccinated are ALLOWED subject to the ruling of the State Religious Authority

Text: 2️⃣ ⛪️ Aktivti sembahyang di Rumah Ibadat Selain Islam (RISI) bagi individu (penganut selain Islam) yang telah divaksin lengkap DIBENARKAN tertakluk kepada ketetapan Kementerian Perpaduan Negara (KPN)
Translated Text: 2️⃣ ⛪️ Prayer activities at Non-Islamic Houses of Worship (RISI) for individuals (non-Islamic adherents) who have been fully vaccinated are ALLOWED subject to the ruling of the Ministry of National Unity (KPN)

Text:
KEMUDAHAN SEKTOR SOSIAL

Kemudahan ini untuk individu yang telah menerima vaksinasi lengkap di NEGERI-NEGERI DALAM FASA 2 DAN SETERUSNYA

1️⃣ 🚗 Rentas daerah DIBENARKAN.
 
2️⃣ 🍽 Aktiviti dine-in DIBENARKAN.
Translated Text:
SOCIAL SECTOR FACILITIES

This facility is for individuals who have received complete vaccination in STATES IN PHASE 2 AND BEYOND

1️⃣ 🚗 Cross-district ALLOWED.
 
2️⃣ 🍽 Dine-in activities are ALLOWED.

Text:
3️⃣ 🚴‍♂️ Sukan dan riadah outdoor tanpa sentuhan dan aktiviti berkumpulan DIBENARKAN.

4️⃣ 🏫🏘 Aktiviti pelancongan dalam negeri sama DIBENARKAN melibatkan homestay dan hotel.
Translated Text:
3️⃣ 🚴‍♂️ Outdoor sports and leisure without contact and group activities are ALLOWED.

4️⃣ 🏫🏘 Domestic tourism activities are also ALLOWED involving homestays and hotels.

Text:
So basically saya rasa tu je kot yg worth highlighting daripada pengumuman tadi. If saya ada terlepas pandang atau tersalah tulis, mohon betulkan ya.

Anyway, stay safe & tak care everyone.

Text:
Okay but first of all, apa yang saya cerita ni bukanlah palatao saya sendiri. Hahah

Tapi ini adalah berdasarkan beberapa jurnal research yang ditulis & dipublish ya. 

Rujuk link ResearchGate ni: https://t.co/CEnYbpSRgH
Translated Text:
Okay but first of all, what I'm telling you about is not my own palatao. hahaha

But this is based on several research journals written & published yes.

Refer to this ResearchGate link: https://t.co/CEnYbpSRgH

Text:
Okay, so basically dalam research ni ada 5 hipotesis awal yang diorang nak kaji.

Janganlah tanya pasal research methodology dia ya, kalau nak tahu methodology boleh baca paper tu sendiri. Haha

Let's talk about their conclusion.
Translated Text:
Okay, so basically in this research there are 5 initial hypotheses that people want to study.

Don't ask about his research methodology, if you want to know the methodology you can read the paper yourself. Haha

Let's talk about their conclusion.

Text:
1. Brand knowledge affects consumer behavior.

So dalam paper ni conclude yang bila satu2 brand tu lebih dikenali, consumer tend to choose that brand compared to other brands.

"Consumer buying behavior will increase or decrease with 
brand knowledge."
Translated Text:
1. Brand knowledge affects consumer behavior.

So dalam paper ni conclude yang bila satu2 brand tu lebih dikenali, consumer tend to choose that brand compared to other brands.

"Consumer buying behavior will increase or decrease with 
brand knowledge."

Text:
2. Effect of Reference Groups on Consumer Buying Behavior

Jawapannya juga betul. Reference group memberi kesan pada buying decision.

Untuk yg lebih suka bersosial, kawan lebih mempengaruhi buying decision diorang daripada family.
Translated Text:
2. Effect of Reference Groups on Consumer Buying Behavior

The answer is also correct. Reference group affects the buying decision.

For those who prefer to socialize, friends influence people's buying decisions more than family.

Text:
3. Old Consumers tend to be More Brand Loyal

Betul ke?

Yup, pun betul juga.

Kalau nak consumer yang setia, pilihlah mereka yang berusia. Old is gold they say. Hehe
Translated Text:
3. Old consumers tend to be more brand loyal

Really?

Yup, that's right too.

If you want loyal consumers, choose those who are old. Old is gold they say. Hehe

Text:
4. Emotional exploitation is important for affecting 
consumer buying behavior.

Based on this research, the answer is yes. 

"Emotional exploitation affects the consumer behavior on basis of perception of consumers."

Penting jaga emosi pelanggan.
Translated Text:
4. Emotional exploitation is important for affecting 
consumer buying behavior.

Based on this research, the answer is yes. 

"Emotional exploitation affects the consumer behavior on basis of perception of consumers."

Penting jaga emosi pelanggan.

Text:
5. Consumer behavior fluctuates on the gender basis.

Tidak.

Maksudnya, sama je lelaki dengan perempuan. Bila dia dah percaya dengan satu-satu brand, buying decisionnya akan lebih memihak kepada brand tu.
Translated Text:
5. Consumer behavior fluctuates on the gender basis.

Nope.

Meaning, men and women are the same. When he believes in one brand, his buying decision will be more in favor of that brand.

Text:
So adakah branding penting?

Based on this research, jawapannya adalah ya. Sangat penting.

Bila brand kita lebih diketahui terutamanya disebabkan kualiti produk kita, maka kita akan lebih bertahan lama dalam sepak terajang industri kita. Hehe
Translated Text:
So is branding important?

Based on this research, the answer is yes. Very important.

If our brand is better known mainly due to the quality of our products, then we will last longer in our industry. Hehe

Text:
Waktu Ramly Mokni nak start business, dia apply loan MARA. Berapa?

RM7,000.

Sikit kan?

Nilai tu mmg kecik sgt utk MARA approve. Tapi disebabkan MARA sendiri  tak percaya dengan market segment yang Ramly Mokni propose, loan 7000 tu pun kena reject.

So apa Ramly Mokni buat?
Translated Text:
When Ramly Mokni wanted to start a business, he applied for a MARA loan. How much?

RM7,000.

A little right?

That value is too small for MARA to approve. But because MARA itself did not believe in the market segment that Ramly Mokni proposed, the loan of 7000 had to be rejected.

So what does Ramly Mokni do?

Text:
Dia tetap mulakan bisnes dia dengan modal yang dia ada. Berapa?

RM2,000.

Yup, dengan RM2000 je dia berjaya kembangkan perniagaan dia sehingga menjadi top  player dalam food industry dekat Malaysia. Power weh. Haha

Apa yang dia buat dengan resources yang limited tu?
Translated Text:
He still started his business with the capital he had. How much?

RM2,000.

Yup, with only RM2000 he managed to grow his business until he became a top player in the food industry near Malaysia. It's powerful. Haha

What did he do with the limited resources?

Text:
Dengan RM2,000 tu dia mulakan production burger dia dari rumah. Waktu awal-awal dia start, sehari cuma boleh produce dalam 100-200 daging burger je.

Lepas dah buat daging burger tu, mesti kena jual. Jadi macam mana cara dia marketkan produk dia 
tadi?
Translated Text:
With the RM2,000 he started his burger production from home. When he first started, he could only produce 100-200 burgers a day.

After making the burger meat, it must be sold. So how does he market his product
earlier?

Text:
Masuk pasaraya besar? Nope.

Jual rumah ke rumah? Nope.

Dia jual semacam mana yang kita tengok Burger Ramly dijual sekarang. 

Dekat tepi jalan.
Translated Text:
Enter the supermarket? Nope.

Selling house to house? Nope.

He sells the kind we see Ramly Burger selling now.

Near the roadside.

Text:
So dia pacak khemah, letak banner dan mula berniaga burger yang ready to eat. Awal-awal orang belum kenal kan, jadi dia marketkan produk dia dengan cara tu.

Tapi burger waktu tu belum biasa dengan lidah orang Melayu. 

So apa dia buat?
Translated Text:
So he set up a tent, put up a banner and started selling ready-to-eat burgers. In the beginning, people didn't know it yet, so he marketed his product that way.

But burgers at that time were not familiar to Malays.

So what did he do?

Text:
So Ramly alter sikit resipi burger jalanan ni ikut tekak melayu. Letak sos lebih sikit, mayonis, rempah-rempah sikit bagi naik rasa. 

Terus meletup! Hehe

Macam mana dia boleh start bisnes dia dengan cara tu?
 
Sebab dia kenal siapa audience dia.
Translated Text:
So Ramly slightly alters this street burger recipe to suit the Malay palate. Put a little more sauce, mayonnaise, spices to increase the taste.

Keep exploding! Hehe

How can he start his business that way?
 
Because he knows who his audience is.

Text:
Sebab tu penting untuk orang bisnes betul-betul kenal dan faham audience yang kita target. Baru kita dapat customize produk untuk solve masalah yang diorang hadapi.

So tak lama lepas tu, burger Ramly mula terjual 3000 keping setiap hari.

3000 keping wehh.
Translated Text:
That's why it's important for business people to really know and understand our target audience. Only then can we customize products to solve the problems that people face.

So not long after that, Ramly burgers started selling 3000 pieces every day.

3000 pieces.

Text:
So macam mana Ramly berjaya kembangkan bisnes dia daripada 100 keping sampai 3000 keping  and now 1,000,000+ keping setiap hari?

Dia gunakan konsep ejen dan stokis.

Ramly cuma fokus kepada production, dan orang lain yang marketkan produk-produk dia.

Siapa agen dia?
Translated Text:
So how did Ramly manage to grow his business from 100 pieces to 3000 pieces and now 1,000,000+ pieces every day?

He uses the concept of agents and stockists.

Ramly only focuses on production, and other people who market his products.

Who is his agent?

Text:
Tu yang pacak gerai-gerai burger tepi jalan dengan tulisan Ramly besar-besar tu. Itulah agen yang menyebarkan produk dia ke seluruh Malaysia.

Kalau kita refer pada statistik, Ramly ni ada lebih kurang 30,000 micro-entrepreneurs dibawah jenama dia.
Translated Text:
That's where the roadside burger stalls with big Ramly inscriptions are located. That's the agent who spreads his products all over Malaysia.

If we refer to statistics, Ramly has approximately 30,000 micro-entrepreneurs under his brand.

Text:
Macam mana boleh achieve number of agent seramai ni?

1. Easy.
2. Less cost.
3. Everyone can do it.
Translated Text:
Macam mana boleh achieve number of agent seramai ni?

1. Easy.
2. Less cost.
3. Everyone can do it.

Text:
Nak pacak payung tepi jalan ni tak perlukan proses yang panjang pun. Nak kena apply situ, sini. 

Nak kena plan and everything. Tak perlu pun. Lagi-lagi pacak gerai depan rumah, pap setel.
Translated Text:
If you want to put up an umbrella by the roadside, you don't need a long process. You have to apply there, here.

Want to have a plan and everything. No need. Again, the stall in front of the house, pap set.

Text:
Kos untuk start bisnes pun sangat rendah. Tak perlu beli dapur yang besar, alatan yang susah-susah, chiller and everything. 

Kos bawah 5,000 pun dah boleh start berniaga. Korang pernah tengokkan gerai burger tepi jalan ada apa? 

Cuba estimate kos diorang berapa.
Translated Text:
The cost to start a business is also very low. No need to buy a big kitchen, difficult tools, chiller and everything.

You can start a business with a cost of less than 5,000. Have you ever seen a roadside burger stand?

Try to estimate how much it costs.

Text:
Dan yang paling penting, semua orang boleh buat. 

Siapa yang tak reti flip burger angkat tangan! 

Haa see, mana ada. Haha. 

Even remaja belasan tahun pun boleh start berniaga burger.
Translated Text:
And most importantly, everyone can do it.

Who doesn't want to flip a burger, raise your hand!

Haa see, where is it? Haha.

Even teenagers can start a burger business.

Text:
Jadi dengan menggalakkan lebih ramai orang untuk buat bisnes ni, dalam masa yang sama bisnes dia pun berkembang. 

Flow dia mudah je:

Lagi banyak gerai burger >> Lagi ramai pelanggan kenal Ramly >> Lagi banyak daging burger 
terjual.
Translated Text:
So by encouraging more people to do this business, at the same time his business also grows.

His flow is simple:

More burger stalls >> More customers know Ramly >> More burger meat
sold out.

Text:
That’s how Ramly create demand untuk produk-produk dia.
Lepas tu bila keluar je apa-apa produk, insyaAllah takde masalah untuk dijual lagi. 

30,000 ejen ni memang sentiasa menanti je.

Yang paling penting dalam bisnes ni adalah untuk kita create demand & marketing.
Translated Text:
That's how Ramly creates demand for his products.
After that, if any product comes out, God willing, there will be no problem to sell it again.

These 30,000 agents are always waiting.

The most important thing in this business is for us to create demand & marketing.

Text:
Ada 5 cara, macam mana FoodPanda ni makes money. Saya terangkan briefly dalam thread ni.

1. Registration Fees Charged From The Restaurant‌‌

2. Commission From Restaurant ‌‌

3. Delivery Fee From Customers‌‌

4. Advertisement

5. Affiliate Income‌‌
Translated Text:
Ada 5 cara, macam mana FoodPanda ni makes money. Saya terangkan briefly dalam thread ni.

1. Registration Fees Charged From The Restaurant‌‌

2. Commission From Restaurant ‌‌

3. Delivery Fee From Customers‌‌

4. Advertisement

5. Affiliate Income‌‌

Text:
1. Registration Fees Charged From The Restaurant‌‌

One time fee ni untuk restoran, kafe atau gerai yang baru nak berdaftar dengan FoodPanda.

Ni standard je sebenarnya. The income is one-off.
Translated Text:
1. Registration Fees Charged From The Restaurant‌‌

This one time fee is for restaurants, cafes or outlets that are just about to register with FoodPanda.

It's really standard. The income is one-off.

Text:
2. Commission From Restaurant ‌‌

Dekat sini yang dia makan paling banyak tu. FoodPanda ambil 15-25% daripada harga makanan tu.

Kalau harga mknn tu RM10, RM2.5 dapat ke FoodPanda.

That's why kita selalu nampak yang harga mknn dkt foodpanda ni lagi mahal daripada kdai mkn.
Translated Text:
2. Commission From Restaurant ‌

This is where he eats the most. FoodPanda takes 15-25% of the price of the food.

If the price of the meal is RM10, RM2.5 can go to FoodPanda.

That's why we always see that food prices at foodpanda are more expensive than food shops.

Text:
Especially utk local restaurant. Sebab margin untung diorang dah sedia rendah.

Bayangkan kalau nasi lemak ayam harga RM6 dekat kedai. Yang diorg dapat RM4.50 je, manalah nak cover overhead cost.

So diorang terpaksa tambah harga jadi RM8. Yg diorang dpt still RM6.
Translated Text:
Especially for local restaurants. Because the profit margin is already low.

Imagine if chicken nasi lemak costs RM6 near the store. People only get RM4.50, how do they cover the overhead cost?

So people had to increase the price to RM8. People can still get RM6.

Text:
Tiba2 teringat kisah akak yang after tolak all the fees tu, hasil jualan daripada seribu lebih tinggal 24 sen je.

Aduhai.

Tapi tu maybe isu lain. But foodpanda patut take this matter seriously lah. Kesian kat small business.
Translated Text:
I suddenly remembered my sister's story that after deducting all the fees, the sales revenue from over a thousand was only 24 cents.

Alas.

But that's maybe another issue. But foodpanda should take this matter seriously. Pity the small business.

Text:
3. Delivery Fee From Customers‌‌

Delivery fee ni macam biasa kita tengok.

But most of the chunks untuk rider.
Translated Text:
3. Delivery Fee From Customers

This delivery fee is what we usually see.

But most of the chunks for the rider.

Text:
4. Advertisement

Optional for certain restaurant untuk advertised restoran diorang dekat FoodPanda untuk dapat lebih banyak exposure.

Maybe yang masuk dalam PandaBox promo and certain other promo tu masuk dalam kategori ni.
Translated Text:
4. Advertisements

Optional for certain restaurants to advertise restaurants near FoodPanda to get more exposure.

Maybe those that are included in the PandaBox promo and certain other promos fall into this category.

Text:
5. Affiliate income

Foodpanda pun ada partner up dengan beberapa company untuk promote servis diorang.

Cth macam kad kredit etc. 

But jarang nampak kat foodpanda Malaysia.
Translated Text:
5. Affiliate income

Foodpanda has partnered up with several companies to promote their services.

Eg like credit cards etc.

But rarely seen at foodpanda Malaysia.

Text:
6. Bonus 

Ceh siap ada bonus. Hahaaha

Now FoodPanda ada pandapro.

Subscription package optional untuk yg biasa guna FoodPanda. Those yg opt in akan dapat better delivery rate, few promos etc.
Translated Text:
6. Bonuses

Check ready there is a bonus. hahaha

Now FoodPanda has pandapro.

Optional subscription package for those who normally use FoodPanda. Those who opt in will get better delivery rates, some promotions etc.

Text:
So senanglah Foodpanda buat ratus-ratus juta?

Tidak jugak.

Bak kata orang tua-tua, 

Besar periuk, besarlah keraknya.

Infografik daripada elluminati ni menarik untuk dilihat. https://t.co/GTwkdT62P1
Translated Text:
So is it easy for Foodpanda to make hundreds of millions?

Not really.

As the elders say,

The bigger the pot, the bigger the crust.

This infographic from illuminati is interesting to see. https://t.co/GTwkdT62P1

Text:
Zalora - fesyen
Sephora - kosmetik
Applecrumby - ?

Haa! Kalau tak pernah dengar pasal applecrumby, most likely korang ni masih single. Hahaha.

Applecrumby adalah e-commerce yang fokus kepada barangan bayi.
Translated Text:
Zalora - fashion
Sephora - cosmetics
Applecrumby - ?

Ha! If you have never heard of applecrumby, most likely you are still single. Haha.

Applecrumby is an e-commerce that focuses on baby items.

Text:
Applecrumby ni founded by suami isteri Sean and Jesmine Tan pada tahun 2012. 

Tahun 2011 Sean and Jesmine ni dapat anak yang pertama and they really like tcertain organic brands tapi masalahnya susah nak dapatkan dekat Malaysia.
Translated Text:
Applecrumby was founded by husband and wife Sean and Jesmine Tan in 2012.

In 2011 Sean and Jesmine had their first child and they really like certain organic brands but the problem is it's hard to get it in Malaysia.

Text:
Tahun 2011 - 2012 dulu, kos penghantaran apa semua sangatlah mahalnya. So, diorang beli kebanyakan barang in bulk dan cari buyer yang ada interest yang sama.

Macam sekarang guna pakai konsep personal shopper dekat IG lah kot?

But then, they decided untuk start AppleCrumby.
Translated Text:
In 2011 - 2012, the shipping costs were very expensive. So, people buy most items in bulk and look for buyers who have the same interest.

How do you use the personal shopper concept on IG now?

But then, they decided to start AppleCrumby.

Text:
AppleCrumby ni bukan cikai2.

Tahun 2014, AppleCrumby ni first seed funding round from Teak Capital.

Tahun 2016, diorang raise fund USD 300k daripada 500 Startups.

Interesting kan?
Translated Text:
This AppleCrumby is not a lover.

In 2014, AppleCrumby was the first seed funding round from Teak Capital.

In 2016, people raised USD 300k from 500 startups.

Interesting right?

Text:
To date, AppleCrumby ni ada more than 10,000 products! 

Untuk tawarkan harga yang lagi kompetitif, diorang dapatkan hak eksklusif pengedaran daripada beberapa jenama antarabangsa.

Power kan? Daripada nak beli untuk kegunaan sendiri, dah raise funding more than 1mil!
Translated Text:
To date, AppleCrumby has more than 10,000 products!

To offer more competitive prices, people get exclusive distribution rights from several international brands.

Power right? Instead of buying for my own use, I have raised more than 1mil in funding!

Text:
So guys, there is nothing wrong if you want to focus on one niche. 

Bagi saya, untuk fasa2 awal lagi better start dengan fokus kepada satu niche.

Kenapa?
Translated Text:
So guys, there's nothing wrong if you want to focus on one niche.

For me, for the initial phases, it's better to start by focusing on one niche.

Why?

Text:
Sebabnya lagi mudah dan boleh scale dengan lebih pantas sebenarnya.

Sebenarnya satu niche tu pun tak habis makan weh. Haha. Banyak produk yang kita boleh jual daripada satu niche tu saja.
Translated Text:
The reason is that it is easier and can actually scale faster.

In fact, even one niche is not enough to eat. Haha. There are many products that we can sell from that one niche.

Text:
Strategi stand out ni dah lama company besar pakai, antaranya Apple.

Kenapa ramai sangat iFag? 

Sebab Apple jadikan customer experience tu as something personal.

You can do anything and everything with Apple!
Translated Text:
This stand out strategy has been used by big companies for a long time, including Apple.

Why are there so many iFag?

Because Apple makes the customer experience something personal.

You can do anything and everything with Apple!

Text:
Also, bila pakai Apple, terasa macam uplah sikit. haha. (okay saya tau hp android pun mahal jugak)

Dan pengalaman macam ni menarik perhatian orang.
Translated Text:
Also, when using Apple, it feels like a little uplah. haha. (okay, I know android phones are expensive too)

And this kind of experience attracts people's attention.

Text:
Actually, ada 2 cara untuk stand out daripada pesaing lain.

Apa dia?
Translated Text:
Actually, there are 2 ways to stand out from other competitors.

What is it?

Text:
First, lead from the bottom.

Biasa kita tengok, satu2 decision tu dibuat based on pendapat CEO je kan?

Kali ini, kita terbalikkan dan jadikan setiap decision tu dibuat based on customer kita.

Kenapa?
Translated Text:
First, lead from the bottom.

We usually see that decisions are made based on the opinion of the CEO, right?

This time, we turned it upside down and made every decision based on our customer.

Why?

Text:
Bila customer berada di atas, kita akan menjadikan customer as everything!

So customer yg akan jadi main factor untuk sebarang keputusan dan perubahan.

Bukan bermakna CEO tu tak penting.
Translated Text:
When the customer is on top, we will make the customer as everything!

So the customer will be the main factor for any decisions and changes.

It does not mean that the CEO is not important.

Text:
Tapi kena ingat, bisnes kita hanya akan bertahan kalau ada customer.

Kalau customer lari, siapa yang nak support bisnes kita?
Translated Text:
But remember, our business will only survive if there are customers.

If the customer runs away, who wants to support our business?

Text:
Second, connect with your customer.

Customer experience itu penting!

Sebab itulah, tak salah untuk fokuskan dkt bahagian customer service (especially after sales service).
Translated Text:
Second, connect with your customer.

Customer experience is important!

For this reason, it's not wrong to focus on customer service (especially after sales service).

Text:
Bila customer service bagus, customer akan happy.

Tapi kalau tak bagus?

Customer akan rasa marah dan tertipu.
Bayar mahal-mahal, tapi dapat apa?
Translated Text:
If the customer service is good, the customer will be happy.

But what if it's not good?

Customers will feel angry and deceived.
Pay a lot, but get what?

Text:
Sebab tu, customer experience ni kita wajib utamakan kalau nak kekal bersaing dengan musuh2 kita.

Tak kisah jual apapun, sentiasa utamakan service dan experience terbaik utk customer.
Translated Text:
That's why we must prioritize customer experience if we want to stay competitive with our enemies.

No matter what you sell, always prioritize the best service and experience for the customer.

Text:
Banyak business berjaya sebab diorang dapat kekalkan customer.

Kenapa customer kekal?

Sebab customer experience diorang power. Hehe.
Translated Text:
Many businesses are successful because people can keep customers.

Why do customers stay?

Because customer experience is the power. Hehe.

Text:
Kesimpulan thread ni mudah je sebenarnya, kalau nak bisnes maju dan power, sentiasa utamakan customer okay! Haha

Text: @FezzaHussin @threadreaderapp unroll
Translated Text: @FezzaHussin @threadreaderapp unroll

Text:
1. Guna Video

Kalau dulu update di IG atau FB Story je, sekarang semua orang dah mula nak guna TikTok!

Nampak tak persamaan kedua-duanya?

Ya, dua-dua menggunakan format video!

So, rugilah kalau kita tak tap into video marketing ni.
Translated Text:
1. Use Video

If you used to only update on IG or FB Story, now everyone wants to use TikTok!

Can't you see the similarity between the two?

Yes, both use video format!

So, it will be a loss if we don't tap into this video marketing.

Text:
87% marketer bgtahu yang video dapat tarik lebih banyak trafik ke website mereka.

84% pelanggan pulak bgtahu yang diorang lebih tertarik nak membeli lepas tengok video.

Powerful kan impact video dalam marketing ni?
Translated Text:
87% of marketers say that video can drive more traffic to their website.

84% of customers said that people are more interested in buying after watching a video.

Is the impact of video powerful in marketing?

Text:
2. Collect database

Ramai sangat usahawan langsung tak simpan data pelanggan! Mostly yang niaga kecil-kecilan atau part-time lah.

Rugi weh, rugi besar!

Data ni sebenarnya menyimpan jawapan dan kunci untuk bisnes kita berkembang.
Translated Text:
2. Collect database

Many entrepreneurs do not save customer data! Mostly small business or part-time.

Loss, big loss!

This data actually holds the answers and keys for our business to grow.

Text:
Contohnya, kita akan tahu siapa pelanggan kita, apa mereka suka beli dan kenapa mereka membeli.

Daripada data tu juga, korang boleh buat keputusan, perbelanjaan dan juga pengiklanan perniagaan.
Translated Text:
For example, we will know who our customers are, what they like to buy and why they buy.

From that data too, you can make decisions, expenses and even business advertising.

Text:
Also,kalau korang ada produk baru, bolehlah guna data sedia ada untuk lihat sama ada produk itu akan berjaya atau tidak.

Kalau sebelum ini korang tak pernah simpan data, tolong mulakan sekarang.

Go!
Translated Text:
Also, if you have a new product, you can use existing data to see if the product will be successful or not.

If you have never saved data before, please start now.

Go!

Text:
3. Mobile friendly website

Semua orang ada 1 handphone paling kurang.

Tak salah nak cakap, yang handphone dah jadi satu keperluan pun.

Korang tahu tak, lebih 70% trafik sekarang ni datang daripada handphone atau peranti mudah alih?
Translated Text:
3. Mobile friendly website

Everyone has at least 1 mobile phone.

It's not wrong to say that mobile phones have become a necessity.

Did you know that more than 70% of traffic now comes from mobile phones or devices?

Text:
7 daripada 10 tau!

Bayangkanlah kalau website korang gempak kat komputer.

Tapi bila buka dekat phone, aduh, tak mesra pelanggan langsung!

Alamatnya, terbantutlah hajat pelanggan nak shopping nanti.

So, pastikan website korang WAJIB mobile friendly.
Translated Text:
7 out of 10 you know!

Imagine if your website looks great on a computer.

But when you open it near the phone, ouch, it's not customer friendly at all!

The address is, the customer's desire to shop later is stunted.

So, make sure your website MUST be mobile friendly.

Text:
4. Always listen to customer

Customer is always right (well it’s right tapi kadang2 tak betul. Haha).

Itulah falsafah yang diagungkan oleh ramai marketer kat luar.

Kenapa?

Sebab yang membeli dan guna produk kita adalah pelanggan.
Translated Text:
4. Always listen to customers

Customer is always right (well it's right but sometimes it's not right. Haha).

That is the philosophy glorified by many marketers out there.

Why?

The reason that buys and uses our products is the customer.

Text:
Jadi, turunkan ego sebagai peniaga dan dengar feedback pelanggan korang.

Boleh juga minta pelanggan untuk beri feedback di Facebook, emel, media sosial dan survey.
Translated Text:
So, lower your ego as a trader and listen to your customer's feedback.

You can also ask customers to give feedback on Facebook, email, social media and surveys.

Text:
Daripada feedback yang diterima, boleh tambahbaik perkhidmatan dan produk yang ada.

Lagipun, bila kita tunjukkan yang kita willing to improve, sekaligus menaikkan kepercayaan pelanggan kepada kita.

Cubalah!
Translated Text:
From the feedback received, it is possible to improve the existing services and products.

After all, when we show that we are willing to improve, at the same time increase the customer's trust in us.

Try it!

Text:
5. Manfaatkan testimoni pelanggan

Perasan tak, sekarang ni banyak bisnes yang repost atau reshare balik testimoni pelanggan diorang?

Takpun, paling biasa dibuat adalah share screenshot mesej dengan pelanggan.

Well, itu biasa.
Translated Text:
5. Take advantage of customer testimonials

Have you noticed that now many businesses repost or reshare customer testimonials?

Anyway, the most common thing to do is to share a screenshot of the message with the customer.

Well, that's normal.

Text:
Apa kata korang cuba teknik lain pula.

Boleh minta budi baik pelanggan untuk buat satu video testimoni bila mereka guna produk korang.

Dari situ, korang gabungkanlah beberapa video menjadi satu.
Translated Text:
Why don't you try another technique?

Can you kindly ask customers to make a testimonial video when they use your product.

From there, you combine several videos into one.

Text:
Macam mana nak minta pelanggan buat video? Kemon, bagilah something kat diorang. Gift ke, diskaun for next purchase ke.

Prospek pelanggan akan lebih tertarik dengan testimoni pelanggan sedia ada. Lagi2 yg genuine mcm ni.
Translated Text:
How to ask a customer to make a video? Kemon, give something to people. Gift to, discount for next purchase to.

Prospective customers will be more interested in existing customer testimonials. More genuine ones like this.

Text:
That's all. Sebenarnya takdelah hacks sangat pun, tapi saya percaya 5 benda ni memang sangat impactful pada bisnes kita.

Suka thread macam ni? Jangan lupa follow @FezzaHussin eh. Saya akan update thread related dengan bisnes & marketing selalu kat sini. Hehe
Translated Text:
That's all. Actually there aren't any hacks, but I believe these 5 things are indeed very impactful on our business.

Like threads like this? Don't forget to follow @FezzaHussin eh. I will update threads related to business & marketing is always here. Haha

Text:
Mati ni sebenarnya motivasi paling besar untuk terus hidup. Ironi kan? Dua perkataan yang berlawanan maksud diletakkan dalam satu ayat. Hidup - mati.

Jom cerita sikit pasal motivasi mati.
Translated Text:
Death is actually the biggest motivation to continue living. Ironic right? Two words with opposite meanings are placed in one sentence. Life - death.

Let's talk a little about the motivation to die.

Text:
1. Mati membuatkan kita kurang rasa takut untuk hadapi kehidupan.

Like seriously, as long as masalah tu bukanlah mati, kita sentiasa boleh start balik semula.

Bisnes kita tak jadi? Then kita boleh start semula.
Investment kita rugi? Then kita boleh cari duit lagi.
Translated Text:
1. Dying makes us less afraid to face life.

Like seriously, as long as the problem is not dead, we can always start again.

Is our business not working? Then we can start again.
Is our investment a loss? Then we can find more money.

Text:
Jadi kita dapat hidup tanpa perasaan takut melampau dengan apa yang akan jadi.

Of course lah perasaan takut tu kita tak mampu nak buang semua. Kita ni manusia biasa je kot. Haha

But, dengan yakin pada kematian yg boleh datang bila2, kita akan rasa lagi hidup sebenarnya.
Translated Text:
So we can live without extreme fear of what will happen.

Of course, the feeling of fear is that we cannot afford to throw it all away. We are just ordinary people. Haha

But, with confidence in death that can come at any time, we will feel alive again.

Text:
2. Mati menghidupkan sense of urgency

Mati ni bukan pengakhiran bagi kita. Just a milestone for us.

Lepas mati atas dunia ni, ada banyak lagi checkpoint yang kita kena lalui. Alam kubur, alam barzakh, hari penghisaban, titian sirat...fuh panjang lagi.
Translated Text:
2. Dying activates a sense of urgency

Death is not the end for us. Just a milestone for us.

After dying in this world, there are many more checkpoints that we have to go through. The realm of the grave, the realm of barzakh, the day of reckoning, titian sirat... phew it's too long.

Text:
Dan kita sendiri pun tahu, tujuan kita hidup ni banyalah untuk beribadah kepada Dia. Tuhan yang Maha Esa. Allah.

Hidup ni cumalah ujian untuk kita.

So setiap ujian, mestilah ada waktu tamatnya.

Bila waktu tamat kita? Bila kita mati.

Bila kita mati? Itu yang kita tak pasti.
Translated Text:
And we ourselves know that the purpose of our lives is to worship Him. Almighty God. God.

Life is just a test for us.

So every test must have an end time.

When is our time up? When we die

When do we die? That we are not sure.

Text:
Sebab kan kita tak pasti tu lah, sense of urgency itu wujud.

Nak berubah jadi baik? Buat sekarang.
Nak sedekah lagi banyak? Buat sekarang.
Nak tukar kerja yg lagi baik? Buat sekarang.

Sebab kita harap, penutup kehidupan kita ni adalah penutup yang terbaik.
Translated Text:
Because we are not sure, the sense of urgency exists.

Want to change for the better? Do it now.
Do you want to donate more? Do it now.
Want to change a better job? Do it now.

Because we hope, the end of our life is the best end.

Text:
3. Mati menghidupkan kasih sayang

النعمة إذا فُقِدت عرفت

Korang pernah dengar ayat ni?

Bila nikmat tu dah hilang, barulah kita nak hargai.
Translated Text:
3. Dying gives life to love

النعمة ادي فُقِدت عرفت

Have you ever heard this verse?

When the favor is gone, then we want to appreciate it.

Text:
Apa nikmat dalam hidup kita ni?

Ibu ayah. 
Adik beradik.
Kawan-kawan.

Basically, orang yang kita paling sayang adalah nikmat yang paling besar dalam kehidupan kita.

Tapi tentulah jarang kita nak ingat benda ni. Bila kita nak ingat? Bila mereka dah takde nanti.
Translated Text:
What is the blessing in our life?

Mother father.
Siblings.
Friends.

Basically, the person we love the most is the greatest blessing in our lives.

But of course we rarely want to remember this thing. When do we want to remember? When they are gone later.

Text:
Sebab tu, bila kita selalu ingat mati, kita tak mampu nak marah atau gaduh lama2 dengan org yg kita sayang.

Sebesar mana pun salah yang diorang buat, pasti dan pasti kita mampu untuk maafkan bila kita teringatkan kematian.

Kan?
Translated Text:
That's why, when we always remember death, we can't afford to be angry or fight for a long time with the people we love.

No matter how big a mistake people make, surely and definitely we are able to forgive when we are reminded of death.

Right?

Text:
Satu hari nanti, kita pasti akan mati. Tua mati; muda pun mati. Sakit mati; sihat pun mati.

So apa kita nk buat sementara masih hidup atas dunia ni?

Buatlah kebaikan sebanyak-banyaknya buat bekalan disana nanti. Dan sementara masih hidup, bolehlah follow @FezzaHussin okay. Haha
Translated Text:
One day, we will surely die. Old and dead; die young Death pain; even healthy dies.

So what do we want to do while still living in this world?

Do as much good as possible to supply there later. And while still alive, you can follow @FezzaHussin okay. Haha

Text:
1. Burger King

Tahun 2019 dulu, Burger King pernah cipta satu misteri yang menjadi tanda tanya ramai orang kat Twitter.

Burger King like tweet influencer2 antaranya Casey Neistat, Nadeshot, Brant Daugherty dan beberapa orang lain yg diorang tweet tahun 2010 dulu.
Translated Text:
1. Burger King

In 2019, Burger King once created a mystery that became a question mark for many people on Twitter.

Burger King likes tweets from influencers, including Casey Neistat, Nadeshot, Brant Daugherty and several others who were tweeted in 2010.

Text:
So diorang ni pun pelik. Dah kenapa akaun Burger King stalk sampai tweet tahun 2010 kan?

Influencer2 ni mula raise their concern and cuba untuk solve misteri tu. Antara yang tweet, Casey Neistat. 

"why is Burger King liking my 8 year old tweets?"

https://t.co/uOzYhYNBdD
Translated Text:
So this person is also strange. Why did the Burger King account stalk until it tweeted in 2010, right?

These influencers started raising their concern and trying to solve the mystery. Among those who tweeted, Casey Neistat.

"why is Burger King liking my 8 year old's tweets?"

https://t.co/uOzYhYNBdD

Text:
Bukan dia sorang je, 3,4 orang lagi tweet benda yang sama. Last-last, Burger King reveal kenapa diorang like tweet tahun 2010.

"some things from 2010 are worth revisiting—like your old tweets. and funnel cake fries. get them now for a limited time."

https://t.co/u2OlQAqSjS
Translated Text:
Bukan dia sorang je, 3,4 orang lagi tweet benda yang sama. Last-last, Burger King reveal kenapa diorang like tweet tahun 2010.

"some things from 2010 are worth revisiting—like your old tweets. and funnel cake fries. get them now for a limited time."

https://t.co/u2OlQAqSjS

Text:
Tapi dapat kecaman lah jugak trick ni, sampai Casey Neistat buat video kata Burger King exploit dia. And dia suruh sebahagian daripada sales tu disumbangkan pada charity org.

Dan Burger King setuju dengan idea tu.
Translated Text:
But this trick was also criticized, until Casey Neistat made a video saying that Burger King exploited him. And he told a part of the sales to be donated to charity.

And Burger King agrees with that idea.

Text:
2. Warner Brothers

Marketing trick ni dibuat untuk filem Detective Pikachu dulu.

3 hari sebelum tayangan filem ni, ada satu akaun yang tweet link youtube untuk filem ni versi cetak rompak.
Translated Text:
2. Warner Brothers

This marketing trick was made for the first Detective Pikachu movie.

3 days before the release of this movie, there was an account that tweeted a youtube link for the pirated version of this movie.

Text: Untuk nampakkan lagi real, pelakon dia sendiri quote rt tweet yang ada link tu. https://t.co/Qp95wqkZzQ
Translated Text: To make it look more real, the actor himself quoted rt the tweet with the link. https://t.co/Qp95wqkZzQ

Text:
Well, of course link tu takdelah full movie Detective Pikachu tu, cuma opening je. Haha

Yang lain video pikachu berjoget je sejam lebih.

Setakat hari ni, video tu dah ditonton 34 Juta tau.
Translated Text:
Well, of course the link isn't the full Detective Pikachu movie, it's just the opening. Ha ha

The others are videos of pikachu dancing for over an hour.

So far today, the video has been watched 34 million years.

Text:
3. Wendy's

Yang ni saya fikir ramai yang dah tahu. Sebab banyak juga online bisnes dekat Malaysia yang buat strategi yang sama.

Tahun 2017 dulu, ada satu twitter user yang buat lawak mintak 1 tahun supply untuk nugget Wendy's ni.

So apa Wendy's reply?
Translated Text:
3. Wendy's

I think many people already know this. Because there are also many online businesses near Malaysia that do the same strategy.

In 2017, there was a twitter user who joked about asking for 1 year supply for Wendy's nuggets.

So what's Wendy's reply?

Text:
18,000,0000 RT.

Haha. Maksudnya kalau mamat ni dapat 18 juta RT dekat tweet dia, then Wendy's akan supply FREE nugget for 1 whole year untuk mamat ni. 

Masa tu memang jadi kegilaan juga. Banyak company yang tiru strategi sama. https://t.co/O5Kn8Bt1TL
Translated Text:
18,000,0000 RT.

Haha. This means that if this mamat gets 18 million RTs near her tweet, then Wendy's will supply FREE nuggets for 1 whole year for this mamat.

That time was really crazy too. Many companies imitate the same strategy. https://t.co/O5Kn8Bt1TL

Text:
Saya rasa sampai ke hari ni pun, strategy Wendy's ni masih digunakan oleh online bisnes dekat Malaysia & luar negara.

Which is good.

Low cost, high impact!
Translated Text:
I think even today, this Wendy's strategy is still being used by online businesses in Malaysia & abroad.

Which is good.

Low cost, high impact!

Text:
Itulah 3 trick daripada company2 besar yang kita boleh belajar ni. Of course, diorang hire marketing agency atau ada team yang power dibelakang mereka, but kita boleh replicate idea yang sama untuk guna dekat bisnes kita jugak.

Awak pun power jugak sebenarnya. Hehe
Translated Text:
Those are 3 tricks from big companies that we can learn. Of course, people hire marketing agencies or have a powerful team behind them, but we can replicate the same idea to use in our business.

You are also really powerful. Hehe

Text:

Hopefully, tweet2 saya memberi manfaat. Kalau suka, bolehlah follow akaun saya ni @FezzaHussin. Lg ramai follower, lg smgt nk update thread. Haha

Hopefully, my tweets are useful. If you like it, you can follow my account @FezzaHussin. I have a lot of followers, I want to update the thread right away. Haha

Text:

Kalau korang berminat, bolehlah saya buat satu thread panjang sikit esok lusa.

Actually there are many interesting things that he shares in this Shoe Dog book. Articles of business, marketing & branding & about life

If you are interested, I can make a long thread the day after tomorrow.

So are you interested? If interested, follow this @FezzaHussin. Haha

Text:
1. Beli buku

Inilah masanya untuk dapatkan buku free weh. Hehe

For me, buku is one of the greatest investment yang ada atas dunia ni.

Kalau korang pernah baca pasal investment, mesti korang familiar dengan compounding effect bila kita invest dalam something kan.
Translated Text:
1. Buy a book

This is the time to get free books. Hehe

For me, books are one of the greatest investments in the world.

If you have ever read about investment, you must be familiar with the compounding effect when we invest in something, right?

Text:
Compounding effect bila kita invest dekat buku ni memang something else.

Serius tak tipu.

Kalau korang minat pasal bisnes, belilah buku berkaitan bisnes. Kalau minat melabur, bila buku pelaburan. Kalau minat bercucuk tanam, beli buku pertanian.
Translated Text:
The compounding effect when we invest in this book is indeed something else.

Seriously don't cheat.

If you are interested in business, buy a book related to business. If interested in investing, when the investment book. If you are interested in farming, buy an agricultural book.

Text:
Tak semestinya korang kena beli buku yng related dengan apa yang korang study.

Selama ni takde bajet kan nak beli buku yang kita suka, ni dah ada RM150, belilah buku yang kita suka.
Translated Text:
You don't necessarily have to buy books related to what you study.

As long as we don't have the budget to buy the books we like, here we have RM150, buy the books we like.

Text:
2) Join online course

Ada yang redeem e-Belia thru bigpay? Kalau ada baguslah. Sebab korang boleh guna duit tu untuk join online course.

Kalau buku, korang tak rasa feel belajar tu, maybe korang boleh join online course.
Translated Text:
2) Join online course

Has anyone redeemed e-Belia thru bigpay? If there is, it's good. Because you can use that money to join an online course.

If it's a book, you don't feel like learning, maybe you can join an online course.

Text:
“Buat apa online course, youtube kan ada.”

Betul juga. Tapi tentulah tak sama.

Online course ni biasanya lebih structured, ada assesment, ada ruang untuk discussion and well bila kita bayar for something, kita akan jadi lebih komited & disiplin untuk belajar.
Translated Text:
"Why do online courses, there's YouTube."

That's right. But of course not the same.

These online courses are usually more structured, there are assessments, there is room for discussion and well if we pay for something, we will become more committed & discipline to study.

Text:
Ada kawan saya ambil online course ni, dari taktahu cakap thai, terus boleh sembang thai.

Ada jugak yang amek course pasal big data & data science. Ilmu tu dia guna utk research master dia.

Berbaloi kan! Hehe
Translated Text:
I have a friend who took this online course, from not knowing how to speak Thai, to being able to chat in Thai.

There are also those who take a course on big data & data science. He uses that knowledge for his master's research.

It's worth it! Hehe

Text:
3. Beli something untuk parents

Saya ingat kawan saya pernah cerita waktu dia buat program dekat Indonesia dulu.

Dia bawak adik2 sekolah rendah pergi shopping barang2 kemahuan diorang. Peruntukannya lebih kurang Rp250K/orang. Lebih kurang RM70 macam tu.
Translated Text:
3. Buy something for parents

I remember my friend once told me when he did a program near Indonesia.

He took the elementary school sisters to go shopping for the things they wanted. The allocation is approximately Rp250K/person. About RM70 like that.

Text:
Ada seorang adik ni, dia ambil sikit je barang2 yg dia nak. Pastu dia tarik tangan volunteer yang jaga dia.

Dia cakap dekat volunteer tu,

Kak, bisa gak aku belikan susu buat adikku & roti buat mamakku di rumah?
Translated Text:
There is this sister, she just takes a little of the things she wants. Then he pulled the hand of the volunteer who was looking after him.

He said to the volunteer,

Sis, can I buy milk for my sister & bread for my mom at home?

Text:
Cuba bayangkan, dengan nilai sekecil itu pun dia masih teringat pada mak, adik & basically keluarga dia kat rumah.

Jadinya, saya fikir ada eloknya juga kalau sebahagian daripada wang tu digunakan untuk buat mak kita tersenyum gembira.
Translated Text:
Try to imagine, even with such a small value, he still remembers his mother, sister & basically his family at home.

So, I think it would be good if part of the money was used to make our mother smile happily.

Text:
Idk mak awak suka apa. Tapi sebenarnya, apa-apa pun mak kita suka je kalau kita belikan untuk dia.

Sebab bukan mahal atau murah yang menjadi ukuran. Tapi pemberian tu adalah tanda ingatan kita pada dia yang dah banyak berjasa kat kita. Hehe
Translated Text:
I don't know what your mom likes. But actually, no matter what we buy for her, our mother likes it.

Because it is not expensive or cheap that is the measure. But the gift is a sign of our memory of him who has served us a lot. Hehe

Text:
Anyway, this thread sepatutnya happy2 je. Kenapa hujung2 macam nak sedih pulak. Haha

So itulah, kalau korang nak tips pasal bisnes & marketing, korang boleh follow akaun @FezzaHussin ni and DM/reply korang nak tahu pasal apa. 

Saya akan allocate masa saya utk jwb. Hehe
Translated Text:
Anyway, this thread should be happy. Why are the ends so sad? Haha

So that's it, if you want tips about business & marketing, you can follow this @FezzaHussin account and DM/reply what you want to know about.

I will allocate my time for jwb. Hehe

Text:
1. Manfaatkan IG Story

Banyak bisnes yang tak manfaatkan IGS ni dengan sempurna. Padehal, IGS ni sangat berkesan. And tbh, saya boleh katakan lagi berkesan dan dapat reach lebih ramai audience daripada post gambar dekat feed.

Sayang betul kalau kita tak manfaatkan betul2.
Translated Text:
1. Take advantage of IG Story

Many businesses do not take full advantage of IGS. In fact, this IGS is very effective. And tbh, I can say it's more effective and can reach more audiences than posting pictures near the feed.

It's a pity if we don't take advantage of it.

Text:
Bila buat IGS tu, cuba hasilkan benda yang kreatif. Sekarang ni banyak apps yang boleh guna untuk edit & dapatkan hasil terbaik.

Antara yang korang boleh guna: canva, crello, creatopy.

Tapi tak perlu sempurna. Jalan terus & keep improving along the way.
Translated Text:
When doing IGS, try to produce something creative. Now there are many apps that can be used to edit & get the best results.

Among the ones you can use: canva, crello, creatopy.

But it doesn't have to be perfect. Straight road & keep improving along the way.

Text:
2. Sentiasa monitor ruangan komen

First and foremost, kita & bisnes kita ni tak femes. Jadi janganlah kekwat sangat nak balas komen tu. Hahaha.

But seriously, banyak bisnes yang saya tengok tak jaga bahagian komen ni. Ada orang komen, tak direplynya.
Translated Text:
2. Always monitor the comment section

First and foremost, we & Our business is not feminine. So don't be too strong to reply to that comment. Haha.

But seriously, many businesses I see don't take care of this comment section. Some people commented, they didn't reply.

Text:
Bila ada orang interact dengan konten kita, appreciate effort diorang dengan like & reply comment tu.

Selain menaikkan engagement rate, audience pun akan rasa lagi 'rapat' dengan kita. Itu yang penting.
Translated Text:
If there are people who interact with our content, appreciate everyone's efforts with likes & reply to that comment.

In addition to increasing the engagement rate, the audience will also feel more 'close' to us. That's what matters.

Text:
3. Manfaatkan hashtag sebaik mungkin

IG tak macam Facebook atau Twitter.

Kalau dekat FB/Twitter ni, kita search je satu keyword tu, tweet yang ada keyword tu akan appear. Tak sama macam IG.
Translated Text:
3. Make the most of hashtags

IG is not like Facebook or Twitter.

If we're near FB/Twitter, we just search for that one keyword, the tweet that has that keyword will appear. Not the same as IG.

Text:
Dekat IG kita kena pakai hashtag. Max kita boleh guna sampai 30 hashtag.

Tapi janganlah korang pergi spam hashtag tu pulak. Hahha. Sampai hashtag yang takde kena mengena pun korang bedal sama.

Itu merepek ya.
Translated Text:
We have to use hashtags on IG. Max we can use up to 30 hashtags.

But don't spam the hashtag. Hahaha. Even hashtags that don't have to do with each other are the same.

That sucks.

Text:
Guna hashtag yang berkaitan dengan apa yang kita post dan lagi baik kalau kita dapat gunakan hashtag yang tengah trending atau banyak digunakan.

Ada satu case study, post yang guna 30 hashtag, dapat 3 kali ganda like daripada post yang guna 10 hashtag ke bawah. https://t.co/VUpb1HyFd3
Translated Text:
Use hashtags related to what we post and even better if we can use hashtags that are trending or widely used.

There is a case study, a post that uses 30 hashtags, gets 3 times as many likes as a post that uses 10 hashtags or less. https://t.co/VUpb1HyFd3

Text:
4. Konten video

Content video ni dah berapa ramai orang bagitahu dah untuk perbanyakkan. 

Sebab banyak apps yang tengah fokus untuk naikkan konten dalam bentuk video ni.
Translated Text:
4. Video content

The content of this video has been told by many people to increase it.

Because many apps are focusing on uploading content in the form of videos.

Text:
Saya tahu, tak semua orang mampu buat video yang gempak2. Tapi ingatlah, sesungguhnya kita tak perlu gempak untuk bermula. Hahaha.

Mula je dulu. Macam saya cakap tadi. Take your first step & improve along the way.
Translated Text:
I know, not everyone can make great videos. But remember, we don't really need to be tall to start. Haha.

Let's start first. Like I said earlier. Take your first step & improve along the way.

Text:
Bila bisnes dah mula stable, ada untung yang boleh dirolling, hirelah staf untuk jaga konten dekat IG tu.

Tak cukup bajet nak hire staf? Saya cadangkan korang outsource je dekat company yang boleh manage akaun instagram bisnes korang.
Translated Text:
When the business is stable, there is a profit that can be rolled over, hire staff to take care of the content on IG.

Not enough budget to hire staff? I suggest you outsource to a company that can manage your business's Instagram account.

Text:
Personally, saya recommend korang untuk gunakan servis daripada Rise & Win. So korang tak perlulah nak hire videographer, editor, copywriter etc.

Diorang ada team yg lengkap dah & boleh produce content yg mantap untuk ig korang.

Ni IG diorang: https://t.co/NQFfVANtkO
Translated Text:
Personally, I recommend you to use the service from Rise & Wine. So you don't need to hire a videographer, editor, copywriter, etc.

People already have a complete team & can produce strong content for your ig.

This person's IG: https://t.co/NQFfVANtkO
