Text:
Dekat Sheikh Jarrah sekarang ni, israel tengah halau keluar rakyat Palestin yang tinggal dekat situ.

Halau keluar dari rumah diorang sendiri tau. Gila betul.
Translated Text:
Near Sheikh Jarrah right now, Israel is driving out the Palestinians who live there.

Get out of your own house, you know. Really crazy.

Text:
Lepas owner asal kena halau, dia masukkan orang israel dalam rumah tu. Kira rumah yg milik orang Palestin tu berubah hak milik jadi orang israel punya. 

Tak boleh nak brain weh situasi ni?

Orang dtg rumah kita, halau kita, pastu rumah tu tiba2 jadi milik dia.
Translated Text:
After the original owner was evicted, he let Israelis into the house. Suppose the house that belonged to the Palestinians changed its ownership to that of the Israelis.

Can't you brainstorm this situation?

People come to our house, drive us away, then the house suddenly becomes his.

Text:
Sebab benda merepek ni, rakyat Palestin buat demonstrasi membantah tindakan israel ni. 

Mariam Afifi ni salah seorang yang terlibat dengan demonstrasi tu. Mariam ni musician dekat Jerusalem.

Disebabkan dia lantang ketika berdemonstrasi, tentera israel rentap, seret & pukul dia!
Translated Text:
Because of this mess, the Palestinians demonstrated against this Israeli action.

Mariam Afifi is one of the people involved in the demonstration. Mariam is a musician near Jerusalem.

Because he was loud when demonstrating, the Israeli army beat, dragged & beat him!

Text:
Dia ditangkap, digari dan dipukul. 

Sebab apa?

Sebab mempertahankan mereka² yang lemah ni. 

Lihat situasi & keadaan ni membuatkan saya malu. Kadang rasa apa yg saya buat dah cukup untuk membela mereka.
Translated Text:
He was arrested, handcuffed and beaten.

Why?

Because of defending those who are weak.

See the situation & This situation makes me ashamed. Sometimes I think what I do is enough to defend them.

Text:
Tapi apalah sangat usaha kita ni nak dibandingkan dengan pengorbanan dan susah payah saudara² kita yg berjuang dekat sana. 

Setiap lelaki, perempuan, tua, muda bahkan kanak2 pun mempertaruhkan nyawa mereka untuk mempertahankan masjid al-Aqsa yg menjadi kiblat pertama kita.
Translated Text:
But how much is our effort compared to the sacrifices and hard work of our brothers who are fighting there.

Every man, woman, old, young and even children risked their lives to defend al-Aqsa mosque which is our first Qibla.

Text:
Jadi guys, kita nak kena bantu our brother n sister kat sana!

The least we can do adalah mendoakan mereka. 

Kalau kita ada rezeki lebih, sebahagian rezeki kongsikanlah untuk bantu mereka.
Translated Text:
So guys, we have to help our brothers and sisters there!

The least we can do is pray for them.

If we have more sustenance, share some sustenance to help them.

Text:
Saidina Abdul Rahman bin 'Auf r.anh masuk islam hasil dakwah Saidina Abu Bakar r.anh. 

Korang tahu, dalam 10 sahabat yang dijanjikan syurga oleh Allah swt, 5 daripadanya masuk Islam asbab dakwah Saidina Abu Bakar r.anh. 

Masya-Allah.
Translated Text:
Saidina Abdul Rahman bin 'Auf r.anh converted to Islam as a result of the preaching of Saidina Abu Bakar r.anh.

You know, in the 10 companions who were promised heaven by Allah swt, 5 of them converted to Islam because of the preaching of Saidina Abu Bakar r.anh.

Masha-Allah.

Text:
Dalam peristiwa hijrah, setiap muhajirin (mereka yang berhijrah) akan dipasangkan dengan ansar (penduduk Madinah). 

Betapa bijaknya baginda Nabi ﷺ, beliau pasangkan setiap orang tu berdasarkan orang yang berkongsi minat, mindset atau interest yang sama.
Translated Text:
In the event of hijrah, every muhajirin (those who migrated) will be paired with ansar (residents of Madinah).

How wise was the Prophet ﷺ, he paired each person based on people who share the same interest, mindset or interest.

Text:
Disebabkan Saidina Abdul Rahman merupakan seorang businessman maka beliau dipairkan dengan Saidina Sa'ad Ibn Rabi'. 

Saidina Sa'ad ni pun terkenal antara businessman yang berjaya di Madinah. Hartanya, kekayaannya serta minatnya memang sama level dengan Saidina Abdul Rahman r.anh
Translated Text:
Because Saidina Abdul Rahman is a businessman, he was paired with Saidina Sa'ad Ibn Rabi'.

Saidina Sa'ad is also famous among successful businessmen in Medina. His property, wealth and interests are indeed at the same level as Saidina Abdul Rahman r.anh

Text:
Lepas Rasulullah ﷺ pairkan tu, maka Saidina Saad pun bagitahu Saidina Abdul Rahman, 

Aku akan bagi separuh daripada harta aku untuk kau. 

Dan kalau kau mahu, bahkan isteri pun akan aku ceraikan untuk kau kahwini.
Translated Text:
After Rasulullah ﷺ paired it, Saidina Saad also told Saidina Abdul Rahman,

I will give you half of my property.

And if you want, I will even divorce my wife for you to marry.

Text:
Statement kedua tu kata mufti, adalah untuk tunjukkan level kesanggupan sahabat ansar ini untuk entertain sahabat2 muhajirin. 

Bayangkan kawan-kawan, kita sendiri tak mampu nak bersikap semacam ni, even pada ahli keluarga kita sendiri.
Translated Text:
The second statement, said the mufti, is to show the level of ability of these ansar friends to entertain the muhajirin friends.

Imagine friends, we ourselves are not capable of behaving like this, even to our own family members.

Text:
Katalah abang kita datang kepada kita kerana kesusahan yang dihadapi, sanggup tak kita nak bagi separuh daripada harta kita untuk dia?

Bantu memang kita akan bantu. 

Tapi level para sahabat ni memang satu macam. Memang kita sukar untuk faham.
Translated Text:
Let's say our brother came to us because of the difficulties he faced, are we willing to give half of our wealth to him?

Help indeed we will help.

But the level of these friends is one of a kind. Indeed we are difficult to understand.

Text:
Setelah ditawarkan semua tu, Saidina Abdul Rahman tersenyum dan berkata, 

Semoga Allah merahmati kamu, kekayaan kamu & ahli keluargamu.

Tunjukkan aku, dimanakah pasar. 

Beliau tolak semua tawaran tu dan tanya dimana tempat untuk beliau mula berniaga.
Translated Text:
After being offered all that, Saidina Abdul Rahman smiled and said,

May God bless you, your wealth & your family members

Show me where the market is.

He rejected all the offers and asked where he could start business.

Text:
Satu bentuk yakin yang sempurna kepada yang Maha Kaya. 

Bayangkan kalau waktu kita susah, baru lepas bankrap, takde apa-apa, member kita offer separuh daripada harta dia untuk kita. 

Dan kita tolak!

Sebab faham rezeki itu datangnya daripada Dia, bukan manusia.
Translated Text:
A perfect form of confidence in the Almighty.

Imagine if our time is hard, he just went bankrupt, there is nothing, he offers us half of his property for us.

And we push!

Because I understand that sustenance comes from Him, not man.

Text:
Kemudian bila tiba di pasar, Saidina Abdul Rahman r.anh beli seekor unta dengan bayaran kredit. 

Kemudian dijual unta tersebut dengan harga yang sama, yang diambil daripada unta tersebut cumalah talinya.
Translated Text:
Then when he arrived at the market, Saidina Abdul Rahman r.anh bought a camel with a credit payment.

Then the camel was sold for the same price, only the rope was taken from the camel.

Text:
Jadi secara kasarnya, untung niaga beliau untuk setiap transaksi cumalah tali unta. 

Kita pun confuse kan, apa yang Saidina Abdul Rahman cuba buat ni? 

Setakat untung tali, mana boleh kaya!
Translated Text:
So roughly speaking, his profit for each transaction is just a camel string.

We are also confused, right? What is Saidina Abdul Rahman trying to do?

As far as rope profit, how can you be rich!

Text:
Inilah yang menariknya strategi perniagaan beliau. 

Tali unta ni sangat penting untuk kawal unta tu. Dan talinya (pada waktu tu) adalah limited dan jenis guna semula (bukan jenis pakai buang). 

Apa yang terjadi adalah, Saidina Abdul Rahman sedang create satu demand tanpa sedar.
Translated Text:
This is the attractiveness of his business strategy.

This camel rope is very important to control the camel. And the strap (at that time) was limited and reusable (not disposable).

What happened is, Saidina Abdul Rahman was creating a demand without realizing it.

Text:
Bila semakin banyak unta yang dijual tanpa tali, maka demand untuk mendapatkan tali unta semakin bertambah. 

Tali tu pulak ada pada siapa?

Saidina Abdul Rahman bin 'Auf. 

Maka dikatakan pada waktu itu, beliau yang mengawal market tali unta ni.
Translated Text:
When more and more camels are sold without ropes, the demand for camel ropes increases.

Who has the rope?

Saidina Abdul Rahman bin 'Auf.

So it is said that at that time, he controlled the camel rope market.

Text:
Lepas control market tali unta, perlahan-lahan Saidina Abdul Rahman kembangkan bisnesnya dengan menjual unta. 

Kemudian ke sektor hartanah, retail dan semakin membiak-biak. 

Sehinggalah hartanya pun ikut membiak sama.
Translated Text:
After controlling the camel rope market, Saidina Abdul Rahman slowly developed her business by selling camels.

Then to the real estate sector, retail and more and more.

Until his wealth also multiplied.

Text:
Ada satu ketika, Saidina Abdul Rahman jual sebidang tanah miliknya dengan harga 40,000 dinar. 

Berapa banyak 1 dinar? 

1 dinar = RM745 (anggaran tahun 2017)

Jadi 40,000 dinar = +-15,000,000!

Apa yang dia buat dengan duit tu?
Translated Text:
There was a time, Saidina Abdul Rahman sold a piece of land he owned for 40,000 dinars.

How much is 1 dinar?

1 dinar = RM745 (2017 estimate)

So 40,000 dinars = +-15,000,000!

What did he do with the money?

Text:
1/3 beliau berikan kepada ahli keluarganya
1/3 beliau berikan kepada isteri Nabi ﷺ (ketika ini Nabi ﷺ telah wafat)
1/3 beliau berikan kepada orang miskin

Untuk diri sendiri?

Menurut mufti, Saidina Abdul Rahman kata, 

I have enough already.
Translated Text:
1/3 he gave to his family members
1/3 he gave to the wife of the Prophet ﷺ (now the Prophet ﷺ has passed away)
1/3 he gave to the poor

For yourself?

According to the mufti, Saidina Abdul Rahman said,

I have enough already.

Text:
MasyaAllah. 

Betapa hebatnya para sahabat ni kan, sampai nilai yang buat mata kita terbeliak nak terkeluar ni pun dia boleh infaqkan macam tu je.
Translated Text:
God willing.

How great are these friends, even the value that makes our eyes widen to come out, he can spend like that.

Text:
Sebelum beliau meninggal dunia, Saidina Abdul rahman telah menginfaqkan: 

50,000 dinar di jalan Allah.
400 dinar untuk setiap sahabat atau ahli keluarga para sahabat yang menyertai perang Badar. 

Ni infaq yang dibuat ketika beliau masih lagi hidup bukan wasiat.
Translated Text:
Before he died, Saidina Abdul Rahman spent:

50,000 dinars in the way of God.
400 dinars for each friend or family member of the friends who participated in the Badr war.

Ni infaq made when he was still alive is not a will.

Text:
Bila meninggal dunia, Saidina Abdul Rahman bin Auf r.anh telah meninggalkan 3 isteri. 

Pembahagian faraid untuk isteri ni 1/8 daripada harta. Maknanya, 3 orang isteri tersebut kena kongsi 1/8 tersebut.

Korang tahu berapa anggaran setiap isteri beliau dapat?

80,000 dinar
Translated Text:
When he died, Saidina Abdul Rahman bin Auf r.anh left 3 wives.

The distribution of farid for the wife is 1/8 of the property. That means, the 3 wives have to share 1/8 of that.

Do you know how much each wife gets?

80,000 dinars

Text:
Gitulah kawan-kawan. 

Terlampau banyak yang kita boleh belajar daripada kisah para sahabat ni. Bukan perkara2 akhirat saja, bahkan perkara2 dunia pun, ada yang kita boleh pelajari daripada mereka. 

Sebab mereka juga manusia.
Translated Text:
That's it friends.

There is so much we can learn from the stories of these friends. Not only the things of the hereafter, but even the things of the world, there is something we can learn from them.

Because they are also human.

Text:
Mereka juga ada keperluan hidup sama seperti kita.

Bezanya, mereka tidak pernah meletakkan kehidupan dunia ini sebagai matlamat hidup mereka.

Dunia, harta atau apa saja yang mereka miliki, mereka sekadar meletakkannya ditangan.

Bila tiba saat untuk melepaskan, mereka lepaskan.
Translated Text:
They also have life needs just like us.

The difference is, they never put the life of this world as their life goal.

The world, property or whatever they have, they simply put it in their hands.

When it's time to let go, they let go.

Text:
Shibal biyong ni kalau kita terjemahkan dalam bahaya melayu lebih kurang macam, 'Mampuslah, belanja je!' (lagi kasar bunyi dia sebenarnya)

Konsep ni muncul disebabkan kekecewaan generasi muda terhadap keadaan ekonomi, pasaran hartanah dan peluang pekerjaan yang sangat menekan.
Translated Text:
This shibal biyong if we translate it in Malay danger is more or less like, 'Can you afford it, just go shopping!' (he actually sounds ruder)

This concept emerged due to the frustration of the young generation with the economic situation, real estate market and job opportunities that are very stressful.

Text:
Disebabkan kekecewaan ini generasi muda jadi tak percaya dengan simpanan dan pelaburan jangka masa panjang. 

"Buat apa nak simpan duit? Sama je!"

"Aku dah penat-penat kerja ni, beli je lah baju ni. Mahal sikit takpe."
Translated Text:
Due to this disappointment, the younger generation does not believe in long-term savings and investments.

"What do you want to save money for? It's the same!"

"I'm tired of this work, just buy this shirt. It's a little expensive, isn't it?"

Text:
"Stress gila bos marah, jom pergi makan buffet mahal kat hotel!"

Generasi kita lagi suka untuk menikmati instant gratification. 

Dan lebih malang kita ni sebenarnya terlebih menikmati sampai sanggup belanjakan wang yang banyak untuk perkara2 yang tak perlu.
Translated Text:
"Stress is crazy, the boss is angry, let's go eat an expensive buffet at the hotel!"

Our generation likes to enjoy instant gratification.

And it's even more unfortunate that we actually enjoy it so much that we are willing to spend a lot of money on unnecessary things.

Text:
Kita sanggup habiskan RM20 untuk secawan kopi, RM27 untuk sebatang aiskrim dan RM58 untuk satu hidangan makanan. 

Benda ni sebenarnya kalau nak salahkan generasi muda sepenuhnya pun tak adil jga. 

Tapi sebagai orang muda, mahu tak mahu kita kena kawal diri kita dalam berbelanja
Translated Text:
We are willing to spend RM20 for a cup of coffee, RM27 for an ice cream and RM58 for a meal.

In fact, if you want to blame the younger generation completely, it is not fair.

But as young people, like it or not we have to control ourselves in shopping

Text:
Kegagalan startup

- Hampir 90% startup sebenarnya gagal. Hanya 10% je yang berjaya.
- Daripada 90% yang gagal ni, 10% gagal pada tahun pertama mereka bermula!
- Lagi 70% gagal antara tahun kedua sampai tahun kelima.
- Accross all industries, failure rates startup ni hampir sama.
Translated Text:
Startup failure

- Almost 90% of startups actually fail. Only 10% succeed.
- Of the 90% who fail, 10% fail in the first year they start!
- Another 70% fail between the second year and the fifth year.
- Across all industries, startup failure rates are almost the same.

Text:
Kenapa gagal?

- The number one reason adalah sebab startup tu misread market demand. 42% startup gagal disebabkan alasan ni.
- Sebab yang kedua: duit funding & personal money pun dah habis. 29% gagal disebabkan perkara ni.
Translated Text:
Why fail?

- The number one reason is because the startup misread market demand. 42% of startups fail due to this reason.
- The second reason: funding money & personal money has run out. 29% fail because of this.

Text:
- Selain dua sebab tu, 23% gagal disebabkan founding team yg lemah/
- 19% pulak gagal disebabkan masalah persaingan.
- Masalah persaingan ni utk startup yg berusia 3-5 tahun kebiasannya.
- Tapi 82% mengaku yg antara punca kegagalan bisnes mereka adalah masalah cash-flow.
Translated Text:
- In addition to those two reasons, 23% fail due to a weak founding team/
- 19% failed due to competition problems.
- This competition problem is for startups that are usually 3-5 years old.
- But 82% admit that one of the causes of their business failure is cash-flow problems.

Text:
Cerita pasal kejayaan pulak

- Founder yang ada track record successful business sebelum ni peratus kejayaan dia 30% lagi tinggi berbanding drpd orang biasa.
Translated Text:
A story about success

- Founders who have a track record of successful business before this, their success rate is 30% higher than that of ordinary people.

Text:
- 82% startup founders yg berjaya mengaku yg diorang ada quakification & experience untuk run that company.

- Antara perkara paling penting adalah beri perhatian kepada pelanggan kita untuk dapat pelanggan yg setia. Hehe.
Translated Text:
- 82% of successful startup founders admit that they have quakification & experience to run that company.

- One of the most important things is to pay attention to our customers to get loyal customers. Hehe.

Text:
Cabaran

- Cabaran paling susah & sukar untuk startup adalah generate business yg baru.

- Founder yang pernah gagal sebelum ni ada 20% probability untuk berjaya,

- Yang tak pernah gagal, probabilitynya untuk berjaya cuma 18%.
Translated Text:
Challenge

- The hardest challenge & It is difficult for startups to generate new business.

- Founders who have failed before have a 20% probability of success,

- Those who never fail, the probability of success is only 18%.

Text:
Startup funding facts

- VC terima lebih 1000 proposal setiap tahun.
- Mostly vc interested dengan bisnes yg require investment lebih daripada 250K.
- Tahun 2017, venture capital funding capai USD 155 billion!
- Bytedance adalah startup yang paling bernilai USD 75 billion.
Translated Text:
Startup funding facts

- VCs receive over 1000 proposals every year.
- Mostly VC interested in businesses that require investment of more than 250K.
- In 2017, venture capital funding reached USD 155 billion!
- Bytedance is the most valued startup at USD 75 billion.

Text:
Nabi ﷺ ditanya puasa mana yang paling mulia setelah Ramadhan? 

Baginda berkata: 

"Sha'ban untuk menghormati bulan Ramadhan" 

Sahabat berkata: 

"Amal mana yang terbaik?" 

Nabi ﷺ berkata: 

"Bersedekah di bulan Ramadhan”

Jami` at-Tirmidhi 663
Translated Text:
The Prophet ﷺ was asked which fast is the most honorable after Ramadan?

He said:

"Sha'ban to honor the month of Ramadan"

Friends said:

"Which charity is best?"

The Prophet ﷺ said:

"Giving charity in the month of Ramadan"

Jami` at-Tirmidhi 663

Text:
Rasulullah ﷺ bersabda,

Satu tasbihah di bulan Ramadhan lebih baik daripada seribu tasbihah yang lain.

Jami` at-Tirmidhi 3472
Translated Text:

Text:
Abu Hurairah r.anh berkata, 

Saya mendengar Rasulullah ﷺ bersabda mengenai Ramadan, 

Barang siapa berdoa pada malam hari di dalamnya (Ramadan) kerana iman yang ikhlas & mengharapkan pahala dari Allah, maka semua dosa-dosanya sebelumnya akan diampuni.

Sahih al-Bukhari 2008

Text:

Nabi ﷺ adalah yang paling pemurah dari semua orang, dan dia menjadi lebih murah hati pada bulan Ramadhan ketika Jibril bertemu dengannya. 

Jibril selalu bertemu dengannya setiap malam pada bulan Ramadan untuk mengulang kaji al-Quran dengannya.

The Prophet ﷺ was the most generous of all people, and he became even more generous in the month of Ramadan when Gabriel met him.

Jibril used to meet him every night in Ramadan to review the Qur'an with him.

Text:
Ahlan wa sahlan ya Ramadan. 

Ya Allah, sampaikanlah kami ke bulan ramadan. Jadikanlah ramadan tahun ini, ramadan paling baik daripada ramadan-ramadan sebelum ini. 

Amiin.
Translated Text:
Ahlan wa sahlan ya Ramadan.

Ya Allah, bring us to the month of Ramadan. Make this year's Ramadan the best Ramadan of all previous Ramadans.

Amen.

Text:
Bila masuk je rumah, rasa nak nangis weh.

Pijak je karpet, basah stokin ni. Ingatkan ada air tumpah ke, bila pandang atas rupanya atap rumah yang bocor.

Waktu tu pulak musim hujan, memang berlecak habis rumah. Huhu
Translated Text:
When I enter the house, I feel like crying.

Step on the carpet, get these socks wet. Remember that there is spilled water, when you look at the roof of the house it looks like it is leaking.

At that time it was rainy season, the house was really wet. Huh

Text:
Nenek ni dah umur 70 tahun, nak jalan pun susah.

Bukan takat nak uruskan rumah, nak uruskan diri sendiri pun perlukan tenaga. Bertambah pula dengan 2 orang anak istimewa. 

Tak dapat nak bayangkan macam mana kalau saya di posisi makcik ni. Fuh
Translated Text:
This grandmother is 70 years old, it's hard to even walk.

It's not just about taking care of the house, taking care of yourself also requires energy. In addition to having 2 special children.

I can't imagine what it would be like if I were in this aunt's position. Phew

Text:
Tapi makcik ni baik, hebat orangnya.

Sepanjang kami berbual, tak dgr langsung keluhan

Tak pernah dia kata anak istimewa menyusahkan dia.

Tak pernah dia salahkan Tuhan atas ujianNya.

Jauh sekali nak menyalahkan kami yang terlambat berjumpa dengan dia.
Translated Text:
But this aunt is good, she is a great person.

As long as we talked, there were no complaints

He never said that special children made him difficult.

He never blamed God for His trials.

Far from blaming us for being late to meet him.

Text:
Bila ditanya apa yg dia perlukan, cukup sederhana permintaannya.

Sekadar sehelai dua kain sarung tambahan.

Menitik air mata kami mendengar satu-satunya permintaan dia.
Translated Text:
When asked what he needed, his request was quite simple.

Just two extra sheets of sarong cloth.

Dropping tears we heard his only request.

Text:
Bukan ke patutnya dia minta kami baikikan rumah sekali?

Atau setidaknya, suruhlah kami belikan makanan untuk sebulan dua?
Translated Text:
Shouldn't he ask us to fix the house once?

Or at least, tell us to buy food for a month or two?

Text:
Dan nescaya Kami akan menguji kalian dengan sedikit daripada perasaan takut, rasa lapar, kekurangan harta benda, kehilangan nyawa (kematian), serta tumbuh-tumbuhan dan berikanlah khabar gembira kepada orang-orang yang bersabar.

[2:155]
Translated Text:
And surely We will test you with a little of fear, hunger, lack of property, loss of life (death), and plants and give glad tidings to those who are patient.

[2:155]

Text:
1. Company

- apa yang company kita jual?

- apa yang membezakan produk yg kita offer dengan competitor?

- apa advantage company kita?

- kalau ada tambahan modal 50K, kita akan invest dkt mana?

- kalau kena cut bajet 10% drpd overhead, company kita akan cut dekat mana dulu?
Translated Text:
1. Company

- what does our company sell?

- what differentiates the products we offer from competitors?

- what is our company advantage?

- if there is an additional capital of 50K, where will we invest?

- if the budget has to be cut by 10% from overhead, where will our company cut first?

Text:
So you guys boleh tanya soalan ni pada diri sendiri.

Actually boleh tambah beberapa soalan lagi untuk dapatkan analisis yg lagi detail.
Translated Text:
So you guys can ask this question to yourself.

Actually, you can add a few more questions to get a more detailed analysis.

Text:
2. Collaborators

- siapa run daily operation company kita?

- supplier barang yg kita jual?

- siapa shipping provider?

- siapa proses payment gateway?

- siapa provide e-commerce kita?

- domain/hosting provider?
Translated Text:
2. Collaborators

- Who runs our daily operation company?

- the supplier of the goods we sell?

- who is the shipping provider?

- who processes the payment gateway?

- Who is our e-commerce provider?

- domain/hosting provider?

Text:
Listkan semua bisnes & individu yg terlibat untuk bisnes kita operate.

Soalan kat atas tadi contoh je, boleh usahakan kembangkan lagi untuk dapatkan semua yg terlibat utk bisnes kita operate.
Translated Text:
List all businesses & individuals involved in operating our business.

The question above is just an example, we can try to develop it further to get everyone involved for our business to operate.

Text:
3. Customer

- persamaan customer/klien kita?

- siapa target audience kita?

- apa produk yg paling banyak/sikit terjual?

- customer kita dtg dr mana?

- berapa repeat purchase yg kita dapat?
Translated Text:
3. Customers

- our customer/client equation?

- Who is our target audience?

- what are the products that have sold the most/least?

- Where do our customers come from?

- how many repeat purchases do we get?

Text:
Listkan dulu soalan2 & semak database kita. 

Duduk & listkan dulu soalan utk dapatkan detail ttg clien/customer kita. Nesti dapat lagi byj soalan.
Translated Text:
List the questions first & check our database.

Sit & list the questions first to get details about our client/customer. Must have more questions.

Text:
4. Competitors 

- siapa direct competitor?

- established competitors & emerging competitors?

- apa strength competitors kita?

- apa weakness competitors kita?

- What audiences are my competitors targeting?
Translated Text:
4. Competitors 

- siapa direct competitor?

- established competitors & emerging competitors?

- apa strength competitors kita?

- apa weakness competitors kita?

- What audiences are my competitors targeting?

Text:
5. Climate

Climate ni external factors yg boleh affect bisnes kita. Contohnya, industry trends, societal trends, legal trends atau teknologi2 baru.
Translated Text:
5. Climate

Climate is an external factor that can affect our business. For example, industry trends, social trends, legal trends or new technologies.

Text:
Once kita dah buat ni, kita akan dapat buat easy & digestible information berkaitan bisnes kita.

Bila kita dapat tengok semua elemen ni scr holistik, lg mudah lah kita nak buat decision lagi2 berkenaan marketing.
Translated Text:
Once we have done this, we will be able to do easy & digestible information related to our business.

When we can look at all these elements holistically, it will be easy for us to make decisions about marketing.

Text:
1. Siapa diri kita?

First kenalah figure out siapa diri kita sebenarnya. Macam mana nak kenal diri sendiri? Try jawab soalan kat bawah ni:

- Apa bidang yang power?
- Apa perkara yg memotivasikan saya?
- Apa pujian orang?
Translated Text:
1. Who are we?

First we have to figure out who we really are. How do you know yourself? Try to answer the questions below:

- What are the areas of power?
- What motivates me?
- What people compliment?

Text:
- Projek/Bahagian apa yang orang selalu minta tolong?

- Perkara yang menyebabkan kehabisan tenaga?

- Prokek/perkara yang boleh spend masa tanpa rasa overwhelmed & penat gila?
Translated Text:
- What projects/parts do people always ask for help with?

- Things that cause energy depletion?

- Projects/things that you can spend time without feeling overwhelmed & crazy tired?

Text:
Susah nak jawab? Takpe take ur time. Memang banyak nak kena fikir kan. Hehe

Tapi kalau tak dapat nak jawab jugak, mintaklah bantuan colleagues, kawan2 atau keluarga yg rapat dengan kita.

Jawapan ni akan membantu diri kita kenal dengan diri sendiri. Hehe
Translated Text:
Difficult to answer? Don't take ur time. It's a lot to think about. Hehe

But if you can't answer, ask for help from colleagues, friends or family who are close to us.

This answer will help us get to know ourselves. Hehe

Text:
2. Kenalpasti orang nak kenal kita sebagai apa?

Lepas dah setel jawab soalan-soalan dekat atas ni, kita mesti dah dapat gambaran siapa diri kita yang sebenar.

Daripada banyak benda yang boleh describe diri kita, which sides yang kita nak tonjolkan pada dunia? Haha
Translated Text:
2. Identify what people want to know us as?

After answering the questions above, we must have a picture of who we really are.

Of the many things that can describe ourselves, which sides do we want to highlight to the world? Haha

Text:
Kena ingat,

Personal brand is more than a reflection of who you are today; it’s a roadmap of where you to go.

Dalam 5-10 tahun ni apa plan kita? 

Cari kekuatan kita & tonjolkan pada semua.
Translated Text:
got to remember,

Personal brand is more than a reflection of who you are today; it's a roadmap of where you to go.

In 5-10 years what is our plan?

Find our strength & stand out in all.

Text:
3. Define you audience

 Sebelum nak start personal brand, kenalah tahu kita punya target audience.

Tak semua orang bina personal brand untuk jadi the next kardashian kan? Hehe
Translated Text:
3. Define you audience

 Before you want to start a personal brand, you know you have a target audience.

Not everyone builds a personal brand to become the next Kardashian, right? Haha

Text:
Ada orang nak tonjolkan diri pada industry leader.

Ada orang nak tonjolkan diri pada recruiter.

Ada yang nak tonjolkan diri pada producer.
Translated Text:
There are people who want to stand out from the industry leader.

There are people who want to stand out to the recruiter.

Some want to stand out to the producer.

Text:
Semua audience ni, ada tempat berkumpulnya masing2.

Jadi bila kita dah kenal pasti audience kita, kita boleh agak dah kat mana sebenarnya diorang lepak.

Bila tahu ni, kita bolehlah fokus tonjolkan diri dekat situ.
Translated Text:
All these audiences have a place to gather.

So when we have identified our audience, we can guess where people actually hang out.

When we know this, we can focus on making ourselves stand out there.

Text:
4. Networking

"Networking is a lot like nutrition and fitness: we know what to do, the hard part is making it a top priority."

Networking ni penting tau. Susah nak berjaya kalau kita selalu jadi lone ranger. Haha

Personal brand is how you carry yourself.

Sebab memang kita tengah tonjolkan diri kita kan, bukan kita berlakon pun. Hehe

Personal brand is how you carry yourself.

Because we are showing off ourselves, not acting. Hehe

Text:
Sebelum peperangan tercetus, rakyat Syria dah mula complain tentang masalah pengangguran, corruption & political freedom yang disekat oleh Bashar. 

Lama sangat rakyat Syria ni complain dari tahun 2000 lagi.

Tapi kemuncaknya berlaku pada tahun 2011. 10 tahun lepas!
Translated Text:
Before the war broke out, the people of Syria had started to complain about the problem of unemployment, corruption & political freedom blocked by Bashar.

Syrian people have been complaining for a long time since 2000.

But the peak happened in 2011. 10 years ago!

Text:
Bulan Mac 2011, satu demonstrasi pro-demokrasi tercetus dekat sebuah bandar dekat Deraa.

Waktu ni kalau ingat, Arab Spring baru bermula. Jadi demonstrasi ni katakan terinspirasi daripada gerakan-gerakan Arab Spring tu.
Translated Text:
In March 2011, a pro-democracy demonstration broke out near a town near Deraa.

If you remember this time, the Arab Spring has just started. So this demonstration is said to be inspired by the Arab Spring movements.

Text:
Untuk mengatasi demonstrasi ni, kerajaan Bashar ni ambil jalan mudah dengan gunakan kekerasan & pembunuhan. Semuanya untuk menakutkan rakyat dia sendiri.

Tapi memang silap tindakan dia tu.
Translated Text:
To overcome this demonstration, Bashar's government took the easy way out by using force & murder. All to scare his own people.

But his actions were wrong.

Text:
Orang tengah marah, lagi dia simbah petrol. Api kemarahan semakin memuncak. Rakyat tuntut supaya Bashar letak jawatan sebagai presiden.

Opposition supporters pun mula ambil langkah lebih drastik untuk melawan rejim kerajaan Bashar.
Translated Text:
People are angry, and he spills petrol. The fire of anger is rising. The people demanded that Bashar resign as president.

Opposition supporters also began to take more drastic measures to fight against Bashar's government regime.

Text:
Keganasan memuncak.

Pertempuran dimana-mana.
Ratusan kumpulan-kumpulan pemberontak muncul. Peperangan antara penyokong Bashar & penentang Bashar semakin parah.

Dalam keadaan yang kucar-kacir ni, ISIS & all-Qaeda pun join sekaki.
Translated Text:
Violence escalated.

Battle everywhere.
Hundreds of rebel groups emerged. The war between supporters of Bashar & Bashar's opponents are getting worse.

In this chaotic situation, ISIS & all-Qaeda also joined in.

Text:
Berapa ramai yang meninggal dunia?

Syrian Observatory for Human Rights mengesahkan, setakat bulan disember 2020, 387,118 orang telah meninggal dunia.

 116,911 daripada jumlah kematian yg documented ni adalah rakyat biasa. Sedih kan?
Translated Text:
How many died?

The Syrian Observatory for Human Rights confirmed that, as of December 2020, 387,118 people have died.

 116,911 of the documented deaths are ordinary people. Sad right?

Text:
Tapi bukan tu je, 205,300 orang lagi hilang & tak dijumpai walaupun setelah beberapa tahun dan presumed dead.

Daripada 205K+ ni, 88,000 adalah org awam yg powerless. Sedihnya.

Ada ibu, ayah, anak, kawan2 seseorang dalam setiap angka yang menyedihkan ni.
Translated Text:
But that's not all, another 205,300 people are missing & not found even after several years and presumed dead.

Of these 205K+, 88,000 are powerless civilians. It's sad.

There is a mother, father, child, someone's friends in each of these sad numbers.

Text:
Daripada jumlah tadi, siapa yang paling banyak bunuh siapa?

Kerajaan Syria yang dipimpin Bashar menyebabkan 156,329 kematian. Kumpulan pemberontak membunuh 34,606.
Translated Text:
Out of the total, who killed who the most?

The Syrian government led by Bashar caused 156,329 deaths. Rebel groups killed 34,606.

Text:
Siapa yang terlibat?

Bila perang tercetus, of course negara2 besar akan amek kesempatan. Ada yang support government, ada yang support pemberontak.

Yang merana siapa? Rakyat Syria!
Translated Text:
Who is involved?

When a war breaks out, of course the big countries will take advantage. Some support the government, some support the rebels.

Who is languishing? Syrian people!

Text:
Antara negara yang join sekaki dalam peperangan ni:

- Syria
- Russia
- Iran
- Arab Saudi
- Turkey
Translated Text:
Among the countries that joined together in this war:

- Syria
- Russia
- Iran
- Saudi Arabia
- Turkey

Text:
Kesan peperangan yang berlarutan hampir 10 tahun ni, lebih 2,100,000 rakyat Syria mengalami kecederaan kronik & hilang upaya menyeluruh kekal.

Selain tu, lebih separuh daripada rakyat Syria terpaksa jadi pelarian.
Pelarian di luar negara dan dalam negara.
Translated Text:
As a result of the war that lasted almost 10 years, more than 2,100,000 Syrians suffered chronic injuries & permanent total disability.

In addition, more than half of the Syrian people had to become refugees.
Refugees abroad and within the country.

Text:
5.6 juta daripada rakyat syria kini berada di Lubnan, Jordan, Turki dan beberapa negara eropah lain.

6.7 juta lagi menjadi pelarian di tanah air yang mereka cintai.

Sedih kan? Padehal sebelum peperangan jadi, diorang hidup dalam keadaan baik.
Translated Text:
5.6 million of the Syrian people are now in Lebanon, Jordan, Turkey and some other European countries.

Another 6.7 million became refugees in their beloved homeland.

Sad right? Although before the war, people lived in good conditions.

Text:
As of January 2021, 13,400,000 rakyat Syria yang masih berada di Syria memerlukan bantuan kemanusiaan.

12,000,000 rakyatnya struggle untuk dapatkan makanan setiap hari. 

Setengah juta kanak-kanak mengalami masalah kekurangan nutrisi yang kritikal.
Translated Text:
As of January 2021, 13,400,000 Syrians still in Syria need humanitarian assistance.

12,000,000 people struggle to get food every day.

Half a million children suffer from critical nutritional deficiencies.

Text:
So macam tu lah keadaan Syria sekarang.

Dalam kita dengar tak dengar berita pasal sedare2 kita kat sana, diorang masih menantikan bantuan daripada kita.

Mereka masih menderita, kesusahan & tak berdaya.
Translated Text:
So that's the situation in Syria now.

Whether we hear or not hear news about our sedare2 there, people are still waiting for help from us.

They still suffer, hardship & powerless.

Text:
Jadi tugas kitalah untuk membantu mereka.

Kalau korang nak join kami dalam membantu sedara2 kita dekat sana terutamanya untuk bulan ramadan yang mulia ni, bolehlah klik link dekat bawah ni.

So it is our job to help them.

If you want to join us in helping our fellow citizens, especially for this holy month of Ramadan, you can click on the link below.

Don't forget to RT once, invite other people to help the same. https://t.co/tMT08v7ulW

Text:
1. Set Matlamat Yang Jelas

Lagi2 dalam fasa PKP/P/B/D/EFGHIJKL ni.

Kadang2 kita terpaksa sesuaikan roles mereka dengan keadaan semasa. Some of them might have responsibility shift etc.
Translated Text:
1. Set Clear Goals

More in this PKP/P/B/D/EFGHIJKL phase.

Sometimes we have to adapt their roles to the current situation. Some of them might have responsibility shift etc.

Text:
So leader kena mainkan peranan bantu untuk set goal yg jelas.

Kalau takde goal yg jelas, staf akan terumbang-ambing lah jawabnya. 

Bila staff tak clear, diorg akn stress.
Bila stress jadi tak produktif. Rugi banyak tu.
Translated Text:
So the leader has to play a supporting role to set a clear goal.

If there is no clear goal, the staff will hesitate to answer.

When the staff is not clear, people get stressed.
When stress becomes unproductive. That's a lot of loss.

Text:
Selain tu, penting juga kita create a connection between their contribution and organisational goals.

Bila staff nampak how they contribute to the bigger goals, insyaAllah semua akan lagi bersemangat.
Translated Text:
Apart from that, it is also important for us to create a connection between their contribution and organizational goals.

If the staff see how they contribute to the bigger goals, God willing, everyone will be more enthusiastic.

Text:
2. Recognise & Celebrate Achievements

Tahu tak, ada satu research pernah buat tentang big rewards & small rewards.

Conclusion daripada research tu bagitahu, yang staff who receive regular small rewards 8X more engaged than employees that receive big reward once a year.
Translated Text:
2. Recognise & Celebrate Achievements

Tahu tak, ada satu research pernah buat tentang big rewards & small rewards.

Conclusion daripada research tu bagitahu, yang staff who receive regular small rewards 8X more engaged than employees that receive big reward once a year.

Text:
That's why penting untung leader set & celebrate mini-milestones untuk team kita.

Janganlah setahun sekali baru kita nak celebrate the milestone.

Lagi kerap lagi bagus. And hadiah pun tak perlu mahal2 sebenarnya.
Translated Text:
That's why it's important to profit from the leader set & celebrate mini-milestones for our team.

Don't celebrate the milestone once a year.

The more often the better. And gifts don't have to be expensive.

Text:
3. Bagi constructive feedback

Kebanyakan leader ada slightly more experience than staff lain.

Sebab tu, leader kena sentiasa bagi constructibe feedback pada staff dia.

And surprisingly, constructive feedback ni boleh motivate staff tau!
Translated Text:
3. Give constructive feedback

Most leaders have slightly more experience than other staff.

Because of that, the leader must always give constructive feedback to his staff.

And surprisingly, this constructive feedback can motivate staff you know!

Text:
Constructive feedback ni feedback yang kita bagi with clear intention supaya team member kita tu dapat improve,

Ada satu research ni bagitahu, staff yang dapat constructive feedback 2.5X more motivated tapi malangnya less than half yg dapat feedback daripada leader diorang.
Translated Text:
Constructive feedback is feedback that we give with clear intention so that our team members can improve,

There is a research that tells us that staff who get constructive feedback are 2.5X more motivated, but unfortunately less than half who get feedback from their leaders.

Text:

Text:
1. Tidur Awal Dan Bangun Awal

Adoi, hahahaha.

Saya ni dahlah jenis stay up.
Tapi sebenarnya, tidur awal dan bangun awal tu lebih baik untuk kekal fokus. 

Tak perlu pun bangun awal pukul 4 pagi. Kalau dapat bangun awal setengah jam sebelum subuh pun okay.
Translated Text:
1. Go to bed early and wake up early

Come on, hahahaha.

I'm the stay up type.
But actually, going to bed early and waking up early is better to stay focused.

No need to wake up early at 4 am. If you can get up early, half an hour before dawn, it's okay.

Text:
Bila kita bangun awal, kita ada extra time utk plan task hari tu. Bila ada planning tu nanti senanglah sikit nak buat kerja, sebab dah tahu nak kena buat apa.

Tujuan bangun awal ni sebab bagi kita tempoh bertenang dan relaks je haha. Takdelah tergopoh2 nak rushing kan.
Translated Text:
When we wake up early, we have extra time to plan the day's tasks. When you have a plan, it's a little easier to do work, because you know what you want to do.

The purpose of waking up early is because it is a period of calm and relaxation for us haha. Don't rush to rush, right?

Text:
Bayangkan kalau asyik bangun lambat, dah kalut berebut nak bersiap, kena hadap jem dan kalau ada keluarga, nak urus keluarga pula.

So, bangun awal tu memberi kita peluanglah nak chill-chill sambil bersiap pagi tu. So, kalau nak bangun awal, kenalah tidur awal juga haha.
Translated Text:
Imagine waking up late, struggling to get ready, having to deal with jams and if you have a family, you have to take care of the family as well.

So, waking up early gives us a chance to chill while getting ready that morning. So, if you want to wake up early, you have to go to bed early too haha.

Text:
2. Increase mental focus

Dunia harini banyak sangat distraction kan.

Kejap nak check Twitter, baru tutup fon kejap ada noti org reply story ig pulak. Adoi. Hahah 

So, apa nak buat untuk tingkatkan mental focus?
Translated Text:
2. Increase mental focus

There are a lot of distractions in today's world, right?

Just wanted to check Twitter, just closed the phone and there was a notification that someone replied to the story. Aoi. Hahaha

So, what do you want to do to increase mental focus?

Text:
- remove distraction
- jangan multitasking
- be more present
- take a rest bila penat
Translated Text:
- remove distraction
- jangan multitasking
- be more present
- take a rest bila penat

Text:
3. Set priority

Lagi2 kalau korang jadi leader. Memang kena susun dan atur segala task tu mengikut prioriti dia. Kalau takde perancangan rapi, memang kucar-kacir team nnt.

Tak semua task tu penting & nak kena siapkan cepat kan.
Translated Text:
3. Set priorities

Especially if you are a leader. It is necessary to arrange and arrange all the tasks according to his priorities. If there is no careful planning, the team will be a mess soon.

Not all tasks are important & I want to prepare quickly, right?

Text:
Setkan prioriti mengikut keutamaan & due date for each task.

Ada task yg important tapi due date dia lama lagi, ada task yg penting & due date lagi 2 hari. Utamakan yg tu dulu. Okay?
Translated Text:
Set priorities according to priority & due date for each task.

There is an important task but the due date is taking a long time, there are important tasks & another due date in 2 days. Prioritize that first. okay?

Text:
4. Jangan Micromanage

Saya rasa micromanage ni antara keluhan para pekerja di Malaysia ni. Adoi.

Sebagai leader, memang kita patut ambil tahu sebarang update dan informasi berkaitan organisasi, tapi takperlulah sampai ke semua benda termasuk yang kecil pun nak tahu.
Translated Text:
4. Don't Micromanage

I think micromanaging is one of the complaints of workers in Malaysia. Aoi.

As a leader, we should be aware of any updates and information related to the organization, but it is not necessary to get to all the things, including the small ones that we want to know.

Text:
Benda ni tak menguntungkan sesiapa pun.

Leader akan hilang fokus kalau terlalu micromanage, pekerja pula akan rasa tak bermotivasi nak bekerja di bawah pengurusan yang tak percaya dgn kemampuan diorg.

So, percayalah team korang, korang kan dah lantik yang terbaik!
Translated Text:
This thing does not benefit anyone.

Leaders will lose focus if they micromanage too much, and employees will feel unmotivated to work under management that does not believe in their abilities.

So, trust your team, you have appointed the best!

Text:
Jadi, ada 4 tips nak fokus untuk seorang leader. 

Saya summarizekan di bawah ya; 

1. Tidur awal dan bangun awal
2. Increase mental fokus
3. Set priority
4. Jangan micromanage

Jangan lupa follow @FezzaHussin tau. Hehe
Translated Text:
So, there are 4 tips to focus on a leader.

I'll summarize it below;

1. Go to bed early and wake up early
2. Increase mental focus
3. Set priorities
4. Don't micromanage

Don't forget to follow @FezzaHussin you know. Haha

Text:
1. Belas kasihan

Sifat ni ditunjukkan oleh Nabi SAW dalam banyak hal dan perkara.

Ketika berhadapan dengan musuh yg mencela, meracun & cuba utk membunuh Nabi pun, baginda masih lagi melayan mereka dengan baik.
Translated Text:
1. Compassion

This trait was shown by the Prophet SAW in many ways and things.

When faced with an enemy who criticizes, poisons & tried to kill the Prophet, he still treated them well.

Text:
Tidak pernah walau sekali Nabi ﷺ  berdendam dengan sesiapa yang buat salah pd baginda.

Dan menariknya, sifat ni bukan hanya untuk org muslim, mereka yang tak beriman pun dilayan dengan sifat serupa.

Hebat kan Nabi?
Translated Text:
Never even once did the Prophet ﷺ have a grudge against anyone who wronged him.

And interestingly, this trait is not only for Muslims, those who do not believe are also treated with similar traits.

Is the Prophet great?

Text:
2. Ambil berat tentang orang yg lemah

Kata Nabi SAW,

"Sesiapa yang meringankan daripada seorang mukmin satu kesusahan daripada kesusahan-kesusahan dunia, Allah SWT akan meringankan daripadanya satu kesusahan daripada kesusahan di Hari Kiamat..." (HR Muslim, 2699)
Translated Text:
2. Take care of the weak

The Prophet SAW said,

"Whoever relieves a believer of one hardship from the hardships of the world, Allah SWT will alleviate from him one hardship from the hardships of the Day of Resurrection..." (HR Muslim, 2699)

Text:
Nabi SAW bukan saja memberi galakan dalam bentuk lisan, bahkan Nabi SAW sendiri mengamalkan apa yang disabdakan baginda.

Walaupun baginda sendiri dalam keadaan lapar, beliau tetap mengutamakan insan lain yg memerlukan.

Hebatnya akhlak baginda.
Translated Text:
The Prophet SAW not only gave encouragement in verbal form, even the Prophet SAW himself practiced what he said.

Even though he himself is hungry, he still prioritizes other people in need.

His morals are great.

Text:
3. Adil

Ada satu hari, sahabat baginda Nabi ﷺ datang bertanya tentang hadiah yang cuma diberi kepada seorang anaknya.

 Nabi ﷺ bertanya,

Adakah anak-anak yang lain kau berikan hadiah yang sama seperti ini?
Translated Text:
3. Fair

One day, a friend of the Prophet ﷺ came to ask about a gift that was only given to one of his children.

 The Prophet ﷺ asked,

Do you give other children the same gift as this?

Text:
Bapanya menjawab,

Tidak.

Lalu Nabi Muhammad ﷺ berkata,

Bertakwalah kepada Allah dan berlakulah adil terhadap kesemua anakmu.
Translated Text:
His father replied,

Nope.

Then Prophet Muhammad ﷺ said,

Fear God and be fair to all your children.

Text:
4. Dipercayai

Baginda Nabi ﷺ digelar al-Amin & al-Sadiq.

Malah, waktu ketika mereka menafikan keimanan mereka pun mereka masih tetap mengaku bahawa Nabi ﷺ merupakan insan yg dipercayai.
Translated Text:
4. Trusted

His Majesty the Prophet ﷺ is called al-Amin & al-Sadiq.

In fact, even when they deny their faith, they still confess that the Prophet ﷺ is a trustworthy person.

Text:
5. Libatkan orang lain dalam proses decision-making

Korang tahu, waktu Perang Khandak, yang cadangan menggali parit itu bukan dari baginda Nabi SAW, tetapi dicadangkan oleh Salman al-Farisi.

Turn out, strategi peperangan itu membuahkan hasil.

Text:
1. Audit

Audit apa?

Audit tahap social media presence kita. 

Especially untuk yang dah pernah try marketkan produk guna social media.

Apa yang kita nak audit?
Translated Text:
1. Audit

What audit?

Audit the level of our social media presence.

Especially for those who have tried marketing products using social media.

What do we want to audit?

Text:
Antara perkara yg you guys patut tengok:

- Platform apa yg bisnes korang aktif?

- For each platform, dah fully optimize atau belum? 

- Platform yg mana yg plg bernilai?

- Compare profile kita dengan pesaing.

Ini few ideas lah. Kalau lagi detail lg bgs.
Translated Text:
Among the things you guys should see:

- What platform is your business active on?

- For each platform, is it fully optimized or not yet?

- Which platform is the most valuable?

- Compare our profile with competitors.

These are a few ideas. If you have more details, please let me know.

Text:
2. Kenalpasti customer

Benda ni memang paling crucial untuk determine our priority untuk buat marketing.

For me, untuk part ni kita mesti buat as spesific as possible.
Translated Text:
2. Get to know the customer

This thing is indeed the most crucial for determining our priority for marketing.

For me, for this part, we have to make it as specific as possible.

Text:
Untuk kenalpasti customer kita, ada beberapa soalan yg perlu kita tanya:

- Umur
- Location
- Pekerjaan
- Income
- Problem (yg diselesaikan oleh bisnes kita)
- Platform social media yg diorg aktif
Translated Text:
To identify our customers, there are several questions we need to ask:

- Age
- Location
- Employment
- Income
- Problems (solved by our business)
- Active social media platforms

Text:
Kalau you guys nak lagi detail, korang boleh try google Customer Persona.

Ada template yg kita boleh guna utk determine audiens bisnes kita.
Translated Text:
If you guys want more details, you can try google Customer Persona.

There is a template that we can use to determine our business audience.

Text:
3. Kenalpasti metrik KPI

Antara beberapa metrik yg kita boleh gunakan untuk ukur performance social media marketing kita, antaranya:

- Conversion rate
- Reach
- Mentions
- Sentiment
- Total share
Translated Text:
3. Identify KPI metrics

Some of the metrics that we can use to measure our social media marketing performance include:

- Conversion rates
-Reach
- Mentions
- Sentiments
- Total shares

Text:
Penting untuk kita determine metrik ni sebab apa?

Sebab kita boleh tahu apa yg kita buat tu berhasil atau tak.

Kalau takde improvement dalam metrik yg kita listkan, mungkin ada benda yg kita tersilap buat.
Translated Text:
Why is it important for us to determine this metric?

Because we can know whether what we do is successful or not.

If there is no improvement in the metrics we list, there may be something we did wrong.

Text:
Learn, unlearn, relearn.

Repeat the process sampai kita berjaya.

After all, itu jelah secret recipe kebanyakan org yg berjaya kan. Hehe
Translated Text:
Learn, unlearn, relearn.

Repeat the process until we succeed.

After all, that's the secret recipe of most successful people, right? Hehe

Text:
4. Create & Curate

So now, kita dah buat beberapa step.

Kita dah audit, dah tahu customer kita, dah tahu metrik kita nak ukur.

Apa lagi tunggu?
Translated Text:
4. Create & Curate

So now, we have done several steps.

We have audited, we know our customers, we know the metrics we want to measure.

What are you waiting for?

Text:
Fokus pada penghasilan content yg berkualiti & berkuantiti.

For me, dua2 benda ni penting.

Setiap hari, berbillion content yang diproduce.

High quality content always win if we know how to distribute it.
Translated Text:
Focus on producing quality & quantity.

For me, these two things are important.

Every day, billions of content are produced.

High quality content always wins if we know how to distribute it.

Text:
Antara jenis konten yg kita boleh buat:

- Gambar 
- Video
- Blog post
- Infographics 
- Interview
- Thread
Translated Text:
Among the types of content we can create:

- Pictures
- Videos
- Blog posts
- Infographics
- Interview
- Thread

Text:
5. Track, analyse & optimize

“In God we trust, all others must bring data.” - W. E. Deming

Data sangat penting untuk kita keep track effort kita ni sebenarnya berbaloi ke tak. Haha
Translated Text:
5. Track, analyze & optimize

"In God we trust, all others must bring data." - W.E. Deming

Data is very important for us to keep track of our efforts, is it really worth it or not. Ha ha

Text:
In which platform, our business doing very well.

Konten apa yg people suka.

Gaya bahasa yg mana boleh tarik lebih banyak audiens.

Semua tu kena tengok pada data.
Translated Text:
In which platform, our business is doing very well.

What content do people like?

Which style of language can attract more audience.

Everything has to be looked at in the data.

Text:
That’s why, kita determine metrik awal2 tadi.

Daripada data yg kita dapat, kita boleh analyze dan buat beberapa kesimpulan awal.

Bila dah buat early conclusion, kita optimize mana yg patut.
Translated Text:
That's why, we determined the metrics earlier.

From the data we get, we can analyze and make some preliminary conclusions.

When we have made an early conclusion, we optimize which one is appropriate.

Text:
So ada 5 point yg utk plan social media marketing:

1. Audit
2. Kenalpasti customer
3. Kenalpasti metrik KPI
4. Create & Curate
5. Track, analyse & optimize

Hopefully thread ni bermanfaat utk you guys. 

Jangan lupa follow @FezzaHussin untuk tips berkenaan marketing lagi.

So there are 5 points for a social media marketing plan:

Text:
1. Product

Produk ni kita fahamlah, maksudnya apa-apa produk atau servis yang kita nak offer kat customer.

Fokus utama apa pun produk yg kita nak jual, mestilah solve masalah yg dihadapi oleh bakal customer kita.
Translated Text:
1. Product

We understand this product, it means any product or service that we want to offer to customers.

The main focus of whatever product we want to sell, must be to solve the problems faced by our potential customers.

Text:
Ramai orang terlampau fokus pada produk apa yg nak dijual. Bg saya, better start dgn ambil tahu masalah yg dihadapi oleh bakal customer kita.

Then dari situ baru kita create product yg boleh solve masalah tu.

Takdelah syok sendiri kan. Hehe
Translated Text:
Many people focus too much on what product to sell. For me, it's better to start by finding out the problems faced by our potential customers.

Then from there we create a product that can solve that problem.

Don't be shocked yourself. Hehe

Text:
2. Price

Okay, produk dah ada. So, berapa kita nak jual?

Sebelum letak harga, kena ambil kira segala kos, implisit & eksplisit.

Kos bahan mentah, kos per unit, kos marketing, kos logistik, gaji staf dan etc.
Translated Text:
2. Price

Okay, the product is available. So, how much do we want to sell?

Before setting the price, you have to take into account all costs, implicit & explicit.

Raw material cost, cost per unit, marketing cost, logistics cost, staff salary and etc.

Text:
Janganlah main sedap je.

Pastu, comparekan harga kita dengan harga pesaing. Kompetitif tak? Adakah wajar harga kita tu sebagai pilihan alternatif pelanggan?

Okay je harga lagi mahal, tapi value yg kita provide mesti lagi bagus daripada competitor lah. Hehe.
Translated Text:
Don't play nice.

Then, compare our prices with competitors' prices. Is it competitive? Is our price reasonable as an alternative option for customers?

It's okay, the price is expensive, but the value we provide must be better than the competitors. Hehe.

Text:
3. Place

Okay, produk dah ada. Harga done. So, nak jual kat mana ni?

Nak jual online, offline ke dua2?

Bagi saya, most of the business boleh manfaatkan internet untuk cari customer. Kan?
Translated Text:
3. Place

Okay, the product is available. Done price. So, where do you want to sell it?

Want to sell both online and offline?

For me, most of the business can use the internet to find customers. Right?

Text:
Rancang betul-betul cara untuk marketkan produk korang.
Fokus one at a time.

Nak start online ke offline ke, dua2 pun okay. Cuma pastikan ada ilmu dan terus praktikkan. Tau!

Tapi musim skrg ni better focus online. Musim2 covid ni. hehe
Translated Text:
Plan exactly how to market your product.
Focus one at a time.

Want to start online or offline, both are okay. Just make sure you have knowledge and keep practicing. You know!

But this season it's better to focus online. This covid season. lol

Text:
4. Promotion

Last but not least, bila dah jelas produk, harga dan place, bolehlah mulakan kempen-kempen marketing yang nak dibuat!

Di sinilah segala idea kreatif kena sentiasa mengalir untuk make sure orang kenal dengan produk/servis kita.
Translated Text:
4. Promotion

Last but not least, when the product, price and place are clear, you can start the marketing campaigns you want to make!

This is where all creative ideas have to flow to make sure people are familiar with our products/services.

Text:
Bila orang kenal, barulah ada trust.

Bila dah ada trust, barulah ada sales.

Bila ada sales, barulah ada revenue.

Haaa barulah boleh jadi jutawan bergambar depan Mustang. Hahahaha. Gurau je.
Translated Text:
When people know each other, then there is trust.

When there is trust, then there is sales.

When there is sales, then there is revenue.

Haaa then you can become a millionaire posing in front of a Mustang. Hahahaha. Just kidding.

Text:
But joke aside, marketing memang sangat penting tau.

Takde marketing, macam mana kita nak dapat jualan kan?

Banyak je free resources untuk belajar pasal online marketing ni. Rajin tak rajin je nak google. haha
Translated Text:
But joke aside, marketing is very important you know.

No marketing, how are we going to get sales right?

There are lots of free resources to learn about online marketing. Diligent is not diligent enough to google. ha ha

Text:
So ada 4 elemen penting dalam marketing ni. Ingat tau 4P ni, Product, Price, Place dan Promotion. 

Kenalah pandai-pandai gunakan 4 elemen ni dalam strategi marketing korang nanti.

All the best!

Jangan lupa follow @FezzaHussin pls. Nanti saya belanja tips marketing lagi.

Be smart about using these 4 elements in your marketing strategy later.

All the best!

Text:
1. Campaign

Campaign ni benda first yg kena tetapkan sebelum benda lain. Campaign dalam Adwords boleh ada banyak ad groups.

Dalam satu campaign dia akan share budget yang sama, campaign type & beberapa setting iklan yang lain.
Translated Text:
1. Campaign

The campaign is the first thing that needs to be decided before anything else. Campaigns in Adwords can have many ad groups.

In one campaign he will share the same budget, campaign type & some other ad settings.

Text:
Dalam satu akaun, boleh ada beberapa campaign yang run serentak.

Contoh, 

Ada satu campaign iklan untuk jual baju raya.

Ada satu campaign iklan untuk jual kuih raya.

Takde masalah, ok?
Translated Text:
In one account, there can be several campaigns running simultaneously.

For example,

There is an advertising campaign to sell raya clothes.

There is an advertising campaign to sell Kuih Raya.

No problem, ok?

Text:
2. Ad groups

Dalam campaign tadi, boleh ada banyak ad groups pulak.

Contoh tadi kita ada dua campaign kan:

1. Untuk baju raya
2. Untuk kuih raya
Translated Text:
2. Ad groups

In the campaign, there can be many ad groups.

For example, we have two campaigns, right:

1. For Raya clothes
2. For Eid cakes

Text:
Dalam campaign baju raya, boleh ada beberapa ad group pula, contohnya:

Ad group 1: Baju raya wanita
Ad group 2: Baju raya lelaki
Ad group 3: Baju raya kanak-kanak
Translated Text:
In the baju raya campaign, there can be several ad groups as well, for example:

Ad group 1: Women's raya shirts
Ad group 2: Raya shirts for men
Ad group 3: Children's Raya shirts

Text:
Dalam campaign kuih raya, boleh ada beberapa ad group juga, contohnya:

Ad group 1: Kuih raya - biskut
Ad group 2: Kuih raya - kerepek
Ad group 3: Kuih raya - viral
Translated Text:
In the kuih raya campaign, there can be several ad groups as well, for example:

Ad group 1: Kuih raya - biscuits
Ad group 2: Kuih raya - chips
Ad group 3: Kuih raya - viral

Text:
Atas ni contoh je okay. Korang pandai2 lah fikir sendiri. Hehe

So dalam ad group, kita set keyword, budget and targetting method yang sama.

Dalam campaign ada bajet. Dalam ad group pun ada bajet.
Translated Text:
Above is an example, it's okay. You are good at thinking for yourself. Hehe

So in the ad group, we set the same keyword, budget and targeting method.

In the campaign there is a budget. Even in ad groups there is a budget.

Text:
3. Campaign type

Campaign type ni basically korang nak iklan korang tu appear kat mana.

Google ni ada dua tempat yang iklan korang boleh appear:

1. Search engine

2. Google display network
Translated Text:
3. Campaign type

This type of campaign is basically where you want your ad to appear.

Google has two places where your ad can appear:

1. Search engines

2. Google display network

Text:
Search engine ni, bila kita cari certain keyword, akan keluar iklan dekat bahagian atas/bawah tu.

Google display network ni, bila kita browse certain website, blog, Youtube ada keluar iklan kan?

Haa, yang tu lah.
Translated Text:
This search engine, when we search for a certain keyword, an advertisement will appear near the top/bottom.

This is the Google display network, when we browse certain websites, blogs, YouTube ads come out right?

Ha, that's it.

Text:
So basically campaign type ni ada 3:

1. Search network only
2. Display network only
3. Search network with display select 

So mana yg sesuai dengan bisnes korang?
Translated Text:
So basically campaign type ni ada 3:

1. Search network only
2. Display network only
3. Search network with display select 

So mana yg sesuai dengan bisnes korang?

Text:
4. Keywords

Keyword ni antara benda penting bila kita setup iklan. Kalau korang pernah setup FB ads, atau apa2 ads lain, mesti pernah jumpa jugak kan.

So benda ni akan menentukan iklan korang tu appear kat mana.

Kalau jual biskut raya, takkanlah keyword kita baiki kereta kan.
Translated Text:
4. Keywords

This keyword is one of the most important things when we set up ads. If you have ever setup FB ads, or any other ads, you must have seen it.

So this thing will determine where your ad appears.

If we sell Raya cookies, we won't use the keyword to fix cars, right?

Text:
Macam mana nak cari keyword yang bagus?

Google sendiri ada bagi basic tips untuk build keyword list.

Korang boleh baca kat sini: https://t.co/hpuDCQhhHs
Translated Text:
How to find good keywords?

Google itself has basic tips for building a keyword list.

You can read it here: https://t.co/hpuDCQhhHs

Text:
5. Impressions

Impression ni maksudnya berapa banyak iklan korang ditunjukkan kepada audiens.

Kena ingat, bukan kita sorang je beriklan. Jadi walaupun 100K orang cari keyword yg kita setup, tak semestinya iklan kita je yg keluar eh. Hahah
Translated Text:
5. Impressions

Impression means how many of your ads are shown to the audience.

Remember, we are not the only ones advertising. So even if 100K people search for the keyword we set up, it's not necessarily our ads that come out. Hahaha

Text:
6. Ad Rank

Ad rank ni nilai yang digunakan untuk determine iklan korang tu letaknya kat mana. Ada dua faktor utama yang menentukan ad rank ni:

1. Quality score
2. Bid amount
Translated Text:
6. Ad Rank

Ad rank is the value used to determine where your ad is located. There are two main factors that determine this ad rank:

1. Quality score
2. Bid amount

Text:
Makin tinggi bid, makin tinggi possibility untuk iklan korang tu appear dekat top.

Biasalah, nak tempat sedap kena bayar mahal lah kan? Hahahah
Translated Text:
The higher the bid, the higher the possibility for your ad to appear near the top.

It's normal, if you want a good place you have to pay a lot, right? Hahahah

Text:
1. Jangan pernah give up

Elon Musk kata apa?

“I’d have to be dead or completely incapacitated to give up.”

Mati atau menang. 

Putus asa bukan dalam kamus kita. Ok? Fuhh
Translated Text:
1. Never give up

What did Elon Musk say?

"I'd have to be dead or completely incapacitated to give up."

Die or win.

Despair is not in our dictionary. OK? Fuhh

Text:
2. Do what you love or Love what you do

Apa Elon kata?

“It’s really important to like what you do if you don’t like it, life is too short.”

After all, hidup ni bukan lama mana pun kan.

Asalkan apa yang kita buat tu boleh bawa ke syurga. why not? Hurm.
Translated Text:
2. Do what you love or Love what you do

What did Elon say?

"It's really important to like what you do if you don't like it, life is too short."

After all, life is not that long, right?

As long as what we do can take us to heaven. why not? Humm.

Text:
3. Ambil risiko!! 

Lagi2 untuk orang muda macam kita ni. Cehh. 

Elon kata apa?

“Take risks now and do something bold, you won’t regret it.”

Sebelum ada komitmen yang lebih besar, why not kita try ambil risiko untuk do something crazy & insane? 250 juta setahun ckp gila x?
Translated Text:
3. Take risks!!

Again for young people like us. Cehh.

Elon said what?

"Take risks now and do something bold, you won't regret it."

Before there is a bigger commitment, why don't we try to take the risk to do something crazy & insane? 250 million a year is crazy x?

Text:
4. Benda tu penting? Buat guys! Do it!

“If something is important enough you should try even if the probable outcome is failure.”

Walaupun gagal, kalau benda tu penting dia akan tetap memberi impak kepada masyarakat, negara atau dunia.

Betul tak?
Translated Text:
4. Is that important? Make it guys! Do it!

"If something is important enough you should try even if the probable outcome is failure."

Even if he fails, if that thing is important, he will still have an impact on the community, the country or the world.

Right?

Text:
5. Work super duper hard 

Siapa tak tahu Elon punya gaya kerja kan. ahaha

“If you do the simple math, if somebody else is working 50 hours and you are working 100, you’ll get twice as much done in the course of a year as the other company.”

Well, make sense la kan.
Translated Text:
5. Work super duper hard 

Siapa tak tahu Elon punya gaya kerja kan. ahaha

Text:

“A lot of times an entrepreneur will come up with something that is just slightly better, and it can’t just be slightly better, it’s got to be a lot better.”

Tugas kita lah tu utk create product yg solve masalah. Haha

6. Hasilkan produk yang superbbb

“A lot of times an entrepreneur will come up with something that is just slightly better, and it can’t just be slightly better, it’s got to be a lot better.”

“Are these efforts that people are undergoing resulting in a better product or service? If they’re not, stop those efforts.”

Even kalau ramai orang buat tapi tak menyumbang apa2, kenapa kita kena buat juga? Tinggalkan

Text:
Kisah ni adalah dlm 9 tahun lepas, 2012.

Malala Yousafzai masa tu berumur 15 tahun je.

Bas yang Malala ni naik untuk balik rumah, diberhentikan oleh geng-geng Taliban.
Translated Text:
This story is in the last 9 years, 2012.

Malala Yousafzai was only 15 years old at that time.

The bus Malala took to go home was stopped by Taliban gangs.

Text:
Seorang lelaki dengan topeng bersama senapang naik keatas bas dan tanya, 

Siapa Malala?

Kawan2 dia pun pandang kearah Malala.

Lelaki tu terus melulu kepada Malala dan melepaskan tembakan.
Translated Text:
A man in a mask with a gun got on the bus and asked,

Who is Malala?

His friends also looked at Malala.

The man continued recklessly towards Malala and opened fire.

Text:
Tembakan kena pada bahagian kiri kepalanya dan terus sampai ke leher.

Selain Malala, ada dua orang lagi remaja perempuan yang turut cedera dalam kejadian tu. Fuhh

Nak menangis bila terbayang. Ni bukan drama cintan cintun. Ni real case
Translated Text:
The shot hit the left side of his head and continued to the neck.

Apart from Malala, there are two other teenage girls who were also injured in the incident. Phew

I want to cry when I think about it. This is not a love drama. This is a real case

Text:
Tahu ke kenapa dia ditembak?

Sebab kelantangan dia memperjuangkan hak pendidikan untuk wanita di Pakistan.
Translated Text:
Do you know why he was shot?

Because of the volume she fought for the right to education for women in Pakistan.

Text:
Masa tahun 2008, Taliban mula attack beberapa sekolah perempuan di Swat, Pakistan.

Kalau korang google gambar dekat Swat ni cantik gila weh. 

Bila Taliban attack, Malala ni sampaikan satu ucapan bertajuk:

How dare the Taliban take away my basic right to education?
Translated Text:
In 2008, the Taliban began to attack several girls' schools in Swat, Pakistan.

If you google pictures near Swat, it's crazy beautiful.

When the Taliban attacked, Malala delivered a speech entitled:

How dare the Taliban take away my basic right to education?

Text:
Masa tu dia umur berapa?

Baru 10 tahun weh. 

Masa umur 11 tahun dia mula blogging untuk BBC. Tapi guna nama samaran sebab tak nak geng2 Taliban ni tahu. Nama samaran dia Gul Makai.

Tapi sekejap je identiti tu rahsia.
Translated Text:
How old was he then?

It's only been 10 years.

When he was 11 years old, he started blogging for the BBC. But use a pseudonym because you don't want the Taliban gangs to know. His nickname is Gul Makai.

But for a moment the identity is a secret.

Text:
Bulan Disember 2009, identiti Gul Makai dah bocor weh

Bila diorang dapat tahu, berpuluh ancaman bunuh yang family Malala ni terima.

Tapi diorang masih berpegang pada prinsip. 

Satu lagi, diorang percaya yang fundamentalist group ni takkan mengancam nyawa kanak-kanak.
Translated Text:
In December 2009, Gul Makai's identity was leaked

When people find out, dozens of death threats have been received by Malala's family.

But people still stick to principles.

Another thing, people believe that this fundamentalist group will not threaten children's lives.

Text:
Tapi diorang silap.

Tahun 2012, Malala diserang dan berada dalam keadaan kritikal selama beberapa bulan.

Tengkorak kepalanya dialihkan, sistem saraf bahagian muka rosak, paralyzed di bahagian kiri muka.

Hampir membunuh Malala yang kita kenal hari ni.
Translated Text:
But people are wrong.

In 2012, Malala was attacked and was in critical condition for several months.

His skull was removed, the nervous system of the face was damaged, he was paralyzed on the left side of his face.

Almost killed the Malala we know today.

Text:
Tahun lepas, Malala grad daripada Oxford University dengan degree in philosophy, politics and economics.

Sebenarnya begitulah dahsyatnya semangat orang muda ni.
Translated Text:
Last year, Malala graduated from Oxford University with a degree in philosophy, politics and economics.

Actually, that's how terrible the spirit of these young people is.

Text:
Walaupun baru belia waktu dia perjuangkan apa yang dia percaya, tapi dia mampu menggegarkan ideologi sebuah kumpulan pengganas.

Sampai diorang nak bunuh dia.
Translated Text:
Although he was only a youth when he fought for what he believed in, he was able to shake the ideology of a terrorist group.

Until someone wants to kill him.

Text:
Sebab tu penting untuk develop youth ni.

Bila youth ni didevelop dgn prinsip dan ideologi yang sempurna, negara dan ummat akan dpt manfaat.

Itulah apa yang @MyFundAction & @yoshvolunteer cuba buat hari ni.

So kalau korang kenal mana-mana belia, refer kat kitorang eh. Hahaha
Translated Text:
That's why it's important to develop this youth.

When this youth is developed with perfect principles and ideology, the country and the community will benefit.

That's what @MyFundAction & @yoshvolunteer tried to do it today.

So if you know any youth, refer to us. Haha

Text:
Bila masuk je rumah, rasa nak nangis weh.

Pijak je karpet, basah stokin ni. Ingatkan ada air tumpah ke, bila pandang atas rupanya atap rumah yang bocor.

Waktu tu pulak musim hujan, memang berlecak habis rumah. Huhu
Translated Text:
When I enter the house, I feel like crying.

Step on the carpet, get these socks wet. Remember that there is spilled water, when you look at the roof of the house it looks like it is leaking.

At that time it was rainy season, the house was really wet. Huh

Text:
Nenek ni dah umur 70 tahun, nak jalan pun susah.

Bukan takat nak uruskan rumah, nak uruskan diri sendiri pun perlukan tenaga. Bertambah pula dengan 2 orang anak istimewa. 

Tak dapat nak bayangkan macam mana kalau saya di posisi makcik ni. Fuh
Translated Text:
This grandmother is 70 years old, it's hard to even walk.

It's not just about taking care of the house, taking care of yourself also requires energy. In addition to having 2 special children.

I can't imagine what it would be like if I were in this aunt's position. Phew

Text:
Tapi makcik ni baik, hebat orangnya.

Sepanjang kami berbual, tak dgr langsung keluhan

Tak pernah dia kata anak istimewa menyusahkan dia.

Tak pernah dia salahkan Tuhan atas ujianNya.

Jauh sekali nak menyalahkan kami yang terlambat berjumpa dengan dia.
Translated Text:
But this aunt is good, she is a great person.

As long as we talked, there were no complaints

He never said that special children made him difficult.

He never blamed God for His trials.

Far from blaming us for being late to meet him.

Text:
Bila ditanya apa yg dia perlukan, cukup sederhana permintaannya.

Sekadar sehelai dua kain sarung tambahan.

Menitik air mata kami mendengar satu-satunya permintaan dia.
Translated Text:
When asked what he needed, his request was quite simple.

Just two extra sheets of sarong cloth.

Dropping tears we heard his only request.

Text:
Bukan ke patutnya dia minta kami baikikan rumah sekali?

Atau setidaknya, suruhlah kami belikan makanan untuk sebulan dua?
Translated Text:
Shouldn't he ask us to fix the house once?

Or at least, tell us to buy food for a month or two?

Text:
Dan nescaya Kami akan menguji kalian dengan sedikit daripada perasaan takut, rasa lapar, kekurangan harta benda, kehilangan nyawa (kematian), serta tumbuh-tumbuhan dan berikanlah khabar gembira kepada orang-orang yang bersabar.

[2:155]
Translated Text:
And surely We will test you with a little of fear, hunger, lack of property, loss of life (death), and plants and give glad tidings to those who are patient.

[2:155]

Text:
1. Pamplet & flyers

Pamplet & flyers ni masih lagi berkesan walaupun dah tahun 2021. Hahahha

Esp kalau kita punya nature bisnes tu bersifat setempat.

Mcm bengkel motor/kereta, or taska/tadika ke.
Translated Text:
1. Pamphlets & flyers

Pamphlets & These flyers are still effective even though it's 2021. Hahahha

Especially if we have a local business nature.

Like a motorcycle/car workshop, or a nursery/kindergarten.

Text:
Cepat kena sasaran setempat & sampaikan mesej dengan jelas. 

Pernah buat tapi tak berkesan?

So try semak balik, mungkin content kita kurang menarik, atau copywriting tak ok kot.  

Tbh, saya rasa marketing guna pamplet ni cara yang murah & masih relevant kot.
Translated Text:
Quickly hit the local target & convey the message clearly.

Ever done it but it didn't work?

So try to check back, maybe our content is less interesting, or the copywriting is not ok.

Tbh, I think marketing using pamphlets is a cheap way & still relevant.

Text:
2. Business card

Esp for agen2. Tak kiralah agen hartanah ke, agen takaful ke, agen kereta ke. Hahah

Kadang jumpa org, borak2 kat kedai makan. Sembang2 sikit & hulur business card terus dia macam, eh memang saya tengah cari ni.

Haa! Haha
Translated Text:
2. Business card

Especially for agents. It doesn't matter whether it's a real estate agent, a takaful agent, or a car agent. Hahaha

Sometimes I meet people, chat at restaurants. Chat a little & Hold out your business card and he's like, eh, I'm really looking for this.

Ha! Haha

Text:
Try bayangkan kita tak bawak business card. Lepas sembang maybe awkward kalau tetiba mintak no telefon.

Kalau ada business card kita boleh exchange. Atau kalau orang tu takde pun, at least kita boleh bagi kita punya.

Manalah tahu dia memang mencari kan.
Translated Text:
Try to imagine that we don't bring a business card. After the chat, maybe it's awkward if you suddenly ask for a phone number.

If there is a business card we can exchange. Or if that person doesn't even exist, at least we can give them to us.

How do you know he's really looking for it?

Text:
3. Bagi kupon/baucar

Baru buka kedai baru?

Nak promosikan servis baru?

Boleh mula promosi dengan bagi kupon atau baucar. Tapi janganlah sampai korang pula rugi! Buat kira2 sikit, ok?
Translated Text:
3. For coupons/vouchers

Just opened a new store?

Want to promote a new service?

Can start promotion by giving coupons or vouchers. But don't let yourself lose! Do some math, okay?

Text:
Nak lagi menarik, bahagikan baucar tu mengikut lokaliti/kawasan.

How?

Katalah baru buka kedai makan dekat satu tempat. Dekat tempat ni ada 5 taman perumahan berdekatan.

Edarkan baucar ke semua rumah tu. Tapi setiap taman gunakan colour kertas yg berbeza.
Translated Text:
If you want to make it more interesting, divide the voucher according to locality/area.

How?

Say you just opened a restaurant near one place. Near this place there are 5 housing estates nearby.

Distribute vouchers to all the houses. But each garden uses a different paper color.

Text:
Nanti time opening, bila mereka datang & tebus baucar tu, kita boleh tahu diorang datang dari taman yang mana.

Untuk apa?

The next time, kita tahu nak fokus taman yang mana. Hehe
Translated Text:
Later opening time, when they come & Redeem the voucher, we can tell which park people came from.

For what?

The next time, we know which park to focus on. Hehe

Text:
4. Bagi kad & hadiah

Dah ada pelanggan?

Boleh try kaedah ni.

Bagi kad atau hadiah bila ada special occasion.

Contoh, birthday dia ke, new year, ramadan.
Translated Text:
4. For cards & gift

Do you have a customer?

You can try this method.

Give cards or gifts when there is a special occasion.

For example, his birthday, new year, Ramadan.

Text:
Haa semua boleh.

Cara ni boleh establish & kuatkan lagi relationship brand kita dengan customer. Lagi2 kalau pelanggan tu loyal customer kita.

Kalau dia sanggup habiskan ribuan ringgit untuk beli produk kita, apa salahnya kita bagi coklat waktu birthday dia kan?
Translated Text:
Yes, everyone can.

This way can establish & strengthen our brand relationship with customers. More if the customer is our loyal customer.

If he is willing to spend thousands of ringgit to buy our products, what's wrong with us giving him chocolates on his birthday, right?

Text:
5. Press release

Bagi saya PR ni sangat penting lagi2 kalau company kita dah mula membesar.

Tapi tbh, nak dapat coverage daripada media pun bukanlah mudah jugak. Kena ada win-win situation.
Translated Text:
5. Press releases

For me, PR is very important if our company has started to grow.

But tbh, getting coverage from the media is not easy either. There has to be a win-win situation.

Text:
Media bagi kita coverage.

Kita bagi media good story untuk dipublish.

Banyak je cara untuk buat marketing stunt yang disukai & boleh masuk newspaper semua. But please, jangan buat benda merepek lah. Hehe
Translated Text:
The media gives us coverage.

We give the media good stories to be published.

There are many ways to make a marketing stunt that you like & can enter all newspapers. But please, don't do something stupid. Hehe
