Text:
Bronnie Ware ni nurse kat Australia. Dia jaga bahagian palliative care. Ape tu? Hahah

Palliative care ni basically specialized medical care utk pesakit yg ada masalah penyakit kritikal.

So basically dia mmg berurusan dgn orang yang di penghujung hayat la kiranya.
Translated Text:
Bronnie Ware is a nurse in Australia. He takes care of the palliative care department. What's that? Hahaha

Palliative care is basically specialized medical care for patients with critical illness problems.

So basically he is dealing with people who are at the end of their lives.

Text:
1. Berharap ada keberanian utk menjalani hidup yang mereka nak berbanding hidup yang orang lain expect.

Actually dalam hidup ni mmg semua orang ada expectation pada diri kita.

Ada yang expect kita jadi doktor, ada yang expect kita jadi cikgu. Cehh
Translated Text:
1. Hoping to have the courage to live the life they want compared to the life others expect.

Actually, in this life, everyone has expectations of us.

Some expect us to become doctors, some expect us to become teachers. Cehh

Text:
Ada yang expect kita kerja bagai nak gila then lupa daratan.

Wajar ke mcm tu?

Cuba tanya diri kita sendiri apa yang kita betul2 nak dalam hidup ni?? Jawab dlm hati guys.
Translated Text:
Some people expect us to work like crazy and then forget the land.

Is that normal?

Try asking ourselves what do we really want in this life?? Answer in your heart guys.

Text:
2. Berharap tidak bekerja terlalu kuat.

Kata Bronnie Ware, semua pesakit lelaki berkongsi kekesalan yang sama. Huhu

Ramai yg jadikan pekerjaan sbgai tujuan hidup mereka sampai mengabaikan benda lain yang lebih penting dalam kehidupan.
Translated Text:
2. Hope not to work too hard.

According to Bronnie Ware, all male patients share the same regret. Huh

Many people make work the purpose of their lives to the point of neglecting other things that are more important in life.

Text:
Bukan nak kata kerja kuat tu tak bagus. Sy pun kerja kuat juga

Tapi kalau sampai abaikan benda & tanggungjawab yang lagi penting dalam kehidupan, then something wrong somewhere. 

We need to improve guys. Okey?
Translated Text:
I don't want to say that strong verbs are not good. I also work hard

But if you ignore things & more important responsibility in life, then something wrong somewhere.

We need to improve guys. okay?

Text:
3. Berharap ada keberanian untuk meluahkan perasaan

Ini bukan untuk crush eh. Hahhaha

Meluahkan perasaan ni boleh jadi pada mak, ayah, keluarga, kawan-kawan. Dont get me wrong
Translated Text:
3. Hope to have the courage to express feelings

This is not for crushes. Hahaha

Expressing these feelings can be to mom, dad, family, friends. Don't get me wrong

Text:
Try cek balik, dalam minggu ni atau bulan ni atau tahun ni, berapa kali kita call mak , ayah bagitahu yang kita sayang mereka? Huhu

Berapa ramai je yang bagitahu dekat kawan-kawan yang sebenarnya drg bermakna dalam hidup kita?
Translated Text:
Try to check back, in this week or this month or this year, how many times do we call mom, dad to tell them that we love them? Huh

How many people tell close friends who are really meaningful in our lives?

Text:
4. Berharap saya terus berhubung dengan kawan-kawan

Kata Bronnie Ware,

Often they would not truly realise the full benefits of old friends until their dying weeks and it was not always possible to track them down.
Translated Text:
4. Berharap saya terus berhubung dengan kawan-kawan

Kata Bronnie Ware,

Often they would not truly realise the full benefits of old friends until their dying weeks and it was not always possible to track them down.

Text:
Kadang kita ni bila dah sibuk sangat dengan macam2 benda dalam hidup, kita jadi lupa nak contact kawan-kawan yang dulu pernah tidur sebantal dengan kita. Haha

Yang tolong kita masa susah.
Yang angkat kita masa jatuh.
Yang bagi kita makan masa lapar. Fuh
Translated Text:
Sometimes when we are so busy with all kinds of things in life, we forget to contact friends who used to sleep with us. Haha

Who helps us in difficult times.
The one who lifts us when we fall.
Which for us to eat when we are hungry. Phew

Text:
Kenapa agaknya kita letak drg sebagai prioriti paling akhir dalam tangga yang perlu diingati sepanjang hayat kita?

Padehal diorang deserve more.

Tak ke? Hmm
Translated Text:
Why is it that we put drg as the last priority in the ladder that needs to be remembered for the rest of our lives?

In fact, people deserve more.

Isn't it? Hmmm

Text:
5. Berharap saya berikan ruang utk diri sendiri  lebih gembira & bahagia

Kebahagiaan ni pilihan guys.

Tapi kadang2 kita takut untuk buat pilihan tu.

Sebab pilihan tu bermaksud kita mungkin perlu lakukan sesuatu yang diluar expectation orang lain. Betul x?
Translated Text:
5. Hope I give myself space to be happier & happy

Happiness is a choice guys.

But sometimes we are afraid to make that choice.

Because that choice means we may have to do something that is beyond other people's expectations. Is that right?

Text:
Kita selalu fikir, apa org lain akn cakap, apa yang orang ni akan fikir.

Sampai kita lupa, 

Entah berapa banyak yang kita terluka sepanjang proses berfikir tentang orang lain ni, yang sebenarnya tak peduli pun pasal kita. Hahahh
Translated Text:
We always think, what other people will say, what this person will think.

Until we forget,

I don't know how much we are hurt throughout the process of thinking about other people, who actually don't even care about us. Hahah

Text:
Ramai org rasa, bahagia tu boleh diraih dengan berkongsi dengan orang yang memerlukan. 

Sy bahagia bila dpt bantu org. Kdg sy sengaja beli byk sikit kat gerai2 kecil. Bukan nk tnjuk byk duit. Klau korang tak pernah bisnes, susah mngkin nak faham.
Translated Text:
Many people feel that happiness can be achieved by sharing with people in need.

I am happy when I can help people. I deliberately bought a lot at small stalls. Not to show a lot of money. If you have never been in business, it may be difficult to understand.

Text:
Perasaan seorang peniaga, bila jualan habis, bila ramai customer, bila 1 customer beli byk. Senyum weh dlm hati. Bahagia bila ada rezeki lebih utk fmly. 

Itulah saya rasa. 

Saya harap saya boleh kongsi bahagia tu dgn mereka.
Translated Text:
The feeling of a trader, when the sale is sold out, when there are many customers, when 1 customer buys a lot. Smile in the heart. Happy when there is more sustenance for fmly.

That's what I think.

I hope I can share that happiness with them.

Text:
Kalau korang ada terfikir untuk berkongsi masa, tenaga & apa sahaja dengan mereka yang memerlukan, jomlah join kami di @MyFundAction.

Boleh join sebagai sukarelawan, aktivis atau apa saja.
Translated Text:
If you have thought of sharing time, energy & whatever with those in need, come join us at @MyFundAction.

Can join as a volunteer, activist or anything else.

Text:
Takde masa boleh kongsi rezeki, takde duit banyak, boleh kongsi tenaga, tak dpt bagi dua2, doakan boleh? Semoga sy dan team sentiasa ikhlas dan buat yg terbaik. Hee

Erti hidup pada memberi, jgn tunggu sempurna. Sebab kita mmg takkan sempurna.
Translated Text:
I don't have time to share sustenance, I don't have a lot of money, I can share energy, I can't share it, can I pray? May you and the team always be sincere and do your best. Hey

The meaning of life is to give, don't wait for perfection. Because we will never be perfect.

Text:
1 kebaikkan kita buat. Mampu mengukir 1000 senyuman. Ramadan bakal tiba ni, dah prepare ke nak plan 1 hari 1 kebaikkan? 

Tak pernah? Cuba la try buat this year! Hehe
Translated Text:
1 good thing we do. Able to carve 1000 smiles. Ramadan is coming, have you prepared to plan 1 day 1 to improve?

Never? Let's try it this year! Hehe

Text:
Tahun 1450

Bila ada moveable type ni, membantu dalam penghasilan mass printing.

Bila dah ada mass printing, company pun boleh start buat iklan guna teknologi ni.
Translated Text:
Year 1450

When there is this movable type, it helps in the production of mass printing.

When there is mass printing, the company can start making advertisements using this technology.

Text:
Tahun 1730-an

First majalah dilahir ke dunia. Haha dah mcm ape lahir2. 

Dekat mana lahir majalah ni? 

Di Philadelphia. 

So orang mula sumbat iklan dalam majalah pulak sebab lagi berkesan.
Translated Text:
The 1730s

First magazine was born into the world. Haha what is it like to be born?

Where was this magazine born?

In Philadelphia.

So people started stuffing ads in magazines because it was more effective.

Text:
1830-an: Poster pula popular. Tapi macam biasalah poster ni kan macam annoying. Annoyingnya sampai London ban poster ditampal tahun 1839. Hahah

1867: Billboard pertama disewa guys.

1830s: Posters are also popular. But as usual this poster is kind of annoying. Annoying that the poster tire was patched in London in 1839. Hahah

Text:
1922: Radio pula muncul hujung tahun 1921. Tahun 1922, pengiklanan dekat radio jadi popular pula.

1933: Dalam masa 11 tahun, 55.2% rumah dekat US ada radio.

1941: TV la pulak muncul. Haha Iklan kat TV lagi berkesan sbb ada audio & visual.
Translated Text:
1922: Radio appeared at the end of 1921. In 1922, advertising near the radio became popular as well.

1933: Within 11 years, 55.2% of homes in the US had a radio.

1941: TV appeared. Haha Ads on TV are more effective because there is audio & visual.

Text:
1954: So iklan dekat TV jadi sangat popular sampai kalahkan pengiklanan dekat radio & suratkhabar.

1970: Telemarketing muncul. Sampai skrg hidup lagi guys dia ni. Haha *ehem agen2
Translated Text:
1954: So advertising near TV became so popular that it beat advertising near radio & newspaper.

1970: Telemarketing appeared. Until now, these guys are alive again. Haha * ahem agents

Text:
1980-an: Teknologi printing yang advance, menyebabkan suratkhabar dapat dicetak dengan banyak dalam masa yang singkat. Kos pengiklan di suratkabar mencecah $25 billion pada tahun 1985!

1998: Ada syarikat invest $8.3 billion untuk iklan dekat TV je! Euh
Translated Text:
1980s: Advanced printing technology, causing newspapers to be printed in large quantities in a short time. The cost of advertising in newspapers reached $25 billion in 1985!

1998: There is a company that invests $8.3 billion for advertisements near TV only! Uh

Text:

Text:
1. Tunjuk pada staf yang kita perlukan mereka

Ni benda commen sense tapi ramai yang bila dah naik pangkat atau reach certain level terus lupa. Hahhah

Tapi ni lah antara rahsia dia.
Translated Text:
1. Show the staff that we need them

It's common sense but many people forget when they get promoted or reach a certain level. Hahaha

But this is one of his secrets.

Text:
Kita kena tunjukkan pada staf yang kita perlukan mereka.

CEO Wegmans selalu ingatkan pada staff dia,

“I don't know what you know, but I need what you know.”

Nampak macam simple, tapi penghargaan ni akan buat staf lagi bersemangat.
Translated Text:
We have to show the staff that we need them.

The CEO of Wegmans always reminds his staff,

"I don't know what you know, but I need what you know."

It seems simple, but this appreciation will make the staff more enthusiastic.

Text:
Wlwpun mmg kita as leader dah byk pengalaman, kita tahu apa masalah akan jdi, etc, tapi cuba la appreciate apa yang dia dah buat.

Biasakan dengar dulu idea staff, kalau ada kurang kita just top up, but at least bagi kredit la sikit apa yg dia dah buat. Ok?
Translated Text:
Even though we as leaders have a lot of experience, we know what problems will happen, etc., but try to appreciate what he has done.

Get used to listening to the staff's ideas first, if there is something lacking we just top up, but at least give him a little credit for what he has done. okay?

Text:
2. Jangan pilih kasih. Hahah

Dia selalu belanja coklat, jadi saya kena layan dia baik sikit.

NO!

Hahahahh
Translated Text:
2. Don't show favoritism. Hahaha

He always buys chocolates, so I have to treat him a little better.

NO!

Hahahah

Text:
Tapi kita ni kan manusia. Even mak bapak pun kadang ada anak favorite kan. Cia3... 

Sebab tu kdg2 kita kena stop kejap, & semak balik cara kita layan semua staf kita.

Adakah kita layan semua staf kita samarata atau kita ada beza-bezakan diorang?
Translated Text:
But we are human. Even mom and dad sometimes have a favorite child, right? Cia3...

That's why we have to stop for a moment, & review how we treat all our staff.

Do we treat all our staff equally or do we discriminate between people?

Text:
If ada beza-bezakan disebabkan favourite kita, stop. Benda ni tak sihat.

Kita kena assess semua staf based on performance dan trust. 

Kenapa performance dan trust?
Translated Text:
If there is a difference because our favorite, stop. This thing is not healthy.

We have to assess all staff based on performance and trust.

Why performance and trust?

Text:
Sy pernah ada experience orang tuduh sy suka dgn 1 staff ni sebab tu sy naikkan pangkat dia. Adoi haha nak tergolek bila ingat. 

Tapi sebenarnya saya tak suka pun. Saya naikkan pangkat sebab isu trust.
Translated Text:
I've had the experience of people accusing me of liking this one staff member because that's why I promoted him. I'm sorry haha ​​I want to roll over when I remember.

But actually I don't even like it. I promoted because of trust issues.

Text: Kita letak org jd leader kdg2 bukan sebab dia bagus sgt. Tapi sebab kita trust. Skill mcm mana bagus pun, kalau esok jd leader tahu nak songlap duit company je. Buat ape kan?
Translated Text: We put people to be our leaders not because they are very good. But because we trust. No matter how good your skills are, if you become a leader tomorrow, you know how to steal the company's money. What are you doing?

Text:
Baik la kita letak org kita percaya boleh jaga company dlm masa sama boleh grow company. 

Esok kalau kita takde, inshallah dia boleh bawa grow company lebih baik dari kita. Maybe? 

Tapi terpulang la kalian. Sy sekadar sharing ok?
Translated Text:
Well, we put people we believe can take care of the company at the same time we can grow the company.

Tomorrow if we are not there, inshallah he can bring a better grow company than us. Maybe?

But it's up to you. I'm just sharing ok?

Text:
3. Work hard & show it! 

Staf ni termotivasi kalau tengok leader diorang work hard atau super hard tahap dewa.

Kalau korang jenis masuk ofis pukul 12PM, pergi lunch, balik pukul 3. Masakkkk. Hahahah

Memang staf akan benci & jadi lagi malas lah citer dia. Lol
Translated Text:
3. Work hard & show it!

The staff is motivated when they see leaders who work hard or super hard at god level.

If you're the type to go to the office at 12PM, go to lunch, come back at 3. Cooking. Hahahah

Indeed the staff will hate & so he's too lazy to quote him. Lol

Text:
Org kata sy ni mcm takde life. Kdg tu masuk pukul 8 (sbb ada meeting) balik tu pukul 0000 H pernah, masa PKP tahun lepas lagi la jam 2-3 pagi kadang balik. Sebab last year struggle weh nak selamatkan department. hahah

Gila betul la kalau ingat balik. Eyebag tak usah cerita.
Translated Text:
People say that I have no life. I went in there at 8 o'clock (because there was a meeting) and came back at 0000 H once, during the MCO last year, it was at 2-3 in the morning sometimes. Because last year we struggled to save the department. hahah

It's crazy if you think back. Eyebag doesn't need to be told.

Text:
Kalau ada isu besar dalam department kita, lagilah kita kena ambil berat dan selesaikan cepat2.

Staf kena nampak yang kita ada dengan diorang, bukan kita kerja menghabiskan beras je. Hahaha adoi
Translated Text:
If there is a big issue in our department, we have to take it seriously and solve it quickly.

The staff has to see what we have with people, not that we work to finish the rice. Hahaha come on

Text:
4. Fix thing

Lagi2 kalau benda tu adalah issue yang besar yang boleh affect company punya performance.

Memang kita kena fix secepat mungkin! Huhu
Translated Text:
4. Fix things

Again, if that thing is a big issue that can affect the company's performance.

We really have to fix it as soon as possible! Huh

Text:
Kalau staf ada problem, kita panggil dia.

Cerita la apa kesalahan yang dia buat, then kita offer untuk hantar for consultation if needed lah. 

Kalau salah tu berkaitan benda2 teknikal, maka kita rujuk dia pada yang lebih pakar.

Tapi kita jangan biarkan dia terus buat silap tu.
Translated Text:
If the staff has a problem, we call him.

Tell him what he did wrong, then we offer to send him for consultation if needed.

If the mistake is related to technical things, then we refer him to a more expert.

But let's not let him continue to make that mistake.

Text:
Tapi, jangan la malukan diorang.

Sebab after all, macam selalu diulang-ulang; kita ni semua manusia.

Manusia mana yang terlepas daripada buat silap kan? Staff buat silap kita leader pun kdg sama.
Translated Text:
But, don't embarrass people.

Because after all, like it's always repeated; we are all human.

Which human is spared from making mistakes, right? The staff made the same mistake as the leader.

Text:
5. Always support your team

Biasa kita tengok kalau level manager/bos ni, selalu dalam meeting dia bolot semua pujian. Tapi bila ada silap, kena marah semua dia salahkan team dia. Hahahhah

Sy tak kata kita tak boleh marah/tegur staff. Tapi kena tgk gaya dan cara.
Translated Text:
5. Always support your team

We usually see that at this level of manager/boss, he always misses all the compliments in the meeting. But when something goes wrong, he gets angry and blames his team. Hahahahaha

I didn't say we can't get angry/scold the staff. But you have to look at the style and manner.

Text:
Kalau dlm presentation BOD, sy selalu guna perkataan “my team, kami dah rancang, focus kami, etc” sbb sy rasa apa yg dah kami plan adalah usaha “kami” bersama. Bukan sy sorang. 

Bagilah kredit pada orang yang patut terima pujian tu.
Translated Text:
In the BOD presentation, I always use the words "my team, we have planned, our focus, etc" because I feel that what we have planned is "our" joint effort. Not me alone.

Give credit to the people who deserve it.

Text:
Dan bila ada silap, patut kita kena take full responsibility & tegur kesilapan tu kalau staf kita yang buat.

Barulah staf sayang lebih & lagi bersemangat.
Translated Text:
And when there is a mistake, we should take full responsibility & Reprimand the mistake if our staff made it.

Only the staff love more & more enthusiastic

Text:
Okay, so ada 5 point ya!

1. Tunjuk pada staf yang kita perlukan mereka.
2. Jangan pilih kasih
3. Kerja keras & tunjukkan
4. Fix thing
5. Alway support your team

Setuju?

Kalau setuju, jangan lupa RT & follow @fezzahussin okay! Hahah
Translated Text:
Okay, so there are 5 points!

1. Show the staff that we need them.
2. Don't show favoritism
3. Hard work & show
4. Fix things

Agree?

Text:
1. Objektif tweet ditulis.

Pastikan setiap tweet atau thread yang korang tulis ada objektif atau sasaran yang korang nak capai.

Janganlah semua tweet korang balun nak buat sales. Adumak. Hahha
Translated Text:
1. The objective of the tweet is written.

Make sure every tweet or thread you write has an objective or target you want to achieve.

Don't all your tweets want to make sales. Adumak. Hahaha

Text:
Basically, objektif tweet ni ada 3: 

1. Tweet crowd
2. Tweet sales.
3. Tweet side.

Apa crowd, sale & side ni wehh? Hahah sabarr.
Translated Text:
Basically, objektif tweet ni ada 3: 

1. Tweet crowd
2. Tweet sales.
3. Tweet side.

Apa crowd, sale & side ni wehh? Hahah sabarr.

Text:
Tweet crowd adalah tweet untuk kumpulkan followers. 

Tweet sales literally untuk dapatkan jualan.

Tweet side just fun2 untuk dapatkan engagement.
Translated Text:
Tweet crowd is a tweet to collect followers.

Tweet sales literally to get sales.

Tweet side just fun2 to get engagement.

Text:
So disebabkan setiap tweet ada objektif tersendiri, kayu ukur untuk nilai setiap tweet itu berjaya atau tak pun berbeza.

Kalau tweet crowd macam mana korang nak kata yang dia berjaya? Bila followers korang bertambah.
Translated Text:
So because each tweet has its own objective, the yardstick for the value of each tweet is different.

If you tweet the crowd, how do you say that he is successful? When your followers increase.

Text:
Kalau tweet sales janganlah ukur berapa banyak RT yang dapat. Ukur berapa sales yang berjaya close.

Kalau tweet side, fokus untuk dapatkan engagement (rt/like/comment)
Translated Text:
If you tweet sales, don't measure how many RTs you get. Measure how many sales are successfully closed.

If tweet side, focus on getting engagement (rt/like/comment)

Text:
Kena buat semua jenis tweet ni ke?

Depends kat korang.

What is your short, medium, long term punya matlamat. 

Sebenarnya saya nak cakap buat je lah semua. Saja bagi jawapan selamat. Hehe
Translated Text:
Do you have to do all these types of tweets?

It depends on you.

What is your short, medium, long term goal?

Actually, I want to say just do it all. Just give a safe answer. Hehe

Text:
2. Kategori konten

Saya tengok, dekat twitter ada beberapa kategori tweet yang selalu viral.

Saya pecahkan kategori tweet ni kepada 4:

1. To educate
2. To inspire
3. To inform
4. To entertain
Translated Text:
2. Categories of content

I see, near Twitter there are several categories of tweets that are always viral.

I broke the category of this tweet into 4:

1. To educate
2. To inspire
3. To inform
4. To entertain

Text:
Kalau objektif tweet korang untuk crowd, saya cadangkan guna kategori tweet to educate & to inspire.

Untuk tweet sales, saya lebih suka kategori to inform untuk hard sales & to educate untuk soft sell.

Untuk tweet side, either guna to inform atau to entertain.
Translated Text:
If the objective of your tweets is for the crowd, I recommend using the category tweets to educate & to inspire.

For sales tweets, I prefer the to inform category for hard sales & to educate for soft selling.

For the tweet side, either use to inform or to entertain.

Text:
Saya rasa korang faham kot untuk kategori ni.

To educate ni biasanya koten yang berkongsi ilmu, bagi tips atau nasihat.

To inspire, kita ketengahkan tokoh untuk dijadikan inspirasi.
Translated Text:
I think you understand the coat for this category.

To educate is usually a quote that shares knowledge, gives tips or advice.

To inspire, we highlight figures to be used as inspiration.

Text:
To inform, untuk bagitahu. Contohnya nak bagitahu hari ni ada sale atau kes covid hari ni berapa.

To entertain, hiburan. Gambar selfie, tweet lawak/kuiz.

Okay?
Translated Text:
To inform, to tell. For example, I want to tell you if there is a sale today or how many covid cases there are today.

To entertain, entertainment. Selfies, funny tweets/quizzes.

Okay?

Text:
Dah tahu objektif, dah tahu kategori; sekarang barulah mudah nak cari tajuk!

Betul tak?

Saya dah ada keyword tapi tak tahu nak kembangkan jadi tajuk.

Pergi type keyword dalam kepala dekat sini: https://t.co/uO3HAFrwgA
Translated Text:
You know the objective, you know the category; now it's easy to find a title!

Right?

I already have a keyword but I don't know how to develop it into a title.

Go type keywords in your head here: https://t.co/uO3HAFrwgA

Text:
Dah dapat tajuk. 

Macam mana nak start tulis?

Macam ni.
Translated Text:
Got the title.

How to start writing?

Like this.

Text:
Lepas saya analyze beberapa tweet yang viral, saya lihat ada beberapa persamaan dalam susunan ayat mereka.

Well obviously takdelah sama terang-terangan.

Tapi sama dari segi prinsipnya.
Translated Text:
After I analyzed some viral tweets, I saw that there were some similarities in the order of their sentences.

Well obviously not the same openly.

But the same in principle.

Text:
3. Kepala thread mesti power

Kepala thread adalah elemen terpenting untuk gain RT & like.

Dan kalau korang perasan, kepala thread yang viral ni biasanya ada dua benda yang diorang bawa:

Fakta & emosi.
Translated Text:
3. The thread head must be powered

The thread head is the most important element for RT gain & like.

And if you notice, the head of this viral thread usually has two things that people bring:

Facts & emotions.

Text:
Diorang akan start kepala thread tu dengan facts.

Kemudian masukkan elemen emosi. 

Ditutup dengan pertanyaan.
Translated Text:
People will start the thread with facts.

Then add the emotional element.

Closed with questions.

Text:
Tak percaya?

Cuba malam ni cari 10 tweet yang viral, dan tengok apa persamaannya.

Kepala thread diorang konfem power.
Translated Text:
Do not believe?

Try tonight to find 10 viral tweets, and see what they have in common.

The head of the thread is konfem power.

Text:
4. Menepati kuadran content

Last but not least, pastikan thread/tweet korang ada 4 benda ni:

1. Fakta
2. Emosi.
3. Bahasa.
4. Impactful
Translated Text:
4. Meet the content quadrant

Last but not least, make sure your thread/tweet has these 4 things:

1. Facts
2. Emotions.
3. Language.
4. Impactful

Text:
Benda ni bukan magik.

Dan mungkin susah untuk diterapkan awal2.

Tapi once kita praktis, ia jadi mudah.

Boleh tak macam tu? (*tiru gaya ik*)
Translated Text:
This thing is not magic.

And it may be difficult to implement early2.

But once we practice, it becomes easy.

Can it be like that? (*mimics ik style*)

Text:
Sebenarnya ada banyak lagi saya nak share tapi cukup dulu kot. Let's recap 4 benda:

1. Kenalpasti objektif setiap tweet.
2. Tahu kategori konten.
3. Kepala thread yang menarik
4. Tepati 4 elemen kuadran konten.

Follow @FezzaHussin, nanti saya share lagi.
Translated Text:
Actually, there's a lot more I want to share, but that's enough for now. Let's recap 4 objects:

1. Objective identification of each tweet.
2. Know the category of content.
3. Interesting thread head
4. Fulfill the 4 elements of the content quadrant.

Follow @FezzaHussin, I'll share more later.

Text:
For me there is no such thing a perfect staff. Haha

So first of all, kita kena define maksud bagus tu kita nak macam mana?

Ada orang nak bagus tu means laju buat kerja. Ada orang nak bagus tu means boleh berfikir boleh analisa dan sebagaimana.
Translated Text:
For me there is no such thing as a perfect staff. Haha

So first of all, we have to define what we mean by good?

There are people who want to be good and work fast. There are people who want to be good, which means they can think, analyze and so on.

Text:
Saya define pekerja yang bagus ni ada 3 qualification yang saya tengok.

Sebenarnya topik pekerja ni luas sangat guys, tak cukup thread saya tulis ni. Dan semua ni tergantung pengalaman masing-2. 

Saya share benda yang saya tahu je la ye. Kalau ada nak tambah boleh reply.
Translated Text:
I define a good employee as having 3 qualifications that I look at.

Actually, the topic of workers is very broad, guys, I can't write enough threads. And all of this depends on each other's experience.

I just share what I know. If you have anything to add, you can reply.

Text:
Apa tiga benda yang saya tengok? 

Yang pertama adalah attitude. Always attitude first guys. 
 
Hebat la macam mana pun skill korang. Tapi attitude ke laut. Tong sampah la jawabnya. Haha
Translated Text:
What three things did I see?

The first is attitude. Always attitude first guys.
 
It's great no matter what your skill is. But the attitude to the sea. The trash can is the answer. Haha

Text:
Ada la beberapa pertimbangan yg saya lihat tentang attitude ni.

Kenapa penting sgt attitude?

Sebab ada orang skill mantap penampilan hebat. Pengalaman tak tahu la. Paling senior la kot. Degree master tak usah cerita la. Tapi bab attitude ke laut.

Habis!
Translated Text:
There are several considerations that I see about this attitude.

Why is attitude so important?

Because there are people with great skills and great appearance. I don't know experience. The most senior la kot. Master's degree doesn't need to be told. But the chapter on attitude to the sea.

Finished!

Text:
Rasa diri pandai sangat, orang lain bagi opinion or reject idea dia. Dia melalak. 

Kita as majikan jangan cepat sangat termakan dengan resume calon. Selagi mana dia belum bekerja dengan company kita paling kurang 3 ke 6 bulan. Anggap la kita masih belum kenal dia.
Translated Text:
Feeling very smart, other people give their opinion or reject their idea. He sneered.

As employers, don't be too quick to get overwhelmed with a candidate's resume. As long as he has not worked with our company for at least 3 to 6 months. Suppose we still don't know him.

Text:
And please jangan letak expectation terlalu tinggi. 

Kenapa? 

Sebab bukan semua pengalaman atau skill kat luar sana boleh fit our culture, our aim, our goals. ok?
Translated Text:
And please don't set your expectations too high.

Why?

Because not all experiences or skills out there can fit our culture, our aim, our goals. okay?

Text:
Second is skill. 

Bila dah attitude bagus, mestilah kita nak orang yg skillfull untuk join our team. 

Buat apa ambil orang tapi tak match dengan skill yang kita nak?

Nanti target company ke laut jadinya. Kita pun susah nak grow company.
Translated Text:
Second is skill.

When the attitude is good, we must want skilled people to join our team.

Why hire people who don't match the skills we want?

Later, the target company will go to sea. It's hard for us to grow a company.

Text:
Skill ni luas juga nak bahas. 

Ikut position or role dia. Boleh jadi pengalaman yang dia ada dulu before kita ambit dia bekerja, tak sebagus mana bila masuk ke our company. 

Tapi bagusnya adalah mungkin kita tak perlu ajar dia benda basic.
Translated Text:
This skill is also broad to discuss.

Follow his position or role. It could be that the experience he had before we asked him to work, was not as good as when he joined our company.

But the good thing is that maybe we don't have to teach him basic things.

Text:
Skill ni juga tergantung kerja apa dia buat. 

Kalau as video editor lain la skill dia kena ada dengan seorang akauntan kan? Obviously.

Tapi saya tgk siapa pun pekerja kita nak ambil. Kena ada basic skill menyelesaikan masalah.
Translated Text:
This skill also depends on what work he does.

If it's another video editor's skills, he has to have an accountant, right? Obviously.

But I don't see who our employees want to hire. Must have basic skills to solve problems.

Text:
Sebab dunia pekerjaan ni. Macam-macam masalah yang akan timbul kan. 

Internal dan external. 

Kalau dapat staff jenis termenung je ada masalah susah la kita. Haha kena banyak train lagi okey?
Translated Text:
Because of this world of work. All kinds of problems will arise, right?

Internal and external.

If you can get staff who are only pensive, we have a difficult problem. Haha I have to train a lot more okay?

Text:
The last one will be: kesetiaan (ceh wah haha)
 
Tapi tu lah. 

Susah sikit kita nak tahu staff kita loyal ke tidak. Sebab isu loyal ni stakat kerja 1-2 tahun saya kira belum lagi loyal. 

Jadi it takes time la. So peranan kita la as majikan kena jaga staff betul-2. Betul tak?
Translated Text:
The last one will be: loyalty (cheh wah haha)
 
But that's it.

It's a little difficult for us to know if our staff is loyal or not. Because the loyalty issue is 1-2 years of work, I don't think it's loyal yet.

So it takes time. So our role as employers is to take care of the staff properly. Right?

Text:
Jaga ni bukan stakat makan minum dan keperluan lain. Bagi saya if nak jaga staff kena makesure dia rasa bila dia kerja di company kita ada added value yang kita boleh provide. 

Contoh kat tempat saya kerja, kami provide kelas mengaji bagi yang nak belajar.
Translated Text:
Take care not to eat, drink and other necessities. For me, if you want to take care of staff, you have to make sure that they feel that when they work in our company, they have added value that we can provide.

For example, where I work, we provide study classes for those who want to learn.

Text:
Solat berjemaah di office, project sampingan supaya staff boleh develop pemikiran dan dalam masa yang sama tidak fed up sebab asyik buat kerja sama. 

Haha
Translated Text:
Congregational prayer in the office, side projects so that the staff can develop their thoughts and at the same time not get fed up because they are busy working together.

Haha

Text:
So itu la. Saya rasa 3 benda ni crucial part. 

Tapi yelah. 

Macam cerita sebelum ni. Give and take. 

Kalau majikan je give pekerja diam tak jadi cerita juga. Kalau pekerja je give, majikan buat dunno. Pun sama.
Translated Text:
So that's it. I think these 3 things are crucial parts.

But yes.

Like the story before this. Give and take.

If the employer just keeps the employee quiet, it won't be a story either. If the employee gives, the employer does it. It's the same.

Text:
So yeah, play our role sehabis baik. Sudi terima kritikan dan nothing personal. Jgn emosi terbawa bawa pula ok. 

Tu je lah bebelan kali ni.

Ada apa2 nak tambah?

Btw, jangan lupa RT & follow @fezzahussin okay. Nanti saya buat banyak lagi thread! Heheh
Translated Text:
So yeah, play our role as soon as possible. Willing to accept criticism and nothing personal. Don't get carried away with your emotions, it's ok.

That's the only thing this time.

Do you have anything to add?

Btw, don't forget to RT & follow @fezzahussin okay. I will make more threads later! Heheh

Text:
Interesting story & a good reputation

Interesting story create free publicity. Tapi please jangan buat benda bodoh okay!

Tesla selalu come out dengan kisah yang menarik tentang brand diorang. https://t.co/b5KrM3v2rl
Translated Text:
Interesting story & a good reputation

Interesting stories create free publicity. But please don't do stupid things okay!

Tesla always comes out with interesting stories about people's brands. https://t.co/b5KrM3v2rl

Text:
Korang ingat, tahun 2017 taufan Maria menyerang Puerto Rico? 

Tu antara bencana terburuk yang pernah dialami sampai Trump terpaksa approve Emergency Disaster Declaration dekat sana.

Disebabkan taufan tu, Puerto Rico mengalami masalah gangguan elektrik.
Translated Text:
Do you remember, in 2017 Typhoon Maria attacked Puerto Rico?

That was one of the worst disasters ever experienced until Trump was forced to approve the Emergency Disaster Declaration near there.

Due to the typhoon, Puerto Rico experienced an electrical fault problem.

Text:
Jadi ada sorang netizen mention Elon Musk dan cadangkan untuk rebuild electricity system dekat sana guna independent solar & battery systems.

Elon Musk reply yang Tesla boleh bantu dengan sokongan beberapa org.

20 hari selepas itu Tesla mulakan kerja mereka di Puerto Rico. https://t.co/XiYOq2ApuL
Translated Text:
So a netizen mentioned Elon Musk and suggested to rebuild the electricity system nearby using independent solar & battery systems.

Elon Musk replied that Tesla can help with the support of several people.

20 days after that Tesla started their work in Puerto Rico. https://t.co/XiYOq2ApuL

Text:
Well, that's interesting & very good publicity for your company.

Tapi pleaselah jangan associate interesting story ni dengan story2 viral yang bodoh. Maaf cakap. Sebab selalu sangat nampak viral story kurang pandai semata2 untuk lariskan produk diorang.

Kamon, dah 2021 kot.
Translated Text:
Well, that's interesting & very good publicity for your company.

But please don't associate this interesting story with stupid viral stories. Sorry to say. Because it always seems that viral stories are not very clever just to sell people's products.

Come on, it's already 2021.

Text:
An interesting story is free publicity, and a good reputation builds a brand.

Well, tesla ada dua-dua ni.

Interesting story dan good reputation hasil daripada product mereka yang kita semua tahu macam mana.

Brand kita pulak macam mana?
Translated Text:
An interesting story is free publicity, and a good reputation builds a brand.

Well, Tesla has two of these.

Interesting story and good reputation as a result of their products that we all know what it's like.

What is our brand like?

Text:
Mouth to mouth marketing.

Tesla tak perlu bayar iklan, sebab customer diorang sendiri sibuk cerita tentang Tesla dekat orang lain.

Tapi kenapa?

Sebab Tesla bagi reward untuk depa.
Translated Text:
Mouth to mouth marketing.

Tesla doesn't need to pay for advertising, because the customers themselves are busy talking about Tesla to other people.

But why?

Because Tesla gave a reward for fathoms.

Text:
Mouth to mouth marketing memang sangat power, sebab testimoni tu sangat genuine datangnya daripada pengguna sendiri.

Disebabkan itu, trust orang yang tengok/baca product recommendation daripada orang lain lagi power daripada trust diorang bila tengok iklan.
Translated Text:
Mouth to mouth marketing is very powerful, because the testimonials are very genuine coming from the users themselves.

Because of that, trusting people who see/read product recommendations from other people is more powerful than trusting people when they see advertisements.

Text:
Disebabkan tu Tesla mewujudkan referral program sendiri.

Pernah jumpa mana2 company kereta yang guna referral program untuk jual kereta? Haha. Saya pun tak pernah jumpa.

Kalau jual ebook ada lah kan.
Translated Text:
That's why Tesla created its own referral program.

Have you ever seen any car companies that use a referral program to sell cars? Haha. I have never met either.

If you sell ebooks, it's there, right?

Text:
Waktu tahun 2015, siapa yang refer sorang new buyer akan dapat $1000 credit dalam akaun mereka. 

Kredit ni boleh guna untuk beli kereta baru (tesla of course), servis atau beli aksesori kereta.

Sorang youtuber pernah dapat Tesla Model X FREE sebab referral program ni!
Translated Text:
In 2015, whoever refers a new buyer will get $1000 credit in their account.

This credit can be used to buy a new car (Tesla of course), service or buy car accessories.

A youtuber once got a Tesla Model X FREE because of this referral program!

Text:
Bjorn Nyland jadi orang yang pertama dapat refer 10 orang pembeli. So dia dapat $10K credit, $10K bonus, FREE Founder Edition Model X, dan lawatan ke Tesla Gigafactory.

Bukan dia sorang je.

Ben Sullins pun dpt. Bukan 1 tapi 2 roadsters FREE! Berapa new customer yang dia refer? https://t.co/CuJMxE3kiT
Translated Text:
Bjorn Nyland was the first to be able to refer 10 buyers. So he gets $10K credits, $10K bonus, FREE Founder Edition Model X, and a visit to the Tesla Gigafactory.

He's not the only one.

Ben Sullins also got. Not 1 but 2 FREE roadsters! How many new customers did he refer? https://t.co/CuJMxE3kiT

Text:
105 customer.

Total sales daripada mamat ni sorang je adalah $12,000,000.

Pada waktu itu. Sekarang tak tahu lah mungkin dah bertambah2.

Referral program ni sangat berjaya sampaikan pada tahun 2019, Tesla bagi 80 FREE roadster untuk referral2 yang power ni.
Translated Text:
105 customers.

Total sales from Mamat alone is $12,000,000.

At that time. Now I don't know, maybe it has increased.

This referral program was very successful in 2019, Tesla gave away 80 FREE roadsters for these powerful referrals.

Text:
So ini adalah antara benda yang kita boleh implement dalam bisnes kita jugak sebenarnya.

Kalau company local, korang boleh tengok macam mana Oxwhite punya strategi waktu launch diorang punya first shirt.

Referral program memang powerful weapon for our business.
Translated Text:
So this is one of the things that we can actually implement in our business.

If the company is local, you can see what kind of strategy Oxwhite has when launching, people have the first shirt.

Referral program is indeed a powerful weapon for our business.

Text:
The best customer experience.

Pernah pergi sales center, pastu salesman paksa2 korang addon benda yang korang tak perlu pun?

Atau dia cadangkan kereta yang tak menepati keperluan & mempengaruhi untuk beli kereta yg over bajet?

Not in tesla.
Translated Text:
The best customer experience.

Have you ever been to a sales center, and the salesman forced you to add things you didn't even need?

Or he suggests a car that doesn't meet the needs & influence to buy a car that is over budget?

Not in tesla.

Text:
Sebab apa?

Sebab first, basically kita boleh purchase Tesla ni online je.

Klik, klik setel.

Tapi kalau nak pergi sale center pun takde masalah. Salesman takkan push korang untuk beli lebih daripada kemampuan dan keperluan.
Translated Text:
Why?

Because first, basically we can only purchase Tesla online.

Click, click set.

But if you want to go to the sale center, there is no problem. Salesmen will not push you to buy more than you can and need.

Text:
Tugas diorang basically adalah untuk advise customer untuk buat pilihan yang terbaik.

So there shouldn't be conflict of interest.

Mantap kan?
Translated Text:
Their job is basically to advise customers to make the best choice.

So there shouldn't be a conflict of interest.

Great right?

Text:
Basically tu antara 4 major point yang kita boleh belajar daripada Tesla yang spend $0 dekat iklan.

Mungkin kita tak mampu lah nak capai level $0 iklan tu, tapi pengajaran ni kita boleh ambil untuk implement dalam bisnes kita.

Recap balik main point dekat atas ⬇️
Translated Text:
Basically that is one of the 4 major points that we can learn from Tesla who spends $0 on advertising.

We may not be able to reach the $0 ad level, but we can take this lesson to implement in our business.

Recap the main point near the top ⬇️

Text:
How tesla spend $0 on ads?

1. Build interesting story.
2. Maintain good reputation.
3. Use the power of mouth to mouth marketing.
4. Improve customer experience.

Dapat sesuatu?

Text: Untuk marketing, korang selalu hadapi masalah yg macam mana?
Translated Text: For marketing, what kind of problems do you always face?

Text: Untuk team development, korang hadapi masalah apa?
Translated Text: For team development, what problems do you face?

Text: Topik yang paling korang suka baca.
Translated Text: The topic you like to read the most.

Text:
1) Jadilah role model

Macam mana nak suruh agen jual 100 produk sebulan, kalau kita sendiri tak pernah jual satu pun produk sebulan?

Tapi, bila kita pernah jual 1000 produk sebulan, lagi mudah untuk agen kita jual 100 produk setiap bulan.

Sebab apa?
Translated Text:
1) Be a role model

How are you going to order agents to sell 100 products a month, if we ourselves never sell a single product a month?

But, if we once sold 1000 products a month, it's easier for our agents to sell 100 products every month.

Why?

Text:
Sebab bila kita jadi leader ni, kerja kita bukan semata mengarah & mintak orang lain capai KPI je. 

Kita kena guide mereka.

Macam mana nak guide kalau kita sendiri tak pernah lalui apa yg diorang rasa?
Translated Text:
Because when we become this leader, our job is not just directing & ask others to reach KPI.

We have to guide them.

How can we guide if we ourselves have never been through what people feel?

Text:
Numbers kat atas tu sekadar idea je nak bagi nampak. Takdelah exact figure untuk jadi stokis yg power. Hahah

Yg penting, kita faham bagaimana proses untuk capai target tersebut.

Dan dengan track record kita, agen kita pun termotivasi untuk buat sales. hehe
Translated Text:
The numbers above are just an idea to show you. There is no exact figure to be a powerful stockist. Hahaha

The important thing is that we understand the process to reach the target.

And with our track record, our agents are motivated to make sales. lol

Text:
Now saya handle team marketing NGO, saya try buat semua dari technical sampai ke strategical. 

Saya pernah cuba edit video, buat ads, main content, dealing dgn orang, etc. 

Kita kena tahu supaya senang sok nak grow team. Tahu nak tambah kat area mana. etc
Translated Text:
Now I handle the NGO's marketing team, I try to do everything from technical to strategic.

I've tried editing videos, making ads, playing content, dealing with people, etc.

We have to know so that it is easy to grow a team. Know which area to add. etc

Text:
2) Galakkan team untuk contribute sesuatu

Kena selalu remind team members yang diorang ni part of the team & ajak diorang untuk contribute sama. 

Bagi ruang team untuk plan dan present idea. Minta mereka bagi idea untuk improve. Advice bila perlu.
Translated Text:
2) Encourage the team to contribute something

Always have to remind team members that this person is part of the team & invite people to contribute the same.

For team space to plan and present ideas. Ask them for ideas to improve. Advice when necessary.

Text:
Bagi ruang team cuba idea mereka, dan kalau gagal. Tahniah mereka sedang belajar sesuatu.

Tapi bukan lah hari-hari biar team gagal. hahah lingkup business esok. So situlah datang peranan kita betulkan mana yang salah, okay?

Advice team menuju kejayaan.
Translated Text:
For the team space, try their ideas, and if they fail. Congratulations they are learning something.

But it's not a day to let the team fail. hahah scope of business tomorrow. So that's where our role comes to correct what's wrong, okay?

Advice team towards success.

Text:
3) Bagi hadiah & penghargaan

Okay kita mintak diorang contribute something, tapi apa pulak yg kita bagi?

Kena ingat, bila deal dengan manusia ni tak boleh satu hala je.

Mesti ada give & take.

Kalau kita minta something drpd diorang, kita juga kena bagi something.
Translated Text:
3) For gifts & appreciation

Okay, we ask people to contribute something, but what do we give?

You have to remember, when dealing with humans, it can't be one-way.

There must be give & take.

If we ask for something from someone, we also have to give something.

Text:
Inilah apa yang syarikat2 insurans/unit trust tu semua buat.

Diorang bukan buat bodoh2 tau, diorang implement sistem rewards & recognition ni based on satu research yang pernah publish dekat US dulu.
Translated Text:
This is what the insurance companies/unit trusts all do.

People don't make fools, you know, people implement the rewards system & This recognition is based on a research that was published in the US before.

Text:
Diorang conclude, R&R (Rewards & Recognition) ni memang faktor utama untuk buat agen motivated untuk buat sales lagi banyak.

Jadi, kita tiruvasi. Cuma saya punya team saya educate cara lain. Saya tak bagi duit semata. Saya ada cara lain. Tapi korang bebas nak pilih cara mana.
Translated Text:
People conclude, R&R (Rewards & Recognition) is indeed the main factor to make agents motivated to make more sales.

So, we are tiruvasi. It's just that I have my team to educate in other ways. I don't just give money. I have another way. But you are free to choose which way to go.

Text:
Saya didik team utk faham our mission. Obviously our mission as NGO or Business entitiy dalam MyFundAction bukan reward duit yang kami kejar. 

Saya advocate the value of helping others. Nilai ni tak mampu dibeli dengan wang ringgit. ;)

So, depends okay?
Translated Text:
I educate the team to understand our mission. Obviously our mission as an NGO or Business entity in MyFundAction is not the monetary reward we are chasing.

I advocate the value of helping others. This value cannot be bought with ringgit money. ;)

So, it depends okay?

Text:
Korang boleh nak guna cara mana pun. Itu cara saya hehe.

So saya tak biasa bagi duit pada team. Biasanya saya cuba penuhi keperluan mereka. Tergantung juga kepada performance staff. 

So yeah, give and take.
Translated Text:
You can use any method. That's my way hehe.

So I'm not used to giving money to the team. Usually I try to meet their needs. It also depends on the performance of the staff.

So yeah, give and take.

Text:
Onpay.

Sistem onpay ni lebih kepada borang tempahan/minisite.

Kelebihan sistem ni, dia mudah digunakan, user interface admin yang mudah untuk difahami even untuk yang baru nak bermula sebab tak sofistikated.

Dan dia ada juga features untuk agen, affiliate etc.

Onpay.

This onpay system is more like a booking form/minisite.

The advantage of this system is that it is easy to use, the admin user interface is easy to understand even for beginners who want to start because it is not sophisticated.

Text:
First thing first, determine kekuatan korang kat mana.

Ada orang pandai buat menulis.
Ada yang pandai bercakap.
Ada yang pandai video.
Ada yang pandai ambil gambar.

Korang pandai apa?
Translated Text:
First thing first, determine where your strengths are.

There are people who are good at writing.
Some are good at talking.
Some are good at video.
Some are good at taking pictures.

What are you good at?

Text:
Bila dah determine kekuatan kita, barulah kita tahu nak fokus dekat social media apa.

Kalau kita power menulis, fokus dekat FB & Twitter.
Power edit video, fokus tiktok & youtube.
Hebat bergambar, fokus instagram.

Awal2 ni fokus dekat satu medium dulu, kemudian baru kembangkan.
Translated Text:
When we have determined our strengths, then we know what social media to focus on.

If we have the power to write, focus on FB & Twitter.
Video editing power, focus on tiktok & youtube.
Great picture, instagram focus.

At first, focus on one medium first, then develop it.

Text:
Dah tahu nak fokus dekat medium yang mana.

Next, kenalpasti content goal

Sebelum korang hasilkan satu2 konten, kenalpasti dulu matlamat content yang korang produce tu.

Generally, ada 3 matlamat utama content dekat social media.

Apa dia?
Translated Text:
I already know which medium to focus on.

Next, identify the content goal

Before you produce any content, first identify the goal of the content you are producing.

Generally, there are 3 main goals of social media content.

What is it?

Text:
1. Untuk gain follower.
2. Untuk engagement.
3. Untuk sales.

So setiap content yang kita produce mesti berpaksikan matlamat yang ditetapkan. Bila ada matlamat, kita pun mudah nak ukur yang content tu bagus atau tak.

Sebab apa?
Translated Text:
1. To gain followers.
2. For engagement.
3. For sales.

So every content we produce must focus on the set goal. When there is a goal, it is easy for us to measure whether the content is good or not.

Why?

Text:
Sebab kayu ukur untuk setiap goal tu berbeza.

Untuk gain follower, kita tengok daripada jumlah follower/subscriber 24 jam selepas post tu publish.

Untuk engagement, cukup sekadar kita tengok jumlah like/rt/views sahaja.

Untuk sales, kita tengoklah berapa sales yang dapat.
Translated Text:
Because the yardstick for each goal is different.

To gain followers, we look at the number of followers/subscribers 24 hours after the post is published.

For engagement, just look at the number of likes/rt/views.

For sales, let's see how many sales we can get.

Text:
Nampak tak?

Bila matlamat kita jelas, kita senang nak buat decision content yang macam mana kita nak hasilkan.

Cuba bayangkan kita clueless, taktahu apa matlamat content kita. 

Semua benda pun kita nak ukur. Last2 give up macam tu je.
Translated Text:
Did you see that?

When our goals are clear, we are happy to make a decision on what kind of content we want to produce.

Try to imagine that we are clueless, not knowing what the goal of our content is.

We want to measure everything. The last two give up like that.

Text:
So sekarang, korang dah tahu:

1) Kekuatan korang (untuk fokus dekat medium yang mana)
2) Content goal 

Yang ketiga, apa yang penting?

Audiens.
Translated Text:
So now, you know:

1) Your strength (to focus on which medium)
2) Content goals

The third, what is important?

Audience.

Text:
Sebelum mula produce content, kenalpasti & fahami dulu audiens yang kita targetkan.

Lagi banyak kita tahu pasal audiens kita, lagi banyak yang kita faham, lagi tepat sasaran konten tu.

Create audience avatar kita sendiri.
Translated Text:
Before starting to produce content, get to know & First understand our target audience.

The more we know about our audience, the more we understand, the more targeted the content is.

Create our own audience avatar.

Text:
Contoh: Jual skincare mahal.

Audience avatar:

1. Age: 25-40
2. Sex: Female
3. Career: Professional
4. Location: KL/JB/Penang (Bandar besar)
5. Interest: Duck

Ini contoh, saya takde buat apa2 research okay pasal skincare. Hahaha

Audience avatars:

1.Age: 25-40
2. Sex: Female
3. Career: Professional
4. Location: KL/JB/Penang (Bandar)

Text:
So bila dah ada avatar ni, kita just tulis seolah-olah audiens kita cuma avatar ini sahaja.

Jangan peduli pasal orang lain.

Ada puluh juta orang kat Facebook, 6 juta dekat Twitter, ratus ribu kat LinkedIn. Takkan kita nak tapau semua.
Translated Text:
So when we have this avatar, we just write as if our audience is only this avatar.

Don't care about other people.

There are ten million people on Facebook, 6 million on Twitter, hundreds of thousands on LinkedIn. We don't want to know everything.

Text:
So dah 3 benda,

1. Kekuatan diri
2. Matlamat content
3. Audience avatar

So last sekali apa? Benda ni alasan yang sangat selalu kita dengar bila cerita pasal konten.

Takde idea! Hahaha.
Translated Text:

1. Self-strength
2. Content goals
3. Audience avatar

So what's the last thing? This is the reason we always hear when talking about content.

No idea! Haha.

Text:

Text:
1) Buat akaun media sosial & produce content

Sebelum nak buat media sosial untuk menjual ni, first thing first kena determine yang awak ni ada bakat share konten dalam bentuk yang macam mana?

Penulisan ke?
Video ke?
Gambar ke?

Before you want to make social media to sell this, the first thing is to determine that you have the talent to share content in what form?

The writing?
The video?
The picture?

Text:
Sebab apa penting untuk determine kekuatan kita? Sebab awal2 ni kita tak boleh nak fokus dekat semua benda.

Kalau power menulis, fokus dekat Facebook & Twitter.

Kalau power buat video, fokus dekat Tiktok & Youtube.

Kalau power edit gambar, fokus dekat Instagram.
Translated Text:
Why is it important to determine our strength? Because in the beginning we can't focus on all things.

If you have the power to write, focus on Facebook & Twitter.

If you have power to make videos, focus on Tiktok & YouTube.

If you have power to edit images, focus on Instagram.

Text:
Setiap hari produce at least 2-3 konten berkaitan dengan niche.

Jual barangan skincare? Share lah tips pasal skincare.
Jual barangan baby? Share tips penjagaan anak.
Jual barangan kereta? Share info pasal kereta.

Benda ni memang tak perlu modal, tapi perlu komitmen.
Translated Text:
Every day produce at least 2-3 content related to the niche.

Selling skincare products? Share tips about skincare.
Selling baby items? Share childcare tips.
Selling car items? Share info about the car.

This thing does not need capital, but it needs commitment.

Text:

Lepas dah beberapa minggu start sharing konten, barulah start menjual. Softsell ke hardsell ke, terpulang lah.

Pada saya, dua2 pun boleh.
Translated Text:
Spend 3-4 hours a day on this, God willing there will be results.

It's been a few weeks since I started sharing content, then I started selling. Softsell or hardsell, it's up to you.

For me, both are fine.

Text:

Tapi bukanlah magik. Hari ni buat website, esok terus ada 10,000 customer macam khairulaming. Hahah. Realistik sikit.

Text:

Cipta networking bisnes ni antara tips marketing yang memang $0 cost. Haha.

Literally, berkenalan kot. Mana ada orang minta duit bila kita nak berkenal2.

Unless korang join specific circle lah.

3) Networking

Create this business networking among the marketing tips that really cost $0. Haha.

Literally, get acquainted. Where are people asking for money when we want to get to know each other?

Unless you join a specific circle.

Text:
Katalah korang buat dropship jual cookies, carilah member yang jadi agen/dropship air hipster.

Buat dropship kurma? Berkenalanlah dengan orang yang jual air zam2.

Sebab pelanggan diorang berpotensi untuk jadi pelanggan kita juga. Dan vice versa.

Do you dropship dates? Get to know people who sell zam2 water.

Because our customers have the potential to become our customers as well. And vice versa.

Text:
4) Minta feedback

Customer dah mula beli, apa yang kita kena buat?

Mintalah feedback daripada diorang. 

Kalau ada benda yang ditegur, kita berterima kasih & improve.
Kalau ada benda yang dipuji, kita berterima kasih & screenshot.

Hahaha
Translated Text:
4) Ask for feedback

Customers have started buying, what should we do?

Ask for feedback from people.

If something is reprimanded, we thank & improve.
If something is praised, we thank & screenshots.

Haha

Text:
But seriously, feedback daripada customer sangat penting untuk kita. Either dia nak ws personal atau dia sendiri nak tweet/post dekat FB/IG/Twitter, semuanya tak kisah.

Yang penting feedback tu boleh gain trust daripada pelanggan baru kita selepas ni.
Translated Text:
But seriously, feedback from customers is very important to us. Either he wants to ws personally or he himself wants to tweet/post on FB/IG/Twitter, it all doesn't matter.

The important thing is that feedback can gain trust from our new customers after this.

Text:
5) Thank you notes.

Jual apa pun, pleaselah buat pelanggan rasa dihargai.

Simple sangat nak buat pelanggan rasa dihargai ni, letak thank you notes je hati pelanggan dah berbunga2.
Translated Text:
5) Thank you notes.

Sell ​​anything, please make the customer feel appreciated.

It's very simple to make the customer feel appreciated, just put thank you notes and the customer's heart will blossom.

Text:
Tak perlu kad yang fancy2, tulis atas sehelai kertas/kad kecil & letakkan dalam parcel sekali.

How much it cost?

Tak sampai 30 sen pun. 

Tapi thank you notes ni boleh jadi sebab yang kuat untuk klien bagi feedback untuk produk kita.
Translated Text:
No need for fancy cards, write on a piece of paper/small card & put it in the parcel once.

How much does it cost?

Not even 30 cents.

But these thank you notes can be a strong reason for clients to give feedback for our products.

Text:

Text:
4. Master the message

Okay sekarang dah ada produk yang terbaik, macam mana nak dapatkan pelanggan?

Pelanggan perlu tahu macam mana produk kita mampu selesaikan masalah yang diorang hadapi. Dan sebab itulah sangat penting untuk kita master, message yang ingin disampaikan.
Translated Text:
4. Master the message

Okay, now that you have the best product, how do you get customers?

Customers need to know how our products can solve the problems they face. And that's why it's very important for us to master the message we want to convey.

Text:
Korang pernah tengok macam mana Steve Jobs present iPhone masa awal2 dulu.

Slide yang dia tunjuk tak banyak ayat pun. Banyak grafik dan penyampaiannya cukup jelas. 

Kombinasi bahan grafik, animasi & presentation dia menerbitkan wow factor kepada audiens.
Translated Text:
You've seen how Steve Jobs presented the iPhone in the early days.

The slide he showed didn't even have many sentences. Lots of graphics and the presentation is pretty clear.

A combination of graphic materials, animation & His presentation gives the audience a wow factor.

Text:
5. Cari & kenali musuh

Okay ni nampak macam pelik, tapi sebenarnya tak pelik. Dan memang Steve Jobs sepanjang membangunkan produk dia menggunakan konsep ni.

In fact, brand2 besar sangat terkenal untuk mencipta dan melawan musuh mereka dengan terang-terangan.
Translated Text:
5. Find & know the enemy

Okay, this looks weird, but it's not really weird. And indeed Steve Jobs used this concept throughout his product development.

In fact, big brands are notorious for creating and outright fighting their enemies.

Text:
Coca cola vs Pepsi
Apple vs Android
McD vs KFC

See? Semua ada musuh yang nyata. 

Sebab apa?

Ini semua berpaksikan kepada 'herd mentality' sebuah konsep yang diutarakan oleh psikologis dari Perancis yang bernama Gabriel Tarde & Gustava Le Bon.
Translated Text:
Coca cola vs Pepsi
Apple vs. Android
McD vs KFC

See? Everyone has a real enemy.

Why?

This all revolves around 'herd mentality', a concept expressed by a psychologist from France named Gabriel Tarde & Gustave Le Bon.

Text:
Apa itu herd mentality?

Herd mentality ni adalah satu behavior manusia untuk choosing sides.

Ini memang sifat fitrah semulajadi seorang manusia.
Translated Text:
What is herd mentality?

This herd mentality is a human behavior for choosing sides.

This is indeed the natural nature of a human being.

Text:
Dan bila dah pilih sides, diorang akan feel better berada dalam group diorang tu. 

That's why sangat penting untuk kita cari, kenal & faham musuh kita. Supaya kita dapat entertain customer kita dengan lebih baik.
Translated Text:
And when you have chosen sides, people will feel better being in that group.

That's why it's very important for us to find, know & understand our enemy. So that we can entertain our customers better.

Text:
6. Keep it simple

Tengoklah mana ada produk Apple yang sofistikated.

Dari segi user experience, design produk & even cara pembelian di laman web, Apple menggunakan konsep ini dengan sangat baik.
Translated Text:
6.Keep it simple

Look where there are Apple products that are sophisticated.

In terms of user experience, product design & even how to purchase on a web page, Apple uses this concept very well.

Text:
Mesej yang disampaikan cukup jelas: less is more.

Simplicity bukanlah makna kata kita menaruhkan kualiti produk kita, tapi kita cuba buat dia sesimple mungkin untuk digunakan oleh pelanggan tanpa menjejaskan kualitinya.
Translated Text:
The message conveyed is quite clear: less is more.

Simplicity does not mean that we compromise on the quality of our products, but we try to make them as simple as possible for customers to use without affecting the quality.

Text:
Nampak mudah, tapi sebenarnya lagi susah. 

Sebab tu ada orang kata, simple is the utmost complicated.
Translated Text:
It looks easy, but it's actually more difficult.

That's why some people say, simple is the most complicated.

Text:
1. Fokus menghasilkan produk terbaik

Zaman Apple baru nak bermula dulu, Steve Jobs dengan Steve Wozniak mencetuskan revolusi dalam dunia IT.

Waktu tu Altair 8800 baru release pada umum. Korang tahu tak macam mana rupa bentuk Altair 8800 ni?
Translated Text:
1. Focus on producing the best products

The era of Apple was just about to begin, Steve Jobs and Steve Wozniak sparked a revolution in the IT world.

At that time, the Altair 8800 had just been released to the public. Do you know what the Altair 8800 looks like?

Text:
Jauh sekali daripada bentuk komputer yang kita guna sekarang. Bawah ni saya tunjuk gambar Altair 8800. 

Tapi waktu tu dah kira hebat dah ni.

Kelab2 komputer muncul di seluruh US dan bincang tentang apa yang komputer kecil ni boleh buat. https://t.co/TBrU7XxM5G
Translated Text:
Far from the form of computers we use now. Below I show a picture of the Altair 8800.

But at that time I thought it was great.

Computer clubs popped up all over the US and talked about what this little computer could do. https://t.co/TBrU7XxM5G

Text:
Dan pada waktu tu, dua orang mamat ni menghasilkan satu komputer yang boleh buat lebihh daripada apa yang Altair mampu lakukan.

Bukan setakat tu je, komputer yang depa hasilkan bukan saja boleh digunakan oleh tech enthusiast, tapi orang biasa pun boleh guna.
Translated Text:
And at that time, these two people produced a computer that could do more than what Altair could do.

Not only that, the computer that will be produced can not only be used by tech enthusiasts, but ordinary people can also use it.

Text:
So produk adalah benda paling penting dalam menentukan strategi marketing kita.

Cari masalah.

Kemudian hasilkan produk terbaik yang mampu selesaikan masalah tersebut.

Who know, you might be the next Steve Jobs. Hehe.
Translated Text:
So the product is the most important object in determining our marketing strategy.

Look for trouble.

Then produce the best product that can solve the problem.

Who knows, you might be the next Steve Jobs. Haha.

Text:
2) Fokus kepada user experience

"Focus on creating a universe of sensations, experiences, and values that the person gets when they buy your product."

Inilah ideologi marketing Steve Jobs yang paling seksi.
Translated Text:
2) Fokus kepada user experience

"Focus on creating a universe of sensations, experiences, and values that the person gets when they buy your product."

Inilah ideologi marketing Steve Jobs yang paling seksi.

Text:
Jangan fokus kepada harga. 

Jangan fokus kepada features. 

Tapi fokus kepada pelanggan!

When we take care of our customer, they will take care of our business.
Translated Text:
Don't focus on price.

Don't focus on features.

But focus on the customer!

When we take care of our customers, they will take care of our business.

Text:
Ideologi ini bukan digunakan oleh Apple sahaja. 

Malah kebanyakan jenama-jenama besar memang menggunakan ideologi ini.

Tengok macam mana Nike dan Adidas mempraktikkan benda yang sama dalam syarikat diorang. Sebab akhirnya, pelanggan akan mencari jenama yang dekat dengan mereka.
Translated Text:
This ideology is not only used by Apple.

In fact, most big brands do use this ideology.

See how Nike and Adidas practice the same thing in people's companies. Because in the end, customers will look for brands that are close to them.

Text:
3) Jadikan pelanggan sebagai promoter

Kalau korang perasan Apple user ni bukan sekadar user biasa. Haha. Lagi2 jenis ifag ni.

Apple users are advocates, sponsors, and fans of the brand.
Translated Text:
3) Turn the customer into a promoter

If you have noticed that this Apple user is not just an ordinary user. Ha ha. More types of ifag's.

Apple users are advocates, sponsors, and fans of the brand.

Text:
Bagi saya strategi marketing ni sangat brilliant tau. 

Sebab word of mouth marketing ni sangat2 lah berkesan untuk dapatkan pelanggan baru.

Korang bayangkan, kalau saya jual coklat & saya bagitahu coklat ni sedap gila. Korang yakin tak?
Translated Text:
For me, this marketing strategy is very brilliant.

Because word of mouth marketing is very effective in getting new customers.

Can you imagine, if I sell chocolate & I told you this chocolate is insanely delicious. Are you sure?

Text:
Well, some of you mungkin yakin. Tapi sebahagian lagi akan kata,

Eleh memanglah dia kata sedap dah dia yang jual. Haha!

Tapii cuba korang bayangkan kawan korang yang kata, 

Weh sedap gila coklat ni. Baik kau beli kat Fezza tu.
Translated Text:
Well, some of you may be convinced. But some will say,

It's true that he said it was delicious and he was the one who sold it. Haha!

But try to imagine your friend saying,

Wow, this chocolate is crazy good. Well, you buy it at Fezza.

Text:
Probability untuk korang beli akan meningkat 99% daripada bila saya promote. 

Sebab apa?

Sebab kawan korang tu takde apa kaitan pun dengan bisnes saya. So korang akan rasa pandangan dia adalah sangat genuine.

Jadi itulah apa yang korang kena buat.
Translated Text:
The probability for you to buy will increase 99% from when I promote.

Why?

Because your friend has nothing to do with my business. So you will feel that his views are very genuine.

So that's what you have to do.

Text:
1. Organize masa & kerja

Ini memang sangat2 penting. Kalau tak organize masa dengan letakkan prioriti pada setiap kerja, macam mana kita nak kekal produktif?

End up, akan ada kerja yang patutnya siap hari ni, tak siap2.
Translated Text:
1. Organize time & work

This is very important. If we don't organize our time by prioritizing each job, how are we going to stay productive?

End up, there will be work that should be finished today, but not finished.

Text:
Jadi lagi masalah bila tugasan tu ada kaitan dengan team member kita yang lain. Disebabkan kita delay task kita, kerja mereka pun terbantut sama.

Jadi sebab itu, kita kena organize masa & kerja betul2. Hari ni nak siapkan task apa, pukul berapa, prioriti yang mana.
Translated Text:
So there is another problem when the task is related to our other team members. Because we delay our task, their work also stagnates.

So that's why, we have to organize time & work right. Today I want to prepare what task, what time, which priority.

Text:
Semua tu kena rancang seelok-eloknya sehari sebelum.

Petang sebelum clock-out tu siapkan planning untuk esok. Jadi pagi esok start kerja dah tahu nak buat apa, nak siapkan apa. 

Ada banyak software yang kita boleh guna. Macam team saya banyak guna Trello. Team korang guna apa?
Translated Text:
Everything has to be planned the day before.

In the evening before the clock-out, prepare the planning for tomorrow. So tomorrow morning when I start work I know what to do, what to prepare.

There are many software that we can use. My team uses Trello a lot. What does your team use?

Text:
2. Keep in touch dengan colleague

Okay ni serius sangat penting. 

Kadang kerja dari rumah ni boleh jadi overwhelming disebabkan kita tak dapat jumpa colleague kita. Tak-tak, bukan nak kata keluarga kita tak baik atau menganggu.
Translated Text:
2. Keep in touch with colleagues

Okay, this is seriously very important.

Sometimes working from home can be overwhelming because we can't see our colleagues. No, no, I don't mean to say that our family is bad or annoying.

Text:
Cumanya, colleague kita lagi memahami nature of work kita.

Sebab tu, walaupun korang WFH, waktu bekerja cuba untuk sentiasa keep in touch dengan colleague lain.

Kalau korang leader, lagilah penting untuk sentiasa ambil tahu pasal anak buah.
Translated Text:
It's just that our colleagues still understand the nature of our work.

That's why, even if you are WFH, when working try to always keep in touch with other colleagues.

If you are a leader, it is important to always be aware of your subordinates.

Text:
Ambil tahu bukan dalam skop kerja saja, ambil tahu juga mental well-being mereka.

Ambil berat pasal mereka.

Sebab yang bekerja dengan kita ni manusia. Bukannya robot atau mesin yang takde perasaan.
Translated Text:
Find out not only in the scope of work, also find out their mental well-being.

Take care of them.

Because those who work with us are human beings. Not a robot or a machine that has no feelings.

Text:
3. Wujudkan ruang pejabat

Korang jangan salah faham pulak, bukan suruh beli perabot semua. Hahaha

Wujudkan ruang pejabat ni, cukup sekadar sediakan satu ruang berasingan untuk kita buat kerja.
Translated Text:
3. Create an office space

Don't get me wrong, I'm not telling you to buy all the furniture. Haha

Create this office space, just provide a separate space for us to work.

Text:
Tapi ikutlah keselesaan masing2 dan tak perlu pun untuk upgrade perabot2 semua. 

Tapi kalau rasa perlu dan ada kemampuan, why not kan?

Sebab boleh jadi lama jugak ni kita kena kerja dari rumah. Bila ada ruang yang selesa, insyaAllah produktiviti pun akan meningkat.
Translated Text:
But follow each other's comfort and there is no need to upgrade all the furniture.

But if you feel the need and have the ability, why not?

Because it can be a long time since we have to work from home. When there is a comfortable space, God willing, productivity will increase.

Text:
4. Berhenti bila tiba masanya

Ingat ya kawan2, kita ni manusia.

Even mesin pun kena ada waktu untuk rehat. 

Macam gitulah kita kena layan diri kita. 

Berikan ruang serta masa untuk minda kita berehat daripada urusan2 kerja.
Translated Text:
4. Stop when the time comes

Remember, friends, we are human.

Even the machine has to have time to rest.

That's how we have to treat ourselves.

Give space and time for our minds to rest from work.

Text:
So kita tak rasa saturated sehingga muncul rasa menyampah nak buat kerja tu dah. Haha

Bersosial, ambil angin dekat luar, bersenam.

Itu semua nampak macam bukan kerja hakiki, tapi percayalah ianya sangat membantu untuk increase productivity kita.
Translated Text:
So we don't feel saturated to the point of feeling like it's a waste to do the work. Haha

Socialize, get some fresh air, exercise.

It all looks like it's not real work, but believe me it's very helpful to increase our productivity.

Text:
5. Last but not least: Jagalah kesihatan fizikal & mental

Kadang saya rasa WFH ni boleh tingkatkan masalah kesihatan mental.

Tapi bukan saya je rasa, memang faktanya begitu.

Pandemik kali ni memang betul-betul beri kesan yang negatif untuk kesihatan mental kita terutamanya.
Translated Text:
5. Last but not least: Take care of physical health & mentally

Sometimes I think this WFH can increase mental health problems.

But I don't think so, that's the fact.

This pandemic really has a negative effect on our mental health especially.

Text:
Sebab itu penting sangat2 untuk kita jaga keadaan mental kita.

Kalau ada masalah, jangan simpan sorang2. Ceritakan pada kawan yang kalian percaya atau pergilah kepada pakar.

Kalau korang tak tahu nak cerita pada siapa, boleh je call befriendersKL.
Translated Text:
That's why it's so important for us to take care of our mental state.

If there is a problem, don't keep anyone. Tell a friend you trust or go to a specialist.

If you don't know who to tell, you can call befriendersKL.

Text:
4) Spend time dengan team.

Serius guys, penting gila benda ni.

Takde benda yang lebih penting daripada perasaan dihargai oleh leader sendiri. Trust me. 

Sesibuk mana pun, call dan text our team. Walaupun ya,kita tak cukup masa. Tapi cuba juga boleh?
Translated Text:
4) Spend time with the team.

Seriously guys, this thing is crazy important.

There is nothing more important than feeling appreciated by the leader himself. Trust me.

No matter how busy you are, call and text our team. Although yes, we don't have enough time. But can you try?

Text:
Spend masa untuk dengar idea mereka, 
bagi ruang untuk mereka cerita apa masalah yang ada.

Sambil makan ke minum, dengar apa masalah dan ajar mereka cara selesaikan. Sekarang PKP mungkin tak mampu la makan minum sama.

try to call, text or email!
Translated Text:
Spend time listening to their ideas,
give them space to tell what the problem is.

While eating and drinking, listen to what the problem is and teach them how to solve it. Now the PKP may not be able to eat and drink the same.

try to call, text or email!

Text:
Ada satu quotes Richard Branson ni. Dia kata,

Clients do not come first. Employees come first. Take care of your employees, they will take care of the clients. 

And guess what?

Clients will take care our business. Hehe
Translated Text:
Ada satu quotes Richard Branson ni. Dia kata,

Clients do not come first. Employees come first. Take care of your employees, they will take care of the clients.

Text:
5. Be proactive with feedback

Jangan tunggu masalah jadi besar baru nak fikir cara untuk selesaikan. 

As leader, kita kena nampak "10KM" ke depan masalah yang akan berlaku. 

Jadi macam mana kita nak tahu sesuatu masalah bakal terjadi?

Dapatkan feedback daripada team.
Translated Text:
5. Be proactive with feedback

Don't wait for the problem to become big before thinking about how to solve it.

As leaders, we have to see "10KM" ahead of the problems that will occur.

So how do we know if a problem is going to happen?

Get feedback from the team.

Text:
Listen to your team. Sebab mereka lagi tahu apa yang sedang berlaku. 

Sebab eventually, masalah2 kecil dalam feedback tu akan lead kepada satu masalah yang besar. 

That's why bila kita dapat feedback, kita try untuk selesaikan cepat2 sebelum dia jadi masalah yang lagi besar.
Translated Text:
Listen to your team. Because they still know what is happening.

Because eventually, small problems in the feedback will lead to a big problem.

That's why when we get feedback, we try to solve it quickly before it becomes a bigger problem.

Text:
Feedback ni tak semestinya kita collect dengan cara tradisional, isi form feedback tu. Aduh kamonlah dah 2021 kot. Haha. 

Feedback ni boleh jadi dalam bentuk informal juga. Dalam borak2 kosong antara kita & staff pun kita boleh tangkap.

Dapat feedback, terus selesaikan.
Translated Text:
We don't have to collect this feedback in the traditional way, fill out the feedback form. Oh well, it's already 2021. Haha.

This feedback can be in an informal form as well. In empty chats between us & We can arrest even the staff.

Get feedback, continue to solve.

Text:
Last tapi bukan la terakhir. 

6) First thing first, dont blame semua benda dekat team

Bila ada masalah jadi, saling menyalahkan ni takkan selesaikan apa-2 pun. Fokus pada solusi.
Translated Text:
Last but not the last.

6) First thing first, don't blame everything in the team

If there's a problem, blaming each other won't solve anything. Focus on solutions.

Text:
Kalau team salah, tegur secara jelas apa masalah dan bagitahu solusi untuk baiki. Be rasional. Bukan emosional. Elak campur hal-hal personal dalam urusan kerja. 

Tak kisah apa pun masalah. Sebab macam mana korang lead team, biasanya team kita akan duplicate ape benda kita buat.
Translated Text:
If the team is wrong, tell them clearly what the problem is and tell them how to fix it. Be rational. Not emotional. Avoid mixing personal matters in work matters.

No matter what the problem is. Because how do you lead a team, usually our team will duplicate what we do.

Text:

Share sikit ape pengalaman korang dalam handle team? Mungkin boleh kita sama-sama belajar.
Translated Text:
So yeah, lead by example. Is that okay? Hehe

Share a little about your experience in the handle team? Maybe we can learn together.
