Text:
1. Makesure matlamat jelas 

Bila ada team, kena pastikan semua bergerak kepada satu direction yang jelas. 

Walaupun posisi berbeza, ada editor, designer, marketer, content creator and macam2 lagi, kena makesure semua ada the same understanding terhadap target company.
Translated Text:
1. Makesure the goal is clear

When there is a team, you have to make sure everyone moves in a clear direction.

Even though the positions are different, there are editors, designers, marketers, content creators and so on, you have to make sure everyone has the same understanding of the target company.

Text:
Misalnya, target bulan ni 10 juta, setiap orang kena jelas target tu dan kena tahu apa strategi yang kita nak guna untuk capai. 

Nilai 10 juta tu bukan terletak cuma pada 1 orang ahli team, but it is a collective effort as a team okay!
Translated Text:
For example, this month's target is 10 million, everyone has to be clear about that target and know what strategy we want to use to achieve it.

The value of 10 million does not lie only on 1 team member, but it is a collective effort as a team okay!

Text:
Kalau korang nak buat ads, mestilah kena ada content kan? Datang dari siapa content tu? 

Dah ada content kena la produce dalam bentuk video atau gambar ke, siapa yang buat kalau bukan designer dan edittor kan? 

Lepas tu dah ada semua benda, siapa pula nak run ads tu? Ha??
Translated Text:
If you want to make ads, there must be content, right? Who did the content come from?

There is content that needs to be produced in the form of videos or pictures, who does it if not the designer and editor, right?

After that everything is there, who wants to run the ads? Huh??

Text:
So nampak tak nilai 10 juta tu? Bukan 1 individu yang akan datangkan 10 juta tu, tapi 1 'team' yang bagus akan bawa kita capai target. 

Jangan biarkan team korang terawang-awang tanpa tahu halatuju diorang. Bayangkan bawa kereta tanpa destinasi. Excident kita bhai huhu
Translated Text:
So it looks like it's not worth 10 million? It is not 1 individual who will bring the 10 million, but a good 'team' will take us to reach the target.

Don't let your team wander without knowing where people are going. Imagine taking a car without a destination. Our accident bhai huhu

Text:
Kata Rose Bryant Smith, 

The leader must hold everyone accountable for what they’re achieving, how they go about it, the culture and the values of the team.
Translated Text:
Kata Rose Bryant Smith, 

The leader must hold everyone accountable for what they’re achieving, how they go about it, the culture and the values of the team.

Text:
2. Semak diri sendiri

As leader, kita kena selalu check diri kita. 

Lalau buat strategi ni, apa pro n cons dia?
Ape ilmu kita kena kuasai so boleh guide team dengan baik?

Apa yg kita kurang?
Sekarang team makin ramai, boleh ke guna cara sama?
Translated Text:
2. Check yourself

As leaders, we have to always check ourselves.

Then make this strategy, what are its pros and cons?
What knowledge do we have to master so we can guide the team well?

What are we missing?
Now the team is getting bigger, can we use the same method?

Text:
Sentiasa semak apa yang kita buat untuk team. Sebab team sangat penting untuk capai tujuan yang tinggi menggunung.

Well of course judgement kita takkan selalunya betul. Dalam kebanyakan masa kita selalu nak menangkan diri kita.
Translated Text:
Always check what we do for the team. Because the team is very important to achieve a lofty goal.

Well of course our judgment will not always be right. Most of the time we always want to win ourselves.

Text:
Itulah gunanya mentor.

Orang yang lebih berpengalaman daripada kita. Someone yang can make better judgement than us. Mentor korang siapa?
Translated Text:
That's what a mentor is for.

People who are more experienced than us. Someone who can make better judgment than us. Who is your mentor?

Text:
3. Kenalpasti & buang toksik dalam team

Kita semua manusia. Pasti ada kelemahan.

Macam mana kita nakkan yang terbaik pun, pasti akan ada toxic behaviour dalam team kita.

So, sangat penting untuk kita kenalpasti cepat2 dan singkirkan trait tu daripada team kita.
Translated Text:
3. Identify & get rid of toxins in the team

We are all human. There must be weaknesses.

No matter how much we want the best, there will definitely be toxic behavior in our team.

So, it is very important for us to quickly identify and remove that trait from our team.

Text:
Saya tak kata buang pekerja ya, don't get me wrong pulak~ 

Saya kata buang toxic trait tu.

Tegur orang yang melakukan kesalahan tu. Kalau kesalahan tu melibatkan 2,3 orang, panggil & kumpulkan mereka. Address the issue properly & ask them to improve.
Translated Text:
I didn't say to fire employees, don't get me wrong~

I said get rid of that toxic trait.

Reprimand the person who made the mistake. If the offense involves 2,3 people, call & collect them. Address the issue properly & ask them to improve.

Text:
Kita memang kena tegas dalam team, tapi kita jangan lupa kita dan mereka sama2 manusia. 

Dan seperti lazimnya seorang manusia, dia akan sentiasa melakukan kesilapan. 

Kamon, kadang2 kita pun tak sedar apa yang kita buat tu toksik kan. Hahah
Translated Text:
We do have to be firm in the team, but we must not forget that we and they are human beings.

And as a human being, he will always make mistakes.

Kamon, sometimes we don't even realize what we do is toxic, right? Hahaha

Text:
1) Temuduga semua pekerja sendiri

Kalau korang pergi temuduga dekat Tesla atau SpaceX, ada kebarangkalian yang korang akan jumpa Elon Musk ni.

Waktu awal-awal dulu, memang setiap pekerja akan melalui proses temuduga stage akhir dengan Elon Musk sehinggalah syarikat berkembang
Translated Text:
1) Interview all employees themselves

If you go to an interview at Tesla or SpaceX, there is a probability that you will meet Elon Musk.

In the early days, every employee would go through the final stage interview process with Elon Musk until the company grew

Text:
Proses temuduganya agak panjang. 

Daripada proses biasa, dipanggil HR, dipanggil Project Manager kemudian akhir sekali dengan Elon Musk sendiri. 

Jadi kalau korang nak bina team yang super power. Korang mesti terlibat dalam proses itu sendiri.
Translated Text:
The interview process is quite long.

From the usual process, called HR, called Project Manager then finally with Elon Musk himself.

So if you want to build a super powerful team. You must be involved in the process yourself.

Text:
Saya apply benda sama macam ni dalam company saya handle skrg, first IV oleh HR, second oleh saya sendiri. 

Bagi saya process ni sangat penting, sebab siapa saja yang masuk dlm your team, dia akan memberi kesan pada kelajuan capai target, culture dalam company, dan banyak lagi.
Translated Text:
I applied the same thing like this in my company handle now, first IV by HR, second by myself.

For me, this process is very important, because whoever joins your team, he will have an impact on the speed of reaching the target, the culture in the company, and much more.

Text:
2) Apa masalah yang pernah diselesaikan?

Ini soalan wajib yang Elon Musk akan tanya pada candidate 'cream of the cream' yang dah lalui bermacam tapisan tu. 

Elon kata, soalan ni sangat penting untuk tahu adakah candidate tu yang jumpa dan cari solusi untuk masalah tu.
Translated Text:
2) What problems have been solved?

This is a mandatory question that Elon Musk will ask the 'cream of the cream' candidate who has gone through various screenings.

Elon said, this question is very important to know if the candidate has found and found a solution to the problem.

Text:
Kalau memang dia yang selesaikan, dia akan ceritakan dengan sangat detail. 

Tapi kalau dia hanya salah seorang 'sleeping partner' dalam team, dia akan susah untuk jawab soalan ni. 

Dan saya setuju part ni! kaki sembang ni biasa dia tak tahu nak solve macam mana pun masalah tu.
Translated Text:
If he is the one to finish it, he will tell the story in great detail.

But if he is just one of the 'sleeping partners' in the team, it will be difficult for him to answer this question.

And I agree with this part! This conversation is normal, he doesn't know how to solve the problem.

Text:
Elon kata,

"Because anyone who struggled hard with a problem never forgets it.

Sebab tu bila kita jadi leader, kita yg kena sit down dan solve problem dulu, sebab mmg tugas kita untuk guide team along the way.
Translated Text:
Elon said,

"Because anyone who struggled hard with a problem never forgets it.

That's why if we become leaders, we have to sit down and solve problems first, because it's our job to guide the team along the way.

Text:
3) Selesaikan masalah 

Bukan setakat tanya, dia jugak minta candidate tu selesaikan masalah yang berkaitan dengan jawatan yang dia apply. 

Salah seorang candidate ni pernah kongsi yang Elon tanya soalan Fizik waktu dalam temuduga dia.
Translated Text:
3) Solve the problem

He didn't just ask, he also asked the candidate to solve problems related to the position he applied for.

One of these candidates once shared that Elon asked a physics question during his interview.

Text:
Dia tanya, 

You're sitting in a canoe floating in a pool with a brick in your lap. You drop the brick overboard. What happens to the pool's water level?

Soalan ni nampak simple, tapi kita boleh tahu level kefahaman serta ketajaman seseorang dengan jawapan yang diberi.
Translated Text:
He asked,

You're sitting in a canoe floating in a pool with a brick in your lap. You drop the brick overboard. What happens to the pool's water level?

This question looks simple, but we can know the level of understanding and acuity of a person by the answer given.

Text:
Antara soalan paling saya suka tanya dalam IV adalah, 

"Macam mana awak nak naikkan income company dari 5000, ke 100,000?" 

Tell me anything. 

Dari situ kita boleh tengok cara fikir, cara bertindak dan pengalaman dia dalam menyelesaikan masalah.
Translated Text:
Among the questions I like to ask the most in IV are,

"How do you want to increase the company's income from 5000 to 100,000?"

Tell me anything.

From there we can see his way of thinking, his way of acting and his experience in solving problems.

Text:
Tapi korang jangan pulak tanya soalan tak berkaitan. Elon musk sendiri cakap, 

"I'm not necessarily looking for someone who has brilliant analytical ability if their job is going to be assembling hardware."
Translated Text:
Tapi korang jangan pulak tanya soalan tak berkaitan. Elon musk sendiri cakap, 

"I'm not necessarily looking for someone who has brilliant analytical ability if their job is going to be assembling hardware."

Text: Kalau dia apply posisi as copywriter, awak jangan ler tanya macam mana nak buat akaun pula dah. hahah (walaupun mungkin juga dia tahu sebab ada pengalaman haha)
Translated Text: If he applies for the position of copywriter, don't ask him how to create an account. hahah (although maybe he knows because he has experience hahah)

Text:
4) Jangan risau pasal sijil

Elon memang terkenal dengan sikap ni. Dia memang tak ambil port sangat pasal degree ke diploma. 

Tapi bukan la maksud tak penting pula dah. Dont get me wrong guys, please ya. 😂
Translated Text:
4) Don't worry about the certificate

Elon is famous for this attitude. He really doesn't care much about degrees and diplomas.

But that doesn't mean it's not important. Don't get me wrong guys, please yes. 😂

Text:
Ramai innovator hebat macam Bill Gates, Steve Jobs, Zuckerberg, Larry Page yang takde pun degree.

Dia kata,

"If you had a chance to hire them,of course, that'd be a good idea."
Translated Text:
Ramai innovator hebat macam Bill Gates, Steve Jobs, Zuckerberg, Larry Page yang takde pun degree.

Dia kata,

"If you had a chance to hire them,of course, that'd be a good idea."

Text:
Tapi tu bukan bermaksud yang ada sijil ni tak berguna pulak. Korang jangan pelik-pelik eh. 

Maksud Elon ni jangan letakkan sijil tu sebagai syarat utama.

Tak semua orang ada peluang untuk sambung belajar.
Translated Text:
But that does not mean that having this certificate is useless. Don't be weird.

What Elon means is don't put the certificate as the main condition.

Not everyone has the opportunity to continue studying.

Text:
Yela, maksud saya tu kalau sijil berlambak lepas tu satu benda tak boleh buat, macam mana nak jadi a good team members kan. 

Team work means, a group of people who are working together to solve the problem, achieve target.
Translated Text:
Yes, what I mean is that if the certificate is delayed, that's one thing you can't do, how can you be a good team member, right?

Team work means, a group of people who are working together to solve the problem, achieve the target.

Text:
Tapi, kalau korang tengah belajar sekarang ni janganlah demotivated.

Sebab 70% billionaire dekat dunia ni ada college degree okay! 

So kalau korang ada degree, master, PhD, probability untuk korang jadi billionaire lagi tinggi. Bukan saya kata ni, statistik yang kata. Hahaha
Translated Text:
But, if you are studying now, don't be demotivated.

Because 70% of billionaires in the world have a college degree okay!

So if you have a degree, master's, PhD, the probability of you becoming a billionaire is even higher. I didn't say this, the statistics said. Haha

Text:
5) Cari yang terbaik

"Don't settle for anything less than the best candidate."

Ini memang prinsip Elon bila nak hire seseorang. Dia memang akan cari yang terbaik. No wonder lah team di belakang jenama Tesla dan SpaceX ni memang superpower.
Translated Text:
5) Find the best

"Don't settle for anything less than the best candidate."

This is Elon's principle when hiring someone. He will find the best. No wonder the team behind the Tesla and SpaceX brands is a superpower.

Text:
Pernah satu kali tu, 

SpaceX baru buat yogurt stand dekat hq diorang. Elon arahkan Dolly Singh (bekas Talent Director SpaceX), 

"Go to Pinkberry (macam Llaollao dekat Malaysia) and find me the employee of the month."
Translated Text:
Once upon a time,

SpaceX just made a yogurt stand near everyone's HQ. Elon directed Dolly Singh (former SpaceX Talent Director),

"Go to Pinkberry (like Llaollao near Malaysia) and find me the employee of the month."

Text:
Saya setuju tapi tak 100% la. Sebab saya duduk dalam company yang nak develop youth.

So kalau tak bagi peluang pada orang lain yang baru nak up, baru nak cari pengalaman, takde sape akan bagi peluang pada orang-2 macam ni nak develop diri dia.
Translated Text:
I agree but not 100%. Because I sit in a company that wants to develop youth.

So if you don't give a chance to other people who just want to upgrade, who are just looking for experience, no one will give a chance to people like this to develop themselves.

Text:
6) Attitude paling utama

"No-assholes policy."

Elon takkan hire orang tu bila attitude dia ni macam harem biarpun dia ni super-talented. Yang ni saya sangat3 setuju. 

Tahu kenapa?

Sebab takde masalah yang boleh diselesaikan seorang diri.
Translated Text:
6) The most important attitude

"No-assholes policy."

Elon will not hire that person if his attitude is like a harem even though he is super-talented. I totally agree with this one.

Know why?

Because there is no problem that can be solved alone.

Text:
Tapi melihat kepada pengalaman saya, susah nak detect benda ni dalam interview session sebab masa ni semua orang nak play safe. 

Yang selalu datang lambat kerja pun akan tiba2 datang awal hahah. To be safe, awak call tempat dia kerja sebelum ni.
Translated Text:
But looking at my experience, it's hard to detect this thing in the interview session because at this time everyone wants to play safe.

Those who always come late to work will suddenly come early hahah. To be safe, you call where he worked before.

Text:
So macam tu lah. 

Kalau korang majikan, boleh jadikan sebagai guideline untuk hire your team. 

Kalau korang pekerja, boleh jadikan sebagai guideline untuk jadi the best in your team.

Anyway, follow @FezzaHussin & jangan lupa RT. Thank you for your support.  Will share more.
Translated Text:
So it's like that.

If you are an employer, you can use it as a guideline for hiring your team.

If you are an employee, you can use it as a guideline to be the best in your team.

Anyway, follow @FezzaHussin & don't forget to RT. Thank you for your support. Will share more.

Text:
Success story. 

Zuckerberg bina Facebook dari dalam bilik dorm, sehingga sekarang menjadi antara syarikat yang paling tinggi nilainya di dunia. 

Kisah ni jadi sebab utama kenapa pekerja yang memang super talented nak bekerja dengan dia. Huhu
Translated Text:
Success story.

Zuckerberg built Facebook from a dorm room, until now it is one of the most valuable companies in the world.

This story is the main reason why super talented employees want to work with him. Huh

Text:
Bila kita bawa orang masuk dalam team, isu paling utama isu trust. Boleh ke dia buat kerja? Boleh ke bagi dia buat keputusan? 

Saya hadapi benda sama sebiji macam ni bila team saya makin ramai orang. Dari 4 sampai ke 30 sekarang. Tapi tengok cara Zuckerburg layan staff dia.
Translated Text:
When we bring people into the team, the most important issue is trust. Can he do work? Is it possible for him to make a decision?

I face the same thing when my team has more people. From 4 to 30 now. But look at the way Zuckerburg treats his staff.

Text:
Kepercayaan yang dia bagi pada staff. 

Tak semua keputusan dalam syarikat diputuskan oleh Zuckerberg atau top management Facebook. 

Kebanyakan keputusan (yang berkaitan) datang daripada pekerja yang bergelumang dalam masalah tersebut.
Translated Text:
The trust he gave to the staff.

Not all decisions in the company are decided by Zuckerberg or Facebook's top management.

Most of the (relevant) decisions come from the workers who are wallowing in the problem.

Text:
Zuckerberg siap bagi kepercayaan dekat pekerja dia yang baru beberapa bulan bekerja untuk kenal satu features baru dekat Facebook - Facebook Graph. 

Saya setuju dengan cara ni, bagi peluang team kita develop dan selesaikan masalah. This is how kita grow our team.
Translated Text:
Zuckerberg is ready to trust his employees who have only been working for a few months to get to know a new feature on Facebook - Facebook Graph.

I agree with this method, for the opportunity for our team to develop and solve problems. This is how we grow our team.

Text:
Perwatakan Zuckerberg yang humble. 

Kalau perasan, gambar Zuckerberg kebanyakannya dengan t-shirt & jeans je. Ini yang mungkin kurang kadang2 ada pada certain leader kat luar sana. Tak semestinya kita boss kita kena mewah or pakai kereta hebat2 kan? Ambil sekadar perlu mungkin?
Translated Text:
Zuckerberg's humble character.

If you notice, Zuckerberg's pictures are mostly with t-shirts & just jeans. This is something that may be lacking in certain leaders out there. It's not necessary that we, our boss, have to be luxurious or use a great car, right? Take it as necessary as possible?

Text:
Perwatakan dia buatkan pekerja dia rasa macam,

"He is indeed one of us."

Disebabkan itu pekerja dia rasa lebih dekat dengan dia. 

Sekaligus takde rasa barrier untuk bercakap, cerita masalah produk dan solution yang mereka ada dekat dia.
Translated Text:
His character makes his employees feel like,

"He is indeed one of us."

Because of that his employees feel closer to him.

At the same time, there is no barrier to talk, talk about product problems and solutions they have with him.

Text:
Free food!

Bukan orang Malaysia je suka makanan percuma. Hahaha

Kebanyakan staf rasa sangat dihargai hanya dengan dapat makanan percuma.
Translated Text:
Free food!

It's not just Malaysians who like free food. Haha

Most of the staff feel very appreciated just by getting free food.

Text:
Kalau korang jadi bos nanti, selalu-selalulah belanja staf makan atau sentiasa penuhkan pantri dengan makanan. 

Konfem staf makin sayang & bisnes makin maju. Hehe
Translated Text:
If you become the boss later, always buy food for the staff or always fill the pantry with food.

Confem staff love more & business is progressing. Hehe

Text:

As a leader kita kena open, tak semua benda kita betul, tapi bukanlah semua benda kita salah 😅
Translated Text:
Wanting to build a good team is not easy but not impossible. It took me 6 months to develop the team. And until now I'm still learning.

As a leader we have to be open, not everything we do is right, but not everything we do is wrong 😅

Text:

Kalau siapa ada masalah nak grow team, jom kita sembang 😂. Tukar pendapat ke. Barulah seronok kan hehe

Learn from those who have succeeded, God willing your team will also excel!

If anyone has a problem growing a team, let's chat 😂. Change opinion to. It's just fun hehe

Text:
1. Elon Musk BUKAN founder Tesla

Tesla diasaskan oleh dua orang jurutera yang bernama Martin Eberhard and Marc Tarpenning pada 1 Julai 2003. 

Elon Musk sertai Tesla pada tahun 2004 kerana berkongsi idea yang sama dengan pelaburan awal USD6.3 Juta.
Translated Text:
1. Elon Musk is NOT the founder of Tesla

Tesla was founded by two engineers named Martin Eberhard and Marc Tarpenning on July 1, 2003.

Elon Musk joined Tesla in 2004 for sharing the same idea with an initial investment of USD6.3 Million.

Text:
2. Teknologi yang dibangunkan Tesla adalah sumber terbuka

Kebanyakan syarikat apabila membangunkan sesebuah teknologi (terutamanya teknologi baru) akan mempatenkan teknologi tersebut. 

Bermula Jun 2014, CEO Tesla Elon Musk mengumumkan langkah yang diambil syarikat berkenaan.
Translated Text:
2. The technology developed by Tesla is open source

Most companies when developing a technology (especially new technology) will patent the technology.

Beginning in June 2014, Tesla CEO Elon Musk announced the steps taken by the company.

Text: Dalam keterangannya, Elon Musk menyebut bahawa pesaing sebenar Tesla bukan sebuah syarikat yang membangunkan kenderaan elektrik, tetapi dengan kenderaan biasa yang mencemarkan alam sekitar.
Translated Text: In his testimony, Elon Musk mentioned that Tesla's real competitor is not a company that develops electric vehicles, but with conventional vehicles that pollute the environment.

Text:
3. Kenderaan Tesla boleh dikemaskini dimana-mana

Macam smartphone yang kita guna, bila conmect dengan wifi terus boleh update software kan?

Kereta Tesla pun sama jugak. 

Tengah parking depan rumah pun, dia boleh auto-update. Tak perlu pergi pusat servis untuk update.
Translated Text:
3. Tesla vehicles can be updated anywhere

Like the smartphone we use, when conmect with wifi you can update the software right?

Tesla cars are the same.

Even in the middle of the parking lot in front of the house, he can auto-update. No need to go to the service center to update.

Text:
4.Tesla mempunyai pengkalan supercharge terbanyak di dunia

Walaupun Tesla masih remaja jika dibandingkan dengan syarikat automotif lain, tapi Tesla ada stesen supercharge terbanyak di dunia. 

Kenapa kalau Tesla ada banyak stesen supercharge? Apa yang menakjubkan?
Translated Text:
4.Tesla has the most supercharge base in the world

Although Tesla is still a teenager when compared to other automotive companies, Tesla has the most supercharge stations in the world.

Why does Tesla have so many supercharge stations? What is amazing?

Text:
Bayangkan Perodua ada stesen minyak terbanyak di dunia. Sumber pendapatan syarikat mereka berganda-ganda. 

Bilalah gamaknya stesen supercharger Tesla nak ada kat Malaysia gamaknya. Haha.
Translated Text:
Imagine that Perodua has the most gas stations in the world. Their company's source of income is doubled.

When will the Tesla supercharger station be available in Malaysia? Haha.

Text:
5. Tesla Model 3 merupakan antara kereta paling selamat di dunia

Di belakang Subaru, Lexus & Mercedes, syarikat muda ini berjaya menjadi antara kereta yang paling selamat di dunia. 

Btw, korang tahu tak yang kereta Tesla ni tak boleh meletup macam kereta biasa?
Translated Text:
5. Tesla Model 3 is one of the safest cars in the world

Behind Subaru, Lexus & Mercedes, this young company managed to become one of the safest cars in the world.

Btw, did you know that Tesla cars can't explode like normal cars?

Text:
6. (Bonus sebab teruja) Tesla Gigafactory dikuasakan sepenuhnya dengan tenaga solar

Tesla Gigafactory ni bila siap sepenuhnya nanti adalah bangunan yang terbesar di dunia. 

Saiznya melebihi 15,000,000 sqft. Kalau nak compare, rumah bungalow biasa sizenya 3000 sqft.
Translated Text:
6. (Bonus reason to be excited) The Tesla Gigafactory is powered entirely by solar energy

The Tesla Gigafactory when fully completed will be the largest building in the world.

Its size is over 15,000,000 sqft. If you want to compare, a normal bungalow house is 3000 sqft.

Text:
Jadi saiz tesla Gigafactory ni bersamaan dengan 5000 rumah bungalow yang biasa kita tengok. 

Dan pakai tenaga solar? Serius lah?!
Translated Text:
So the size of this tesla Gigafactory is equivalent to 5000 bungalow houses that we usually see.

And use solar energy? Are you serious?!

Text:
Samsung diasaskan oleh Lee Chull pada tahun 1938. Sewaktu ditubuhkan, syarikat Samsung cuma mempunyai 40 orang pekerja dan berfokus kepada model bisnes trading.

Cuma menjual barang-barang runcit harian.
Translated Text:
Samsung was founded by Lee Chull in 1938. When it was established, the Samsung company only had 40 employees and focused on a trading business model.

Just selling daily groceries.

Text:
Pada tahun 1950-an, Samsung mengembangkan model bisnes mereka. 

Mereka mula menceburkan diri dalam industri kewangan iaitu insurans, sekuriti (pelaburan) dan retail.
Translated Text:
In the 1950s, Samsung expanded their business model.

They started venturing into the financial industry namely insurance, securities (investment) and retail.

Text:
Tahun 1960-an pulak, Samsung mula masuk dalam segmen elektronik (yang kini jenamanya sangat popular).

Apa produk pertama yang dihasilkan?

Yup, TV!
Translated Text:
In the 1960s, Samsung began to enter the electronics segment (which is now a very popular brand).

What was the first product produced?

Yep, TV!

Text:
1983, Samsung mula mengeluarkan komputer pertama mereka. 

Tahu tak, komputer ciptaan Samsung pada waktu tu 14 kali ganda lebih 'advance' daripada komputer yang dibangunkan Microsoft!
Translated Text:
1983, Samsung began to produce their first computer.

Did you know, the computers created by Samsung at that time were 14 times more 'advanced' than the computers developed by Microsoft!

Text:
Sekarang?

Kebanyakan daripada kita cuma tahu Samsung ni syarikat elektronik je, tapi Samsung ni lebih besar daripada tu. 

Lagi besar daripada apa yang kita semua bayangkan.
Translated Text:
Now?

Most of us only know that Samsung is an electronics company, but Samsung is bigger than that.

Bigger than what we all imagine.

Text:
Pada tahun 2019, pendapatan Samsung dilaporkan melebihi USD 200 billion. 

Bagaimana jika ditulis dengan angka nilai ini. 

200,000,000,000!
Translated Text:
In 2019, Samsung's revenue was reported to exceed USD 200 billion.

What if written with this value number.

200,000,000,000!

Text:
Macam mana boleh capai angka sebesar tu? 

Mudah je. 

Samsung ni terdiri daripada 80 gabungan bisnes yang bermacam-macam jenis. Bukan daripada sektor elektronik je.
Translated Text:
How can you reach such a big number?

It's easy.

Samsung consists of 80 business combinations of various types. Not from the electronics sector.

Text:
Dibawah kategori pembinaan & kejuruteraan:

Samsung Engineering & Construction
Samsung Trading & Investment
Samsung Heavy Industries

Dibawah kategori elektronik:

Samsung Electronics
Samsung Eletro-Mechanics
Samsung Techwin
Samsung Mobile Display
Samsung Digital Imaging
Translated Text:
Under the coaching & vocational:

Samsung Engineering & Construction
Samsung Trading & Investments
Samsung Heavy Industries

Under electronics category:

Samsung Electronics
Samsung Electro-Mechanics
Samsung Techwin
Samsung Mobile Display
Samsung Digital Imaging

Text:
Dibawah kategori kewangan:

Samsung Life Insurance
Samsung Securities
Samsung Investment
Samsung Venture

Okay cukup.
Translated Text:
Under the financial category:

Samsung Life Insurance
Samsung Securities
Samsung Investments
Samsung Ventures

OK enough.

Text:
Samsung jugak terlibat dengan oil & gas, marketing, hotel & resort, medical center, automotif dan banyak lagi. 

Padu kan? Tapi apa benda yang Samsung buat kita jarang tahu?
Translated Text:
Samsung is also involved with Oil & gas, marketing, hotel & resorts, medical centers, automotive and many more.

Mixed right? But what are the things that Samsung makes us rarely know?

Text:
Samsung terlibat secara langsung dalam penghasilan peralatan-peralatan ketenteraan. 

Samsung juga membangunkan robot tentera Korea Selatan untuk mengurangkan keterlibatan tentera (manusia) di daerah DMZ.
Translated Text:
Samsung is directly involved in the production of military equipment.

Samsung also developed South Korean military robots to reduce military (human) involvement in the DMZ area.

Text:
Tak cukup padu? 

Samsung juga buat kereta kebal K-9! Kereta kebal ni bukan saja digunakan oleh Korea Selatan, tetapi beberapa negara lain antaranya, Turkey, Australia & India.
Translated Text:
Not cohesive enough?

Samsung also makes a K-9 tank! This tank is not only used by South Korea, but several other countries including Turkey, Australia & India.

Text:
Selain tu, Samsung juga membangunkan enjin jet. 

Ya tak bergurau, jenama sama yang menghasilkan peti sejuk rumah anda, membangunkan enjin jet.
Translated Text:
In addition, Samsung also developed a jet engine.

No kidding, the same brand that produces your home refrigerator, developed jet engines.

Text:
Selain tu, Samsung juga memiliki dan menguruskan taman terbesar di Korea Selatan. 

Dan Samsung juga memiliki bandar mereka sendiri. Samsung Digital City.
Translated Text:
Apart from that, Samsung also owns and manages the largest park in South Korea.

And Samsung also has their own bookie. Samsung DigitalCity.

Text:
Bukan itu je. 

Tahu Menara Burj Khalifa di Dubai? 

Samsung juga yang bina tu. 

Tak tahu Burj Khalifa? Takpe. Mesti tahu KLCC kan? 

Salah satu menara tu pun dibina oleh Samsung. 

Fuhh!
Translated Text:
That's not it.

Know the Burj Khalifa Tower in Dubai?

Samsung also built it.

Don't know Burj Khalifa? Nope. Must know KLCC right?

One of the towers was built by Samsung.

Phew!

Text:
Siapa sangka jenama yang kita tahu buat peti sejuk, tv dan telefon pintar, rupanya lebih besar daripada itu semua. 

Dan ini terhasil daripada cita-cita seorang lelaki biasa.
Translated Text:
Who would have thought that the brand we know makes refrigerators, tvs and smartphones, looks bigger than all that.

And this resulted from the ideals of a common man.

Text:
Mari kita sama-sama bina ekosistem perniagaan yang dapat memanfaatkan umat Islam secara menyeluruh. 

Bahkan mungkin lebih besar daripada Samsung. 

Follow @FezzaHussin untuk lebih banyak perkongsian :)
Translated Text:
Let's build a business ecosystem that can benefit Muslims as a whole.

Maybe even bigger than Samsung.

Follow @FezzaHussin for more sharing :)

Text:
Moga Allah permudahkan segala urusan kalian. Terima kasih sudi mengorbankan masa, tenaga dan harta kalian bersama kami. 

Kata Nabi SAW,

Sesiapa yang melapangkan kesusahan seseorang Muslim, maka Allah SWT akan melapangkan kesukarannya pada hari kiamat. 

(HR Bukhari & Muslim)
Translated Text:
May God ease all your affairs. Thank you for willing to sacrifice your time, energy and wealth with us.

The Prophet SAW said,

Whoever eases the hardships of a Muslim, then Allah SWT will ease his difficulties on the Day of Resurrection.

(HR Bukhari & Muslim)

Text:
Ahmad Dawjee Dadabhoy memang usahawan yang berjaya. Beliau lahir di India, tetapi pada tahun 1940-an, beliau memilih untuk menetap di Kuala Lumpur. 

Walaupun mempunyai perniagaan yang hebat & harta yang banyak, beliau memilih tinggal di rumah flat di Masjid India.
Translated Text:
Ahmad Dawjee Dadabhoy is indeed a successful entrepreneur. He was born in India, but in the 1940s, he chose to settle in Kuala Lumpur.

Despite having a great business & wealth, he chose to live in a flat in Masjid India.

Text:
Takde siapa yang sangka, seorang lelaki yang tinggal di rumah flat di Masjid India tu seorang hartawan yang dermawan.

Beliau kekal tinggal di rumah tu sampailah beliau meninggal dunia pada tahun 1987.
Translated Text:
No one would have thought that a man who lives in a flat in Masjid India is a philanthropic tycoon.

He remained living in that house until he died in 1987.

Text:
Sebelum beliau meninggal dunia, beliau telah mewakafkan beberapa harta untuk kegunaan umat islam. 

Antara harta beliau yang diwakafkan adalah sebidang tanah seluas 1.2 hektar di Jalan Perak (KL), , tiga buah rumah, sebuah kedai di Kompleks Pertama & pemilikan sahamnya.
Translated Text:
Before he died, he had endowed several properties for the use of Muslims.

Among his property that was waqf is a 1.2 hectare plot of land in Jalan Perak (KL), three houses, a shop in Kompleks Pertama & share ownership.

Text:
Kesemua harta yang diwakafkan tu sekarang diuruskan oleh MAIWP melalui “vesting order” yang dikeluarkan oleh Mahkamah Tinggi Kuala Lumpur. 

Tanah yang diwakafkan, telah dibangunkan dengan kerjasama MAIWP, Lembaga Tabung Haji (LTH) dan Bank Islam Malaysia Berhad (BIMB).
Translated Text:
All the waqf properties are now managed by MAIWP through a "vesting order" issued by the Kuala Lumpur High Court.

The waqf land was developed in collaboration with MAIWP, Lembaga Tabung Haji (LTH) and Bank Islam Malaysia Berhad (BIMB).

Text:
Sekarang ni, kalau korang lalu Jalan Perak dan nampak Menara Bank Islam, ketahuilah itu merupakan tanah yang diwakafkan oleh Ahmad Dawjee.

Seorang hartawan yang memilih kehidupan yang sangat zuhud dan sentiasa meletakkan kepentingan ummat dihadapan.
Translated Text:
Now, if you pass Jalan Perak and see Menara Bank Islam, know that it is land donated by Ahmad Dawjee.

A tycoon who chooses a very ascetic life and always puts the interests of the community first.

Text:
Bukan tu je harta yang ditinggalkan. Lepas beliau meninggal dunia, koleksi buku beliau telah dikumpulkan dan semuanya berjumlah 1077 buah buku. 

Buku-buku tu semua disimpan di Perpustakaan Institut Profesional Baitulmal, Kampung Pandan.
Translated Text:
That's not the property left behind. After he died, his book collection was collected and totaled 1077 books.

The books are all stored in the Baitulmal Professional Institute Library, Kampung Pandan.

Text:
“Apabila seseorang manusia mati, segala amalannya akan terputus kecuali daripada tiga sumber, iaitu sedekah jariah, ilmu yang boleh dimanfaatkan dan anak soleh yang sering mendoakannya.”

Hadis Riwayat Muslim (1631)

Muslim Narrated Hadith (1631)

Text:
Ada satu ketika, Nabi SAW bersabda:

“Wahai Sahabatku! Sesiapa sahaja di antara kamu yang menyumbangkan hartanya untuk dapat membebaskan telaga itu, lalu mendermakannya untuk umat, maka akan mendapat Syurga Allah.” (HR. Muslim)
Translated Text:
There was a time when the Prophet SAW said:

"Oh my friend! Anyone among you who donates his wealth to be able to free the well, then donates it to the people, then he will get God's Paradise." (HR. Muslim)

Text:
Tanpa berfikir panjang, Saidina Uthman terus bertemu dengan si Yahudi, pemilik telaga tersebut.

Saidina Uthman menawarkan harga yang sangat tinggi untuk membeli telaga tersebut. 

Tapi Yahudi tersebut menolak tawaran Saidina Uthman sebab takut perniagaannya terjejas.
Translated Text:
Without thinking, Saidina Uthman continued to meet the Jew, the owner of the well.

Saidina Uthman offered a very high price to buy the well.

But the Jew rejected Saidina Uthman's offer because he was afraid that his business would be affected.

Text:
Si Yahudi ni jual air telaga tersebut dengan harga yang sangat mahal. Jadi dia takmau lah jual dekat Saidina Uthman. 

Tapi Saidina Uthman ni bijak tau. Jadi beliau nego dengan si Yahudi tersebut dan tawarkan untuk beli setengah telaga tersebut dengan harga 12,000 dirham.
Translated Text:
The Jew sold the well water at a very high price. So he didn't want to sell it to Saidina Uthman.

But Saidina Uthman is smart. So he negotiated with the Jew and offered to buy half of the well for 12,000 dirhams.

Text:
Macam mana beli setengah telaga? Saidina Uthman tawarkan untuk pemilikan bergilir-gilir dengan pemilik asal tersebut. 

Si Yahudi tu pun setuju. Bisnes masih boleh jalan, 12,000 dirham pun dapat. 

Jadi dia sangka dia dah menang, tapj dia silap!
Translated Text:
How to buy half a well? Saidina Uthman offered to alternate ownership with the original owner.

The Jew agreed. Business can still work, even 12,000 dirhams can be obtained.

So he thought he had won, but he was wrong!

Text:
Bila tiba giliran Saidina Uthman, orang muslim datang dan mengambil air secara percuma untuk dua hari!

Jadi pada hari giliran si yahudi, takde dah orang datang beli. 

Bijak sungguh Saidina Uthman ni.
Translated Text:
When it was Saidina Uthman's turn, Muslims came and took water for free for two days!

So on the day of the Jew's turn, no one came to buy.

Saidina Uthman is really wise.

Text:
Bila bisnes dah makin teruk, si Yahudi ni pulak datang jumpa dengan Saidina Uthman dan bagitahu dia nak jual bahagian dia yang setengah tu dengan harga 8,000 dirham. 

Strategi menjadi!

Maka Saidina Uthman terus bersetuju dengan permintaan tersebut. Tapi tahu tak...
Translated Text:
When the business got worse, this Jew came to see Saidina Uthman and told him that he wanted to sell his half for 8,000 dirhams.

Strategy to be!

So Saidina Uthman continued to agree to the request. But don't you know...

Text:
Lepas Saidina Uthman beli, ada sahabat lain yang datang untuk belj telaga tersebut dengan harga 9 kali ganda daripada harga yang dibayar.

Maksudnya sahabat tu nak beli dengan harga 180,000 dirham!

Tapi Saidina Uthman tolak.
Translated Text:
After Saidina Uthman bought, another friend came to buy the well for 9 times the price paid.

That means the friend wants to buy it for 180,000 dirhams!

But Saidina Uthman refused.

Text:
Sahabat tu pun pelik dan tanya,

Siapa lagi yang sanggup membeli dengan harga yang lebih mahal daripada aku?

Tahu tak Saidina Uthman jawab apa?

Allah!

Subhanallah, hebatnyakan iman para sahabat ni.
Translated Text:
The friend was also strange and asked,

Who else is willing to buy at a more expensive price than me?

Do you know what Saidina Uthman answered?

God!

Subhanallah, great is the faith of these friends.

Text:
Kemudian, tumbuh pula pohon kurma disekelilinh telaga tersebut. Kemudian berkembang biak menjadi semakin banyak. 

Hasil tanaman tersebut dijual, sebahagiannya digunakan untuk membantu anak yatim & fakir miskin, sebahagian pula disimpan dalam akaun bank atas nama Saidina Uthman.
Translated Text:
Later, date trees grew around the well. Then multiply into more and more.

The crops are sold, some are used to help orphans & the poor, and some are kept in a bank account in the name of Saidina Uthman.

Text:
Jumlah tersebut makin bertambah dan bertambah saban tahun, sehinggakan jumlah terkumpul itu mampu membeli sebidang tanah yang strategik berhampiran Masjid Nabawi. 

Dan kemudian didirikan sebuah hotel pula!
Translated Text:
The amount increased and increased every year, until the accumulated amount was able to buy a strategic piece of land near the Prophet's Mosque.

And then a hotel was built!

Text:
Keuntungan daripada hasil perniagaan tersebut terus dimanfaatkan untuk kegunaan umat islam sehingga ke hari ini. 

Ya setelah lebih 1400 tahun harta yang diwakafkan oleh Saidina Uthman terus memberi manfaat untuk umat Islam.
Translated Text:
Profits from the business continue to be used for the use of Muslims until today.

Yes, after more than 1400 years, the property donated by Saidina Uthman continues to benefit Muslims.

Text:
Begitulah hebatnya kekayaan apabila berada di tangan yang betul.

Ianya akan terus memberi manfaat buat ummat. Kan?

Jom sama-sama kita bercita-cita untuk jadi umat Islam yang kaya dan memberi manfaat buat ummat. 

Followlah @FezzaHussin ramai-ramai. Semangat sikit nak menulis 🤣
Translated Text:
That's how great wealth is when it's in the right hands.

It will continue to benefit the community. Right?

Let's all aspire to be wealthy Muslims and benefit the community.

Follow @FezzaHussin a lot. A little spirit to write 🤣

Text:
Essentially dia ada 2 types of tracking:

- Browser-Side Tracking

- Server-Side Tracking
Translated Text:
Essentially dia ada 2 types of tracking:

- Browser-Side Tracking

- Server-Side Tracking

Text:
Browser-side tracking ni basically mcm cookies. 

Data collection method berdasarkan user's web browser.

Bila kita pasang pixel, FB directly receive this behavioral data that is use for signals either for targeting or attribution. https://t.co/9RsaacPKyN
Translated Text:
Browser-side tracking ni basically mcm cookies. 

Data collection method berdasarkan user's web browser.

Bila kita pasang pixel, FB directly receive this behavioral data that is use for signals either for targeting or attribution. https://t.co/9RsaacPKyN

Text: Server-side tracking pula basically instead of FB gets the data directly, we provide it to them via a server through an API. https://t.co/JotJnsas2t
Translated Text: Server-side tracking pula basically instead of FB gets the data directly, we provide it to them via a server through an API. https://t.co/JotJnsas2t

Text: Since by 2023, we're embarking on cookieless world, CAPI is the answer for tracking & attribution in the world that abides by the privacy laws. https://t.co/ZqMyrNANQc
Translated Text: Since by 2023, we're embarking on cookieless world, CAPI is the answer for tracking & attribution in the world that abides by the privacy laws. https://t.co/ZqMyrNANQc

Text:
In a recent webinar, FB ada predict yg conversion optimization with web pixel would no longer be possible as early as end of 2021!

In other words, kalau u tak guna CAPI, u boleh guna lower value actions mcm clicks saja. 

https://t.co/omM93lOaKJ
Translated Text:
In a recent webinar, FB ada predict yg conversion optimization with web pixel would no longer be possible as early as end of 2021!

In other words, kalau u tak guna CAPI, u boleh guna lower value actions mcm clicks saja. 

https://t.co/omM93lOaKJ

Text:
So apa advantages CAPI ni?

Dia bg kita opportunity to improve the quality of our data & ad performance overall.

When CAPI sends data to FB, FB akan match dgn actions which contribute to attributions.

Its advisable to run both Pixel & CAPI together to maximize data matching. https://t.co/S9AAQUEYie
Translated Text:
So apa advantages CAPI ni?

Dia bg kita opportunity to improve the quality of our data & ad performance overall.

When CAPI sends data to FB, FB akan match dgn actions which contribute to attributions.

Its advisable to run both Pixel & CAPI together to maximize data matching. https://t.co/S9AAQUEYie

Text: In one case study, they report 23% conversion lift & 26% incremental sales when running both Pixel & CAPI simultaneously. https://t.co/nzflx1pJ23
Translated Text: In one case study, they report 23% conversion lift & 26% incremental sales when running both Pixel & CAPI simultaneously. https://t.co/nzflx1pJ23

Text:
Before you're sold to implement CAPI, do know that its a bit more tricky to implement it vs pixel & probably need a developer to implement this to your site.

Since its an API, you could also expect to see some infrastructure costs too.
Translated Text:

Text:
In terms of ranking, IG ada share guidelines on content yg akan didownrank in search, antaranya:

- repurposed unoriginal content from another source without adding material value
- promote a contest or giveaway
- miracle health products
Translated Text:
In terms of ranking, IG ada share guidelines on content yg akan didownrank in search, antaranya:

- repurposed unoriginal content from another source without adding material value
- promote a contest or giveaway
- miracle health products

Text: What this means is that kalau your account do such contents, you still boleh dpt likes & comments from followers but your reach in discovery will be limited.

- Accurate & higher quality data gained

- Transparent & compliant with laws since customer opt-in themselves

Jadi kenapa ZPD ni penting?

- Higher relevancy as its directly feed by customer

Text:
1 key thing to note is that, brand perlu telus dgn penggunaan data yg dikumpul.

Jika ada value exchange offers, etc. dgn pemberian data, be upfront on it.

A study by Forbes noted that over 90% of consumers say transparency by a brand is important to their purchase decisions.
Translated Text:
1 key thing to note is that, brand perlu telus dgn penggunaan data yg dikumpul.

Jika ada value exchange offers, etc. dgn pemberian data, be upfront on it.

A study by Forbes noted that over 90% of consumers say transparency by a brand is important to their purchase decisions.

Text:

- Customer surveys
- Questionnaires
- Email opt-ins
- Competitions
- In-app preferences
- Social media stories (polls, etc)

- Customer surveys
